<s> yet another rain record goes with august not even half way through , it was official that the first eight months of 1997 were already the wettest ever on record . </s>
<s> by 5 am today ( thursday ) , the running rainfall total at the hong_kong observatory since the beginning of the year had reached 2,611.3 millimetres , </s>
<s> soaring past the previous record of 2,610.4 millimetres registered in 1973 . </s>
<s> a wet spell generated by the moist southwest monsoon , in addition to the rain brought by typhoon victor earlier in the month , meant that rainfall figure so far this month has already exceeded the august normal of 391.4 millimetres . </s>
<s> this followed hard on the heel of an exceptionally wet june and july whose monthly totals were both more than twice the normal figures . </s>
<s> in fact , the combined june and july rainfall total of 1,529.6 millimetres already went into the record books as the highest ever . </s>
<s> the normal annual rainfall for hong_kong is 2,214.3 millimetres . </s>
<s> hong_kong 's external trade statistics for june 1997 </s>
<s> the census and statistics department today ( thursday ) released detailed statistics on external trade with breakdown by country / territory and commodity for june 1997 . </s>
<s> in june 1997 , the value of re @-@ exports increased by 10 % over a year earlier to $ 101.1 billion , </s>
<s> while that of domestic exports increased by 5.9 % to $ 17.9 billion . </s>
<s> meanwhile , imports increased by 6.4 % to $ 131.7 billion . </s>
<s> comparing june 1997 with june 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to taiwan ( + 17 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland of china ( + 15 % ) , the united_states ( + 12 % ) , the united kingdom ( + 11 % ) , </s>
<s> france ( + 6.4 % ) , the netherlands ( + 6.4 % ) , </s>
<s> japan ( + 4.7 % ) and singapore ( + 1.1 % ) . </s>
<s> however , the value of re @-@ exports to south korea and germany decreased by 12 % and 1.4 % respectively . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to taiwan ( + 11 % ) , </s>
<s> the united_states ( + 11 % ) , the netherlands ( + 8.1 % ) , </s>
<s> the united kingdom ( + 5.7 % ) , the mainland of china ( + 5.1 % ) , </s>
<s> singapore ( + 2.9 % ) and france ( + 2.7 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to germany ( - 4.9 % ) , </s>
<s> south korea ( - 1.9 % ) and japan ( - 0.6 % ) . </s>
<s> taking all destinations together , the value of re @-@ exports in the first half of 1997 , at $ 575.1 billion , </s>
<s> increased by 4.4 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996 , more notable increases in the value of re @-@ exports were registered for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 7.2 billion or 23 % ) ; </s>
<s> clothing ( by $ 5.1 billion or 12 % ) ; </s>
<s> electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 4.8 billion or 8.3 % ) ; </s>
<s> textiles ( by $ 3.3 billion or 7.1 % ) ; </s>
<s> and miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of baby carriages , toys , games and sporting goods ( by $ 3.1 billion or 4.9 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , decreases in the value of re @-@ exports were registered for telecommunications and sound recording and reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 2.2 billion or 4.1 % ) ; </s>
<s> and plastics in primary forms ( by $ 638 million or 4.4 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing june 1997 with june 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to france ( + 31 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland of china ( + 13 % ) , the netherlands ( + 12 % ) , canada ( + 11 % ) , </s>
<s> the united_states ( + 7.3 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( + 3.9 % ) and japan ( + 2.6 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to singapore ( - 18 % ) , </s>
<s> germany ( - 4.5 % ) and the united kingdom ( - 1.6 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to france ( + 21 % ) , </s>
<s> the netherlands ( + 13 % ) and the mainland of china ( + 0.8 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to singapore ( - 22 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( - 8.9 % ) , japan ( - 7.9 % ) , </s>
<s> germany ( - 4.8 % ) , canada ( - 4.7 % ) , </s>
<s> the united_states ( - 4.1 % ) and the united kingdom ( - 2.1 % ) . </s>
<s> taking all destinations together , the value of domestic exports in the first half of 1997 , at $ 95.9 billion , </s>
<s> decreased by 3.4 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996 , more notable decreases in the value of domestic exports were registered for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 1.2 billion or 17 % ) ; </s>
<s> photographic apparatus , </s>
<s> equipment and supplies , optical goods , watches and clocks ( by $ 741 million or 10 % ) ; </s>
<s> textiles ( by $ 409 million or 6.1 % ) ; </s>
<s> miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of jewellery , goldsmiths ' and silversmiths ' wares ( by $ 322 million or 3.8 % ) ; </s>
<s> and manufactures of metals ( by $ 309 million or 15 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , </s>
<s> more notable increases in the value of domestic exports were registered for professional , scientific and controlling instruments and apparatus ( by $ 730 million or 48 % ) ; </s>
<s> and electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 493 million or 3.2 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing june 1997 with june 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of imports from malaysia ( + 32 % ) , </s>
<s> the united kingdom ( + 27 % ) , italy ( + 19 % ) , </s>
<s> germany ( + 18 % ) , japan ( + 16 % ) , the mainland of china ( + 6.9 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( + 4.3 % ) and south korea ( + 0.4 % ) . </s>
<s> however , the value of imports from the united_states and singapore decreased by 3.1 % and 1.3 % respectively . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of imports from the united kingdom ( + 18 % ) , </s>
<s> malaysia ( + 18 % ) , germany ( + 11 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland of china ( + 6.4 % ) , japan ( + 4.4 % ) , </s>
<s> the united_states ( + 2.4 % ) and italy ( + 0.5 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of imports from taiwan ( - 2.0 % ) , </s>
<s> south korea ( - 1.8 % ) and singapore ( - 0.4 % ) . </s>
<s> taking all sources together , the value of imports in the first half of 1997 , at $ 767.5 billion , </s>
<s> increased by 4.6 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996 , more notable increases in the value of imports were registered for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 10.0 billion or 27 % ) ; </s>
<s> electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 8.5 billion or 9.1 % ) ; </s>
