<s> the territory development department will carry out a series of road improvement works in tuen mun . </s>
<s> the works will include the construction of a new bypass road from tuen mun area 45 near butterfly beach to the interchange of lung mun road and wong chu road along the foothills of castle peak . </s>
<s> realignment works will also be carried out at the existing slip road from tuen mun road ( tuen mun bound ) to wong chu road , </s>
<s> a section of siu lun street near siu lun court , a section of lung mun road near san shek wan light rail transit station , </s>
<s> the access tracks near san shek wan tsuen as well as a section of lung mun road near butterfly beach . </s>
<s> in addition , noise barriers ranging from three to five metres in height and noise enclosures of 230 metres in length and 10 metres in height will be built along wong chu road and tuen mun road interchange . </s>
<s> the construction of these barriers will help reduce noise pollution to residents in the nearby public housing estates . </s>
<s> the works form part of the port development in tuen mun which will provide the necessary access to river trade terminal and special industrial developments in tuen mun area 38 near siu lang shui . </s>
<s> site formation works for ma on shan development </s>
<s> the territory development department will carry out extensive infrastructural works in ma on shan to facilitate development of the area . </s>
<s> the works will form part of the continuing programme for ma on shan development phase iii. </s>
<s> the works will comprise site formation and construction of about four kilometres of roads , </s>
<s> a road bridge , a pedestrian subway , drainage systems and associated landscaping works in areas 77 and 86 of ma on shan . </s>
<s> upon completion , the area will be available for housing development to accommodate about 30,000 residents . </s>
<s> works will begin in november for completion in about 30 months . </s>
