<s> northern nt drainage study for flood control measures </s>
<s> the drainage services department has commissioned a drainage master plan ( dmp ) study in the northern new territories with a view to recommending short and long @-@ term flood control measures in the area . </s>
<s> the study will cover san tin , ta kwu ling , sheung shui and fanling . </s>
<s> " the northern new territories includes a number of low @-@ lying flood plains susceptible to serious , </s>
<s> frequent flooding which has been exacerbated by rapid developments in the past decade , " the assistant director of drainage services ( operations and maintenance ) , </s>
<s> mr raymond cheung tat @-@ kwing , said after signing the consultancy study agreement today ( tuesday ) . </s>
<s> " the two @-@ year study will examine the existing drainage system in a comprehensive manner and recommend measures to upgrade it to reduce the flooding hazard . </s>
<s> " it will also develop a computerised asset management system to facilitate future planning , </s>
<s> management and operation of the drainage system , " he said . </s>
<s> under the study , closed circuit televisions and manhole surveys will be used to examine and assess the conditions and adequacies of the existing stormwater drainage system . </s>
<s> it will also set up computer models to simulate the performance of the drainage system under different rainstorm conditions . </s>
<s> in their study report , the consultants will identify and recommend improvement works including both first aid measures and long @-@ term improvement measures . </s>
<s> " first aid measures will provide immediate relief to the flooding problem and will be carried out quickly after the study , </s>
<s> " mr cheung said . </s>
<s> " long @-@ term improvement measures will involve the upgrading and extension of the existing drainage system to meet the needs arising from the development of the area . we expect the first package of works to be carried out as soon as the major river training projects is completed in 2002 , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> among the major river training projects , </s>
<s> stage 1 of the shenzhen river regulation project was completed while construction works for stage 2 are in progress . </s>
<s> the training of the indus and beas rivers will be carried out afterwards . the current study is the fifth of seven dmp studies which cover all flood @-@ prone areas in the territory . </s>
<s> the first study began in january 1996 in yuen long , kam tin , ngau tam mei and tin shui wai . </s>
<s> all the studies are scheduled for completion before end 1999 . </s>
<s> the study in the northern new territories will be carried out by maunsell consultants asia limited at a cost of $ 13 million . </s>
<s> amending the protection of the harbour ordinance </s>
<s> the acting chief executive in council had approved today ( tuesday ) that three amendments should be made to the protection of the harbour ordinance to avoid any possible delay to the non @-@ reclamation works which are not reclamation in the normal sense and to reflect accurately the geographical application of the ordinance . </s>
<s> the ordinance was enacted on june 27 , </s>
<s> 1997 carrying with it a main provision which is a principle of " presumption against reclamation " in the central harbour and a requirement for all public officers to have a legal duty towards that principle in the exercise of their powers . </s>
<s> a government spokesman said that having completed a study on the legal implications , </s>
<s> it was proposed that the ordinance should be amended by narrowing the definition of " reclamation " to mean only work that would turn an area of water into an area usable for dry land purposes and to ameliorate the preamble to reflect accurately the purpose of the enacted ordinance . </s>
<s> the spokesman said that under section 2 of the ordinance , the legal advice is that the definition of " reclamation " if given its widest literal effect , </s>
<s> would create an unrealistic situation in which even the approval for repair of a cable laid on the seabed , or the routine maintenance of facilities within the geographical boundary of the central harbour , would be subject to the " presumption against reclamation " principle . </s>
<s> " for the avoidance of doubt , </s>
<s> an amendment is desirable to exclude projects which are not ' reclamation ' in the normal sense , i.e. projects that would turn the area of water into an area usable for dry land purposes , " he said . </s>
<s> the preamble of the ordinance states that it is " an ordinance to protect and preserve the harbour by establishing a presumption against reclamation in the harbour and by requiring such reclamation to be approved by the legislative council , </s>
<s> the spokesman said that it was obvious that while the first of the declared purposes was effected by the ordinance , the second and third purposes were not . </s>
<s> they relate to those parts of the original bill which were not enacted and should therefore be deleted from the preamble . </s>
<s> moreover , to reflect accurately the geographical application of the principle , </s>
<s> the ordinance should be amended by inserting " central " between " the " and " harbour " in the preamble and the title of section 3. </s>
<s> " the amendments to the ordinance would avoid possible delay to the non @-@ reclamation works which are not reclamation in the normal sense but are essential for the normal operation of our economy , </s>
<s> " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> the secretary for health and welfare , mrs katherine fok , visited the hong_kong society for rehabilitation in pokfulam today ( tuesday ) to see for herself the services provided for people with a disability . </s>
<s> accompanied by the commissioner for rehabilitation , mr augustine choi , mrs fok was briefed on the rehabus service and the vocational rehabilitation and re @-@ training services provided by the society . </s>
<s> the rehabus service , divided into scheduled route service and dial @-@ a @-@ ride ( dar ) service , </s>
<s> provides a territory @-@ wide transport network which enables disabled people to commute to schools , work places or activities centres . </s>
<s> in 1997 / 98 , the government recurrent subvention for the rehabus service is estimated at $ 23.3 million , an increase by more than 190 per cent over 1992 / 93 . </s>
<s> currently , there are 54 vehicles providing scheduled route service from mondays to saturdays . another 14 vehicles are being deployed to provide full @-@ day dar service which is a personalised pre @-@ booked transport service . </s>
<s> in 1998 / 99 , five additional rehabuses will be provided and facilities on the existing rehabuses will also be improved . </s>
<s> mrs fok also learnt about the services provided by the vocational rehabilitation and re @-@ training centre ( vrcc ) including job assessment and evaluation , career counselling and re @-@ training , referral for placement and on @-@ the @-@ job follow @-@ up . </s>
