<s> producer price indices for manufacturing industries </s>
<s> the producer price index for the manufacturing sector as a whole in the second quarter of 1997 was virtually unchanged , when compared with the same quarter of 1996 , according to the results of a survey released today ( tuesday ) by the census and statistics department . </s>
<s> analysed by industry , the producer prices of the consumer electrical and electronic products industry showed a decrease of 5.8 % . </s>
<s> decreases in producer prices were also recorded in the fabricated metal products ( except machinery and equipment ) industry ( - 3.7 % ) , the machinery , equipment , </s>
<s> apparatus , parts and components industry ( - 2.3 % ) , and the plastic products industry ( - 0.5 % ) . </s>
<s> however , the producer prices of the paper products and printing industry and the textiles ( including knitting ) industry increased by 3.7 % and 1.5 % respectively . </s>
<s> the producer prices of the wearing apparel ( except footwear ) industry also increased slightly , by 0.8 % . </s>
<s> comparing the second quarter of 1997 with the first quarter of 1997 , the producer price index for the manufacturing sector recorded a slight increase of 0.4 % . </s>
<s> the producer price index , with 1990 as the base period , reflects changes in the prices of local manufacturing output . </s>
<s> producer prices refer to the actual prices ( net of any discounts or rebates allowed to buyers , plus any surcharges ) received by manufacturers . </s>
<s> transportation and other incidental charges are not included . </s>
<s> the producer price indices for manufacturing industries are compiled from data on producer prices of industrial goods / services collected from the quarterly survey of industrial production . </s>
<s> the survey also collects production data for the compilation of the indices of industrial production which measure the changes in volume of local manufacturing output . </s>
<s> more detailed information can be obtained from the " quarterly producer price indices for manufacturing industries , 2 nd quarter 1997 " report , </s>
<s> which is on sale at $ 8 a copy at the government publications sales centre , ground floor , low block , queensway government offices , 66 queensway , hong_kong , </s>
<s> or at the census and statistics department publications unit , 19 th floor , wanchai tower , 12 harbour road , wan chai . </s>
<s> enquiries about the indices may be directed to the general economic surveys section of the census and statistics department at telephone 2805 6643 . </s>
<s> the following table shows the percentage changes in the producer price indices . </s>
<s> quarterly producer price indices for manufacturing industries ( 1990 = 100 ) </s>
<s> index for % change over 2 nd qtr. 2 nd qtr. 1 st qtr. manufacturing industry 1997 1996 1997 </s>
<s> 1. wearing apparel ( except footwear ) 112.3 + 0.8 + 0.7 </s>
<s> 2. textiles ( including knitting ) 117.2 + 1.5 + 1.5 </s>
<s> 3. paper products and printing 129.3 + 3.7 + 2.9 </s>
<s> 4. plastic products 117.0 - 0.5 + 2.5 </s>
<s> 5. fabricated metal products ( except machinery and equipment ) 106.1 - 3.7 * </s>
<s> 6. consumer electrical and electronic products 80.8 - 5.8 - 2.0 </s>
