<s> october issue of hk monthly digest of statistics on sale </s>
<s> four feature articles entitled " review of real estate activities in hong_kong " , " drug abuse situation in hong_kong in 1996 " , " hong_kong energy statistics , </s>
<s> 1987 @-@ 1996 " and " a profile of the elderly , 1996 " are published in the october 1997 issue of the hong_kong monthly digest of statistics , which is now on sale . </s>
<s> " review of real estate activities in hong_kong " </s>
<s> this article analyses the performance , structural characteristics and business concentration of the real estate sector during the period from 1986 to 1995. the analyses are based mainly on data collected in the annual survey of building , </s>
<s> construction and real estate sectors -- in respect of the reference years 1986 to 1995 . </s>
<s> for analyses on the composition of real estate projects for more recent periods , reference is made to the latest available statistics for 1996 and the first half year of 1997 from the quarterly survey of construction output . </s>
<s> " drug abuse situation in hong_kong in 1996 " </s>
<s> drug abuse has for many years been a problem of concern to our community . </s>
<s> the central registry of drug abuse ( crda ) currently maintained by the narcotics division of the government secretariat collects , collates and analyses information on drug abuse for the purpose of monitoring changes in trends of drug abuse and characteristics of the local drug abusers . </s>
<s> in 1996 , a total of 19,626 drug abusers were reported to the crda , </s>
<s> representing an increase of 1.5 per cent compared with 19,343 in 1995 . </s>
<s> the upward trend of drug abuse among young people observed in 1990 s has been reversed in the past two years . however , the upward trend of drug abuse among females since 1992 persisted in 1996 . </s>
<s> more analyses on the characteristics of drug abusers reported to the crda in 1996 , such as sex and age , </s>
<s> district of residence , types of drug abused , age of first drug abuse and reason for current drug abuse are included in this article . </s>
<s> " hong_kong energy statistics , 1987 - 1996 " </s>
<s> hong_kong does not have any natural reserves of energy . </s>
<s> supply of different forms of primary energy ( e.g. coal and oil products ) are entirely from external sources . </s>
<s> a substantial share of this energy is converted into secondary energy such as electricity and gas for final consumption . </s>
<s> this article summarises the developments related to the supply and demand of energy in hong_kong during the period from 1987 to 1996 . </s>
<s> " a profile of the elderly , 1996 " </s>
<s> the 1996 population by @-@ census conducted by the census and statistics department provides a rich source of information on the demographic and socio @-@ economic characteristics of the population in hong_kong . </s>
<s> it enables studies to be undertaken not only on various facets of the community but also on specific sub @-@ groups of the population such as the elderly . </s>
<s> according to the by @-@ census , persons aged 65 and over constituted 10 per cent of the whole population in hong_kong . </s>
<s> the corresponding figure was 14 per cent in respect of persons aged 60 and over . </s>
<s> over the past decade , the population has been ageing . </s>
<s> it is thus important to gain a better understanding of the characteristics of the elderly . </s>
<s> this article aims to provide an overview of the elderly population in hong_kong based on the by @-@ census results . </s>
