<s> future expansion of hong_kong 's expressway network </s>
<s> the effect of additional links and crossings , are key aspects in determining the future expansion of hong_kong 's expressway and trunk road network , </s>
<s> the director of highways , mr kenneth leung kwok @-@ sun , said today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> addressing a hong_kong institution of engineers symposium on " engineering civil infrastructure for the future " , </s>
<s> mr leung said plans were on the drawing board for a new strategic link in hong_kong 's road network - the western highway - to provide not only additional capacity within hong_kong but also the opportunity for improved links with the pearl river delta area . </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> the highway will connect at its northern end to a new two @-@ kilometre long suspension bridge at kwai shek crossing the international sea channel to tsing lung tau . </s>
<s> " it will rival the recently completed tsing ma bridge both in scale and in grandeur , " mr leung said . </s>
<s> after landing west of tsing lung tau , the road will link to the tuen mun road near so kwun wat and then head north through a four @-@ kilometre long tunnel to meet the yuen long highway near lam tei . </s>
<s> the route is also planned to proceed further in the north westerly direction under the castle peak range eventually linking with the proposed deep bay cross border connection to shekou and provide a direct link between the western side of hong_kong and the shenzhen @-@ guangzhou highway . </s>
<s> he told the symposium that the new western highway would have a considerable impact on development on the western side of the territory . </s>
<s> its commissioning was expected to open up the south @-@ western side of the hong_kong island for residential development for up to 50,000 people and provide some considerable relief to the congested aberdeen tunnel , he said . </s>
<s> the new highway would enhance the attraction of the green island reclamation , which was planned to accommodate a population of over 124,000 , </s>
<s> as a development with convenient access , he added . </s>
<s> he noted that the new route would also open up the western new territories for further residential development and provide more direct access from these areas to the central business districts in kowloon and on hong_kong island . </s>
<s> the north west new territories ( nwnt ) would take up major portions of hong_kong 's future population growth with a planned population of 1.45 million or about 18 per cent of hong_kong 's total by the year 2011 , mr leung said . </s>
<s> apart from saving cost and time for journeys between the nwnt and the urban area , </s>
<s> the route would also provide some much @-@ needed relief to both the tuen mun road and the route 3 country park section , which by the middle of the next decade would be approaching capacity , he added . </s>
<s> " further north , </s>
<s> the route will provide direct access from the new towns of yuen long and tin shui wai to the urban area and shorter and cheaper journeys for commuters , " mr leung said . </s>
<s> in addition to the western highway project , mr leung said the highways department was also planning a number of other extensions to the expressway network . </s>
<s> among these are : </s>
<s> * route 9 from tsing yi to mei foo which will provide some much @-@ needed relief to the route 3 corridor near the busy container port ; </s>
<s> * route 16 which will provide a direct link from route 9 and the container port to sha tin and the eastern side of the new territories ; </s>
<s> * the central kowloon route running in an east @-@ west direction linking yau ma tei and the development at the kai tak airport site once the airport has relocated to chek lap kok ; and </s>
<s> * the central @-@ wanchai bypass which will provide relief for the roads in central business district . </s>
<s> apart from major expressway plans in the future , mr leung also spoke on cross border links . </s>
<s> he said : " fundamental to the growth and prosperity of hong_kong will be its future links to the pearl river delta area . </s>
<s> " it is clear that with the recent growth in trade between hong_kong and other parts of china as demonstrated by the growth in cross border traffic , </s>
<s> the road networks on both sides of the crossing must be upgraded to meet forecasts of increasing demand . " </s>
<s> on railway network , mr leung said a new rail extension with a station at lok ma chau was being proposed as the next stage of west rail . </s>
<s> it will provide relief to the congested crossing at lo wu and a connection to the proposed underground rail system currently planned in shenzhen . </s>
<s> on the road side , </s>
<s> mr leung said improvements to cross border links would include proposals to increase the capacity of the existing border crossings by expanding the number of kiosks and improving the capacity of approach road network . </s>
<s> another method would be the implementation of new border crossings that had been investigated in the crosslinks study , he said . </s>
<s> this includes the connection to the proposed lingdingyang bridge and the deep bay crossing , both of which will need the construction of substantial access routes within the territory to tie them into the strategic highway network . </s>
<s> stage one of the crosslinks study for investigation of traffic demand has commenced early this year , </s>
<s> whilst stage two for investigations on environment , ecology , land use planning , land acquisition , economic viability and preliminary project feasibility / preliminary design will start next month , mr leung said . </s>
