<s> the office of telecommunications authority ( ofta ) today ( friday ) issued official guidelines to paging service operators on the transmission of paging messages . </s>
<s> the purpose of the guidelines is to reiterate to the paging service operators that they are not allowed to screen messages at their own will under the telecommunication ordinance . </s>
<s> the guidelines , however , allow paging operators to refrain from transmitting messages that are obscene , vulgar or connected with illegal purposes . </s>
<s> " in view of the public concern about paging companies refusing to take messages for their customers , </s>
<s> ofta considers it necessary to issue formal guidelines to the paging service operators to remind them to comply with the law and licence conditions , " an ofta spokesman said , adding that a complaint about two paging companies was being investigated by ofta . </s>
<s> following is the guidelines issued by the telecommunications authority to licensees for public radio paging service under the telecommunication ordinance on the transmission of paging messages : </s>
<s> in accordance with section 24 of the telecommunication ordinance , a licensee providing public radio paging services ( " paging service licensee " ) commits an offence if it , among other things , </s>
<s> wilfully destroys , secretes or alters any message that it has received for transmission or delivery , or wilfully abstains from transmitting any message or wilfully detains or delays any message . </s>
<s> a paging service licensee is also required under licence conditions to provide a service satisfactory to the telecommunications authority ( ta ) . </s>
<s> the ta notes that it is a common practice in the paging industry for the paging service licensees to include in their service contracts with their customers clauses that authorise the licensees not to transmit messages that are obscene or vulgar in nature or messages that are connected with illegal purposes . </s>
<s> this is acceptable to the ta as these clauses in the contracts are necessary to protect the interests of the paging operators and their customers . </s>
<s> however , the paging operators must not go beyond these clauses and refuse transmission of an otherwise acceptable and lawful message . </s>
<s> the ta therefore issues these guidelines to the paging service licensees on the handling of messages given to them for transmission . </s>
<s> the ta would like to make it clear that under the law and licence conditions , </s>
<s> a paging service licensee has the obligation to transmit a message given to it for transmission , except those messages which have been agreed by the customer not to be transmitted or messages the transmission of which would be in breach of the law . </s>
