<s> higher levy to finance occupational safety & health council </s>
<s> the government has proposed to increase the rate of the employees ' compensation insurance levy ( the levy ) by one percentage point to generate more income for the occupational safety and health council ( oshc ) to enable it to undertake an expanded programme of activities . </s>
<s> the oshc is a statutory body tasked with encouraging and promoting higher standards of occupational safety and health in hong_kong . </s>
<s> as a self @-@ financing body , the council 's major source of income is the levy imposed on the insurance premia of all employees ' compensation insurance policies which employers are required to take out under the employees ' compensation ordinance . </s>
<s> the current rate of the levy is set at 3.5 per cent on the insurance premium and of this one per cent will go to the oshc . </s>
<s> under the employees ' compensation insurance levy ( rate of levy ) ( amendment ) order 1997 and the employees ' compensation insurance levies ordinance ( amendment of schedule 2 ) notice 1997 gazetted today ( friday ) , </s>
<s> it is proposed that the levy rate be increased by one percentage point and that the additional levy income be channelled to the oshc . </s>
<s> a government spokesman said that the increase was expected to yield an extra annual income of $ 25.2 million for the oshc which had experienced an operational deficit since 1996 @-@ 97 as a result of its increased level of activities and a drop in its levy income . </s>
<s> the oshc has expanded its activities steadily over the years and in response to the recommendations of the 1995 review of industrial safety in hong_kong , </s>
<s> it has , since 1996 @-@ 97 , </s>
<s> substantially enhanced its training , education , information and research activities . </s>
<s> the oshc also has the statutory responsibility of promoting and publicising the occupational safety and health ordinance enacted in may this year . </s>
<s> " this is a milestone legislation as it introduces , for the first time , occupational safety and health protection in the non @-@ industrial sectors , </s>
<s> covering some 1.8 million employees , " the spokesman said , adding that the council will have to provide training to a large number of management staff and employees in the non @-@ industrial sectors . </s>
<s> both the labour advisory board and the employees ' compensation insurance levy management board have indicated their support for the proposed increase in the levy rate . </s>
<s> the amendment order and the notice will be tabled at the provisional legislative council on october 29 , 1997 . </s>
<s> rate adjustment for volunteer pensions </s>
<s> the volunteer and naval volunteer pensions ordinance ( amendment of schedules ) order 1997 was gazetted today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> " the purpose of the order is to adjust the rates for the payment of pension , gratuities and other allowances to beneficiaries to reflect the increase in cost of living in 1997 / 98 , </s>
<s> " a health and welfare bureau spokesman said . </s>
<s> the volunteer and naval volunteer pensions ordinance was introduced in 1950 to provide for the payment of pensions and allowances to veterans of the two volunteer forces who fought in the defence of hong_kong during the second world war . </s>
<s> in previous years , payments have been made by reference to the uk naval , military and air forces etc. ( disablement and death ) service pensions order . </s>
<s> a local payment scheme was introduced on june 20 , 1997. under the scheme , </s>
<s> the secretary for health and welfare may adjust the rates of payment from time to time by order in the gazette . </s>
<s> " it is our intention to adjust the pension rates annually in line with the pension increase awarded to retired civil servants . this increase is set at six per cent for 1997 / 98 . </s>
<s> " however , as the local ordinance only came into effect on june 20 , </s>
<s> beneficiaries will not receive any inflation adjustment for the period between april and june 19 , </s>
<s> 1997 unless an adjustment is made , " the spokesman added . </s>
<s> " for reasons of equity , we therefore propose to pay beneficiaries a supplement which they would otherwise have received under the uk order between this period . </s>
<s> " the adjustment for the period june 20 , 1997 to march 31 , </s>
<s> 1998 payable by government is therefore 7.2 per cent which equates to a six per cent increase over a 12 month period , " he said . </s>
<s> statistics on ocean vessel and seaborne cargo </s>
<s> in the second quarter of 1997 , 11,138 ocean vessels with a total capacity of 50.5 million net registered tons entered hong_kong , according to the figures released today ( friday ) by the census and statistics department . </s>
<s> compared with the second quarter of 1996 , the number of vessels increased by 12 % and capacity increased by 11 % . </s>
<s> net registered ton ( nrt ) is a unit measure in volume terms of the space of a vessel available for carrying passengers or goods . </s>
<s> one nrt is equivalent to 100 cubic feet . </s>
<s> during the same period , there were 11,166 outgoing ocean vessels with a total capacity of 50.2 million net registered tons . </s>
<s> compared with the second quarter of 1996 , the number of vessels increased by 13 % , and capacity increased by 11 % . </s>
<s> in the second quarter of 1997 , the total tonnage of seaborne inward cargo , comprising seaborne imports and seaborne inward transhipment , </s>
<s> was estimated at 23.7 million tonnes , representing an increase of 10 % over the same quarter in 1996 . </s>
<s> the respective increases in the total tonnage of seaborne imports and seaborne inward transhipment were 9 % and 16 % . </s>
<s> during the same period , the total tonnage of seaborne outward cargo , </s>
<s> comprising seaborne exports ( domestic exports plus re @-@ exports ) and seaborne outward transhipment , </s>
<s> was estimated at 10.5 million tonnes , representing an increase of 13 % over the same quarter in 1996 . </s>
<s> the respective increases in the total tonnage of seaborne exports and seaborne outward transhipment were 8 % and 20 % . </s>
<s> of the seaborne inward cargo , </s>
<s> 83 % in terms of tonnage were seaborne imports and 17 % were seaborne inward transhipment . </s>
<s> fifty @-@ six per cent of these cargoes were containerised . </s>
<s> of the seaborne outward cargo , 57 % in terms of tonnage were seaborne exports and 43 % were seaborne outward transhipment . </s>
<s> eighty @-@ seven per cent of them were containerised cargo . </s>
<s> in the second quarter of 1997 , the top five countries / territories of loading for seaborne inward cargo were singapore ( accounted for 16 % in tonnage terms ) , japan ( 13 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( 11 % ) , mainland of china ( 10 % ) and the republic of korea ( 9 % ) . </s>
<s> the top five countries / territories of discharge for seaborne outward cargo were mainland of china ( 26 % ) , the usa ( 20 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( 7 % ) , japan ( 5 % ) and federal republic of germany ( 4 % ) . </s>
<s> the top five principal commodities of seaborne inward cargo in tonnage terms included petroleum , petroleum products and related materials ( 21 % ) ; </s>
<s> iron and steel ( 8 % ) ; </s>
<s> artificial resins and plastic materials ( 8 % ) ; </s>
<s> paper and paper products ( 8 % ) and coal , coke and briquettes ( 6 % ) . </s>
<s> the top five principal commodities of seaborne outward cargo in tonnage terms included machinery ( 13 % ) ; </s>
<s> other manufactured goods classified chiefly by material ( 10 % ) ; </s>
<s> other manufactured articles ( 9 % ) ; </s>
<s> petroleum , petroleum products and related materials ( 6 % ) and toys ( 5 % ) . </s>
<s> ocean vessel statistics are compiled primarily from general declarations submitted to the marine department by ship masters or authorised shipping agents and cover all ocean vessels entering and leaving hong_kong , excluding yachts and pleasure craft . </s>
<s> seaborne cargo statistics are compiled from a sample of consignments listed in the ocean cargo manifests supplied by shipping companies or agents to the census and statistics department . </s>
<s> more details of ocean vessel and seaborne cargo statistics for the second quarter of 1997 are contained in the bilingual report entitled " hong_kong shipping statistics , april - june 1997 " . </s>
<s> the report is now on sale at $ 57 a copy at the government publications centre , ground floor , low block , queensway government offices , </s>
<s> 66 queensway , hong_kong ; </s>
<s> and the publications unit of the census and statistics department , 19 th floor , wanchai tower , 12 harbour road , wan chai . </s>
<s> enquiries on statistics contained in the report may be directed to the shipping and cargo statistics section of the census and statistics department on telephone 2582 4887 . </s>
