<s> beat drugs fund invites applications </s>
<s> organisations are now invited to apply for grants from the beat drugs fund for organising worthwhile anti @-@ drugs activities to fight against drug abuse . applications should be submitted on or before december 31 , 1997 . </s>
<s> the fund has been set up by the government to finance anti @-@ drugs activities which help reduce the problem of drug abuse , particularly amongst the youth , </s>
<s> and to promote community @-@ wide efforts and programmes for combating drug abuse . </s>
<s> in 1996 / 97 , 53 projects were funded with grants totalling $ 20.4 million . </s>
<s> this included about $ 14.3 million for 24 drug treatment and rehabilitation projects , $ 5.9 million for 27 projects on preventive education and publicity , and $ 0.2 million for two international conferences to promote understanding on drug abuse . </s>
<s> the spokesman for the beat drugs fund association pointed out that the association has revised the funding criteria and introduced new ones to maximise the effective use of the fund . </s>
<s> elaborating on the new criteria , the spokesman said that projects to be funded should be non @-@ profit @-@ making in nature , </s>
<s> and requests for grants from commercial enterprises or individuals would not be considered . requests for grants exceeding $ 3 million would normally not be considered . </s>
<s> worthwhile projects adopting the anti @-@ drugs abuse themes designated by the governing committee of the association would be given a higher funding priority . </s>
<s> for the year 1997 / 98 , the themes are promoting family care and parental participation in the fight against drug abuse , </s>
<s> and preventing the youth , particularly those at risk , from experimenting with drugs . </s>
<s> also , innovative projects will be accorded a higher priority . </s>
<s> for non @-@ capital works , the fund will only consider those of short @-@ term nature and with duration of not more than two years . </s>
<s> the detailed funding criteria are contained in the " guide to application for a grant from the beat drugs fund " . </s>
<s> the guide and application forms are available from the beat drugs fund association , </s>
<s> care of narcotics division , 23 rd floor , high block , queensway government offices , 66 queensway ; home affairs department and all district offices ; </s>
<s> and the hong_kong council of social service at duke of windsor social service building , 11 th floor , 15 hennessy road , wan chai . </s>
<s> " the results of selection of projects will be available in april next year , </s>
<s> and applicants are advised to take this into account when scheduling their projects for implementation , " said the spokesman . </s>
<s> enquiries about grant application can be made on telephone 2867 2737 or fax 2810 1790 . </s>
