<s> hk donates hk $ 9.75 million to wto trust fund </s>
<s> the hong_kong special administrative region ( hksar ) will donate a sum of us $ 1.25 million ( hk $ 9.75 million ) to the world trade organisation ( wto ) trust fund to extend trade @-@ related technical assistance to less advanced economies . </s>
<s> the announcement was made by the deputy secretary for trade and industry , mr tam wing @-@ pong , when he attended a high @-@ level meeting on least @-@ developed countries held in geneva on october 27 and 28 . </s>
<s> a government spokesman explained : </s>
<s> " the need to assist the least @-@ developed economies to establish themselves as viable trading partners has always been high on the multilateral trade agenda . </s>
<s> " it has been recognised for some time that despite the rapid pace of global trade liberalisation , </s>
<s> not all of the less advanced economies are in a position to enjoy the benefits of the process , while some even face the risks of being marginalised from the world trading system . </s>
<s> " improving the technical skills and the capability of the least @-@ developed economies would enable them to appreciate the merits of a rule @-@ based multilateral trading system and the benefits of free trade , </s>
<s> the high @-@ level meeting is an initiative agreed at the first ministerial conference of the wto held last december in singapore . </s>
<s> at the conference , </s>
<s> ministers adopted a comprehensive and integrated plan of action which aims to improve the overall capacity of the least @-@ developed economies to respond to the opportunities offered by the trading system . </s>
<s> it was agreed that a high @-@ level meeting would be held to foster an integrated approach among various international institutions to assist the least @-@ developed economies in enhancing their trading capability and improving market access opportunities for their products . </s>
<s> the spokesman said : " where market access is concerned , hong_kong has always maintained an open and free market , </s>
<s> with no restrictions on access for goods and services . we apply zero tariffs on all products , including those identified to be of export interest to the least @-@ developed economies . " </s>
<s> " nonetheless , we have been looking into other areas to contribute to the cause , </s>
<s> and our donation is one of such initiatives , " he said . </s>
<s> the hksar 's contribution of us $ 1.25 million ( hk $ 9.75 million ) will be channelled into the wto trust fund for use on trade @-@ related technical assistance activities , </s>
<s> such as workshops and training courses for the least @-@ developed economies . </s>
<s> contributions are voluntary and one @-@ off in nature . </s>
<s> he said : </s>
<s> " as a major trading economy , an active and constructive member of the wto and a beneficiary of international trade liberalisation , we believe that the benefits of globalisation should be shared by economies at various stages of development . </s>
<s> " the high @-@ level meeting is a significant step in this direction . " </s>
<s> the high @-@ level meeting is organised by the wto , and attended by wto members and observers , as well as representatives from least @-@ developed economies , </s>
<s> and international institutions including international monetary fund , international trade centre , united_nations conference on trade and development , united_nations development programme and world bank . </s>
<s> hong_kong hosts the third apec investment symposium </s>
<s> more than 100 senior businessmen and government officials are gathering in hong_kong these two days ( october 28 and 29 ) to attend the third asia @-@ pacific economic co @-@ operation ( apec ) investment symposium . </s>
<s> hong_kong , china is the host of the event which has adopted the theme of " enhancing the environment for investment in apec " . </s>
<s> the two @-@ day symposium is in line with a call made by apec economic leaders in manila last year for apec to intensify its work on investment . </s>
<s> participants discuss ways of improving investment flows in the apec region and focus on the following areas : </s>
<s> * ways of making investment regimes more open and accessible to foreign investors ; </s>
<s> * the impact of regulatory reform in freeing up cross @-@ border investment flows ; </s>
<s> * links between foreign direct investment and technology transfer ; and </s>
<s> * removing obstacles to investment in infrastructure and services . </s>
<s> the 1997 symposium is part of the regular dialogue between investment policy officials and business communities of apec member economies . </s>
<s> the dialogue in the past resulted in proposals for specific action which have been built into the work programme of the investment experts of the apec committee on trade and investment . </s>
<s> the symposium is chaired by mr peter tullock , senior vice president of canadian imperial bank of commerce in hong_kong . </s>
<s> the secretary for trade and industry , miss denise yue , attended and addressed the opening session of the symposium this morning . </s>
<s> new zealand ; papua new guinea ; the republic of the philippines ; singapore ; chinese taipei ; thailand ; and the united_states of america . </s>
<s> fleet managers sought for lpg taxi pilot scheme </s>
<s> the government is to invite experienced taxi operators to act as fleet managers to manage and operate liquefied petroleum gas ( lpg ) taxis during a pilot scheme to be launched next month ( november ) . </s>
<s> the purpose of the pilot scheme is to collect operational data of lpg taxis under local conditions and to demonstrate their suitability for local commercial use . </s>
<s> apart from managing and operating the lpg taxis , the fleet managers will collect and keep the relevant data required and report regularly to a committee . </s>
<s> comprising of representatives of relevant government departments , taxi trade , vehicle suppliers and relevant academics , </s>
<s> the committee will monitor and steer the pilot scheme as well as consider the results and findings . </s>
<s> if the trial is successful , the government will work out a scheme to introduce lpg taxis , the assistant director of environmental protection , </s>
<s> " the experience gained from the trial can also help introduce other lpg vehicles , </s>
<s> " said mr tse . " switching all the diesel taxis to lpg can reduce up to 30 per cent of the respirable suspended particulates emitted from motor vehicles . </s>
<s> " reducing the number of diesel vehicles is essential to solving our serious air pollution caused by diesel vehicle emission . " </s>
<s> he said lpg vehicles were found to be much cleaner than diesel vehicles in terms of air pollution , </s>
<s> and had been in use in many other countries for more than 30 years . </s>
<s> mr tse stressed that lpg vehicles had an impeccable safety record . </s>
<s> " more than four million lpg vehicles are now being used in about 30 countries . among them , </s>
<s> japan and the netherlands have more than 30 years of experience in using lpg vehicles . </s>
<s> " in japan , over 97 per cent of their taxis are running on lpg . neighbouring places such as korea , taiwan and australia are also using lpg vehicles , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> mr tse said an inter @-@ departmental working group set up in september last year to look into the feasibility of introducing gas vehicles had found lpg a practical clean alternative to diesel and equally safe and technically feasible in hong_kong . </s>
<s> the pilot scheme is needed to collect information on costs and maintenance of lpg taxi as well as to gain local operational experience to address the concerns by the traders , </s>
<s> " initially 30 lpg vehicles comprising new and used vehicles will be operated as urban taxis in the same manner as ordinary commercial urban taxis , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> " to ensure that these lpg taxis will be operated in the same mode as normal commercial taxis , we are inviting experienced taxi operators to act as fleet managers for the trial taxis , " he said . </s>
<s> starting from tomorrow ( wednesday ) , taxi operators wishing to manage and operate the trial lpg taxis can obtain the designated application forms at the reception counter of the transport department headquarters , </s>
<s> the completed forms should be returned with required documents to the transport department tender box at the reception centre of 41 st floor , immigration tower at or before noon on november 10 , 1997 </s>
