<s> taxpayers fined for making false statements </s>
<s> an insurance district manager and two couples of property owners were today ( tuesday ) separately prosecuted for tax evasion offences . </s>
<s> the insurance district manager was charged for , without reasonable excuse , making incorrect statements in his profits tax returns or tax returns - individuals , </s>
<s> contrary to section 80 ( 2 ) ( b ) of the inland revenue ordinance while the two couples of property owners were charged for , without reasonable excuse , failing to inform the commissioner of inland revenue in writing of their chargeability to property tax , </s>
<s> contrary to section 80 ( 2 ) ( e ) of the inland revenue ordinance . </s>
<s> the defendants appeared before the magistrate , mr g tallentire , in separate trials in the eastern magistracy today . </s>
<s> in the first case , mr chow kai @-@ leung , sandy , </s>
<s> inland revenue officers carried out an investigation and found that the salaries , commission and allowances payments did not exist . </s>
<s> the false expenses claims for the six years concerned amounted to $ 2,251,304 and the profits tax evaded was $ 337,694 . </s>
<s> the defendant pleaded guilty to all charges and was fined a total of $ 528,500 . </s>
<s> in the second case , mr wai mun @-@ sang and his wife , madam sin lai @-@ yee , kitty , are the joint tenants of a property in king 's road , hong_kong . </s>
<s> the property was let in the years of assessment 1992 / 93 to 1994 / 95 and the value assessable to property tax amounted to $ 1,176,000 . </s>
<s> in the third case , mr chan tsze @-@ wei and his wife , madam lun kit @-@ ying , kitty , are the joint tenants of a property in taikoo shing , hong_kong . </s>
<s> the property was let in the years of assessment 1991 / 92 to 1993 / 94 and the value assessable to property tax amounted to $ 657,011 . </s>
<s> in both the second and third cases , the defendants were chargeable to property tax in respect of their rental income . </s>
<s> they did not inform the commissioner in writing of their chargeability to tax until the inland revenue department issued tax returns to them respectively in the year 1996 . </s>
<s> as a result , tax of $ 141,120 was evaded in the second case whilst tax of $ 78,841 was evaded in the third case . </s>
<s> the first couple pleaded guilty and were fined a total of $ 134,000 . </s>
<s> the defendants in the third case pleaded not guilty and the case was adjourned for hearing on december 30 , 1997 . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the inland revenue department reminded the public that making incorrect statements in the tax returns without reasonable excuse is an offence . </s>
<s> " every person chargeable to tax for any year of assessment must inform the commissioner in writing that he / she is so chargeable not later than four months after the end of the basis period for that year of assessment , </s>
<s> unless he / she has already been required to furnish a tax return . </s>
<s> " a person who , without reasonable excuse , </s>
<s> makes an incorrect return or fails to notify chargeability of chargeable income is liable to a maximum fine of $ 10,000 for each charge , </s>
<s> and a further fine of three times the amount of tax undercharged , " the spokesman said . </s>
