<s> statement by bcsb </s>
<s> following is a statement by the broadcasting , culture and sport bureau today ( friday ) : </s>
<s> " in the past few months , </s>
<s> the work of the obscene articles tribunal ( oat ) has intermittently been the subject of criticism with some directing specifically at its decision and others on the quality of the adjudicators . </s>
<s> to a certain extent , this reflects a lack of understanding on the part of some media on the operation of the oat and on policy considerations behind its establishment . </s>
<s> taking the opportunity of the conclusion of an appeal case by the court of appeal , it is incumbent upon the broadcasting , culture and sport bureau to clarify and explain the objectives and enforcement of the control of obscene and indecent articles ordinance ( coiao ) . </s>
<s> the government supports the decision of the court of appeal that the oat should not be required to set standards or guidelines on obscenity and indecency . </s>
<s> this has all along been the government 's position . </s>
<s> we must appreciate that the determination of whether an article is obscene or indecent , which involves the making of a judgement , is bound to be subjective . </s>
<s> " obscenity " and " indecency " is an abstract and relative concept . </s>
<s> the consideration of what is obscene or indecent is not an exact science . it changes from time to time , </s>
<s> place to place , and culture to culture . </s>
<s> hence , </s>
<s> it is not surprising to find some members of the community disagreeing or even objecting to the rulings of the oat . </s>
<s> what is important is the need for oat rulings to reflect the public standards . under the coiao , </s>
<s> the oat is required to follow the following guidelines in determining whether an article is obscene and indecent , or in classifying an article : </s>
<s> ( 1 ) standards of morality , decency and propriety that are generally accepted by reasonable members of the community ; </s>
<s> ( 2 ) the dominant effect of an article or of matter as a whole ; </s>
<s> ( 3 ) in the case of an article , the persons or class of persons , or age groups of persons , </s>
<s> to or amongst whom the article is , or is intended or is likely to be , published ; </s>
<s> ( 4 ) in the case of matter publicly displayed , the location where the matter is or is to be publicly displayed and the persons or class of persons , or age groups of persons likely to view such matter ; </s>
<s> and ( 5 ) whether the article or matter has an honest purpose or whether its content is merely camouflage designed to render acceptable any part of it . </s>
<s> the oat was established pursuant to the enactment of the coiao in 1987 to replace the then existing system where the determination of whether an article was obscene or indecent was made by a single magistrate . </s>
<s> that system was severely criticised for its lack of representativeness . </s>
<s> after extensive public consultation , the government decided that it is necessary to devise a system which could reflect the views of the community in the process of classification of articles . </s>
<s> the government therefore proposed to set up the oat with community participation by appointing a judicial officer to be the presiding magistrate and two or more members of the public to serve as adjudicators . </s>
<s> the addition of these lay adjudicators is to enable public standards of morality to be reflected in the oat 's decisions . </s>
<s> the adjudicators are required to advise on what they perceive to be the generally accepted standard by reasonable members of the community . as such , it is not necessary and indeed inappropriate to require them to possess certain academic or professional qualifications . </s>
<s> the views provided by the adjudicators are based on their own understanding of the public moral standards , and cannot and should not be regarded as representing the unanimous view of the community . </s>
<s> those who criticised the decisions of the adjudicators have failed to appreciate this crucial point . </s>
<s> in fact , the ordinance only requires the adjudicators to classify a particular article according to their assessment of whether it can be accepted by the community as a whole . </s>
<s> in making the final decision , the presiding magistrate has to consider whether the adjudicators ' perception of the moral standards of the community is reasonable . </s>
<s> in order to enhance the independence and representativeness of the rulings of the oat , the government amended the coiao in 1995 to increase the minimum number of adjudicators from two to four at full hearings conducted to review the interim classification of articles or to reconsider previously classified articles . </s>
<s> in addition , an adjudicator who was involved in the interim classification of an article should not be allowed to sit as a member of the tribunal at the full hearing to consider the same article . </s>
<s> that apart , in order that the tribunal may cover a wider spectrum of the community , </s>
<s> the number of adjudicators has been increased from 80 to 157. the profile of adjudicators in terms of sex , age and occupation has also been carefully designed to closely follow the demographic structure of the population . </s>
<s> these newly @-@ appointed adjudicators are all recruited by the government through open invitation . they have volunteered with a public spirit to serve the community . </s>
<s> the oat handles tens of thousands of cases every year , but decisions which created controversy or were subject to criticisms were few . </s>
<s> this should show that by and large the oat is fulfilling its role . </s>
<s> the set up of an oat is to provide a simple and efficient machinery to deal with offensive articles unacceptable to the community . </s>
<s> the government is committed to striking a right balance between safeguarding freedom of expression and publication on the one hand , and protecting young persons from materials which may harm their physical or mental development and well being on the other . </s>
<s> while maintaining our policy of not compulsorily requiring publishers to submit their publications for classification , </s>
<s> the government must take enforcement measures against articles which offend public morals and are in contravention of the law . </s>
<s> this is also what the community expects of the government . " </s>
<s> eac submits report to ce </s>
<s> the electoral affairs commission ( eac ) today ( friday ) submitted to the chief executive , mr tung chee hwa , a report of its final recommendations on the delineation of geographical constituency boundaries for the legislative council general election in 1998 . </s>
<s> the final recommendations have been drawn up after taking into consideration all views expressed by the public on the eac 's provisional recommendations during a two @-@ week public consultation between october 11 and 24 . </s>
<s> the report contains two volumes . </s>
<s> volume i consists of the report proper which gives a detailed account of the eac 's work in the demarcation exercise and reasons for the decisions it has made , </s>
<s> copies of 104 written representations received by the eac during the consultation period , and the minutes of nine open meetings which the eac held to listen to public views on the provisional recommendations . </s>
<s> volume ii contains a set of maps showing the recommended delineation of constituency boundaries and a general description of the boundaries . </s>
<s> eac 's report submitted to ce </s>
<s> the electoral affairs commission ( eac ) has today ( friday ) submitted to the chief executive , mr tung chee hwa , its report which contains recommendations on the demarcation of geographical constituency boundaries for the 1998 legislative council election . </s>
<s> " the administration will study the eac 's recommendations carefully and seek the decision of the chief executive in council as soon as possible . </s>
<s> " the decision of the chief executive in council will be gazetted in the form of an order , which will be tabled in the provisional legislative council . </s>
<s> elector registration regulation gazetted </s>
<s> the electoral affairs commission ( registration of electors ) ( geographical constituencies ) ( legislative council ) regulation sets out the procedure for the preparation of a provisional and a final register of electors of geographical constituencies stipulated under the legislative council ordinance . </s>
<s> the provisional register is required to be published not later than february 15 of each year , and the final register not later than march 15 in 1998 and march 31 in each year subsequent to 1998 . </s>
<s> highlighting the main features of the regulation at a press conference today , the chairman of the electoral affairs commission , </s>
<s> the honourable mr justice woo , said the electoral registration officer ( ero ) was required to inform the person concerned by registered post if his decision might entail negative consequences to that person . </s>
<s> " this applies to cases when the ero determines that the person is not eligible to be registered ; </s>
<s> makes an inquiry from that person who may be deregistered if he does not respond ; or decides not to alter an entry in the register as requested by that person . </s>
<s> " this is to ensure that notifications of such decisions can reach the person concerned , " mr justice woo said . </s>
<s> to ensure the registration system works and to guard against misuses of the information obtained by the ero for non @-@ election purposes , the regulations makes it an offence if any person : </s>
<s> * makes a false statement in relation to voter registration ; </s>
<s> * conspires with , incites , compels , induces , coerces , intimidates or persuades another person to make such a false statement ; </s>
<s> * obtains information from a register and uses it or imparts it to another person for a purpose other than a purpose related to an election . </s>
<s> the penalties for the first two offences include disqualification from being registered as an elector and voting at an election , and also being nominated as a candidate . </s>
<s> the last offence includes a penalty to disqualify candidature . </s>
<s> the regulation will be tabled at the provisional legislative council for negative vetting on next wednesday ( november 5 ) and will come into effect on the same day . </s>
<s> mr justice woo said this is to enable elector registration to start immediately on the same day so that eligible persons may have more time to register . </s>
<s> he said that the registration period will last until january 16 , 1998 and urged the public to register as electors and vote in next year 's legislative council general election . </s>
<s> according to the basic law , all permanent residents of the hong_kong special administrative region have the right to vote and the right to stand for election . </s>
<s> all permanent residents who have reached the age of 18 and ordinarily reside in hong_kong are eligible to be registered as electors . </s>
<s> " hence , </s>
<s> those who wish to be an elector but have not yet obtained a permanent identity ( id ) card should apply to the immigration department for the id card now as it normally takes six weeks to process such applications , </s>
<s> " mr justice woo said . </s>
<s> members of the public who wish to seek further information on the permanent resident status and the right of abode may contact the immigration department on 2824 4055 . </s>
<s> for enquiries on elector registration , please call the registration and electoral office on 2891 1001 . </s>
