<s> government committed to reducing landslip danger </s>
<s> the government is committed to further reducing landslip dangers in hong_kong , </s>
<s> having upgraded hundreds of major fill slopes and cut slopes under the landslip preventive measures ( lpm ) programme in the past 20 years . </s>
<s> a new 10 @-@ year lpm programme is being planned to deal with another batch of sub @-@ standard man @-@ made slopes in the new slope catalogue under preparation by the geotechnical engineering office ( geo ) . </s>
<s> this was disclosed by the secretary for works , mr kwong hon @-@ sang today ( friday ) when he was speaking at the opening ceremony of the geo 's 20 th anniversary special exhibition . </s>
<s> the geo together with the transport and highways departments , is devising plans to accommodate the necessary improvement works for roadside slopes with a history of landslips as part of the road improvement projects , </s>
<s> " mr kwong said . </s>
<s> he also pointed out that government maintenance departments were now committed to enhancing their slope maintenance standard and that resources had been allocated to them to carry out the necessary works . </s>
<s> " apart from undertaking regular routine maintenance to prevent government slopes from deteriorating to an unsafe state , </s>
<s> preventive maintenance will be carried out to improve the slopes using prescriptive measures , " mr kwong said . </s>
<s> on natural hillsides , which cover 60 per cent of hong_kong 's total area , </s>
<s> mr kwong said the government had begun a preliminary assessment of landslide hazards associated with them in order to ensure the safe development of land . </s>
<s> " detailed risk assessments will be conducted to develop appropriate measures to mitigate the risk in these areas , </s>
<s> " he added . </s>
<s> but mr kwong said government actions alone could not resolve the slope safety problem . </s>
<s> " we will continue to stress the importance of maintenance of private slopes , </s>
<s> " he said , adding that the feasibility of a mandatory slope maintenance scheme was being examined . </s>
<s> the geo 20 th anniversary special exhibition , which introduces the wide range of geotechnical engineering work carried out by the government , is one of the major events to mark the office 's 20 years of service . </s>
<s> the two @-@ day exhibition features a number of exhibits and game stalls to promote the slope safety message . </s>
<s> panels covering topics such as hydraulic fill , safe handling of explosive and natural terrain landslide study are on display . </s>
<s> other attractive items and game stalls include quarry models and slope safety jigsaw puzzles . </s>
<s> the exhibition , is held at the ground floor podium of the civil engineering building , 101 princess margaret road , </s>
<s> ho man tin and is open to public until 5 pm tomorrow ( saturday ) . admission is free . </s>
<s> amendments to the trade unions ordinance </s>
<s> amendments to the trade unions ordinance under the employment and labour relations ( miscellaneous amendments ) ordinance 1997 , </s>
<s> which was passed by the provisional legislative council on october 29 , was gazetted today ( friday ) with immediate effect . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the labour department said the amendments gave effect to the results of a comprehensive review of the entire trade unions ordinance conducted by the labour department , </s>
<s> including the provisions of the trade unions ( amendment ) ( no. 2 ) ordinance 1997 , and were aimed at ensuring the healthy development of trade unions in hong_kong . </s>
<s> the amendments include : </s>
<s> trade union to be a member of a related organisation in foreign countries without the need for prior approval from the government . </s>
<s> elaborating on the new provisions regarding affiliations with organisations in foreign countries , the spokesman said , " local trade unions will be allowed to become a member of related organisations ( i.e. organisations of workers , </s>
<s> employers and relevant professional organisations ) in foreign countries without the need for prior approval from the government . </s>
<s> " instead they will only be required to seek approval of the majority of the voting members present at a general meeting by secret ballot before proceeding to become a member of the organisation and to notify the registrar of the trade unions of the labour department within one month after becoming a member of such organisation . </s>
<s> " however , </s>
<s> the previous requirement to seek the chief executive 's approval for affiliation with overseas organisations other than those of workers , </s>
<s> employers and relevant professional organisations is restored . " </s>
<s> enquiries about the amendments can be made to the registry of trade unions of the labour department at 2852 3501 or 2852 3459 . </s>
<s> $ 162.7 million approved for new technical curriculum </s>
<s> the finance committee today ( friday ) approved non @-@ recurrent funds totalling $ 162.7 million for implementing a new technical curriculum in prevocational and secondary technical schools in september 2000 . </s>
<s> an education department spokesman said the recommendation for a new technical curriculum came from a working group to review prevocational and secondary technical education . in march 1997 , </s>
<s> the working group suggested revamping and enriching the existing technical curriculum by putting more emphasis on business and technological subjects as well as languages to meet the changing needs of society . </s>
<s> the recommendations received wide support from the community . </s>
<s> the spokesman noted that the recommended new technical curriculum aims at equipping students with fundamental and transferable skills to enable them to adapt to a changing work environment and to proceed to higher studies in business and technological fields if they wish . </s>
<s> it involves wider application of modern technology in teaching and learning so that students could acquire an understanding and appreciation of the technological trend . </s>
<s> the new and updated business and technological subjects include , at junior secondary level , </s>
<s> the three subjects of fundamentals ( business fundamentals , design fundamentals and technology fundamentals ) which equip students with basic and transferable skills , concepts and knowledge . </s>
<s> also included are design and technology ( alternative syllabus ) and eight application subjects such as fashion design , graphical communication , automobile technology and retail merchandising . </s>
<s> each application will encompass application of the integrated elements , where appropriate , of the three fundamentals in a particular situation , </s>
<s> but not on job @-@ specific training . </s>
<s> at senior secondary level , </s>
<s> the new subjects introduced are graphical communication , technological studies , information technology and design & technology ( alternative syllabus ) . </s>
<s> " in this connection , some of the special rooms / workshops in prevocational and secondary technical schools will need to be converted , </s>
<s> the facilities upgraded and teaching materials made available to ensure proper teaching and learning of the new and updated business and technological subjects , " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> to support the implementation of the new technical curriculum in these schools , </s>
<s> the expenditure of the approved commitment of $ 162.7 million spanning three years from 1998 @-@ 99 to 2000 @-@ 01 will be used for conversion and upgrading of 233 special rooms / workshops ( $ 57 million ) , </s>
<s> upgrading of furniture and equipment in 273 special rooms / workshops ( $ 84.3 million ) and producing 100 sets of teaching and learning materials ( $ 21.4 million ) for each of the new business and technological subjects . </s>
<s> an ad hoc committee on the development of the new technical curriculum was formed in september 1997 , </s>
<s> comprising experts from the tertiary institutions , hong_kong examinations authority , vocational training council , hong_kong productivity council , </s>
<s> schools concerned and the education department . </s>
<s> the committee is responsible for developing the new business and technological subjects , overseeing the production of the relevant teaching and learning materials and mapping out strategies of teacher training and retraining . </s>
<s> to ensure effective implementation of the new technical curriculum in prevocational and secondary technical schools , the committee will keep the schools informed about the progress of development of the new business and technological subjects on a regular basis . </s>
<s> owners can benefit from improved building management </s>
