<s> gambling licence fees to be revised in december </s>
<s> licence fees covering lotteries , tombolas , </s>
<s> games of amusement with prizes , trade promotion competitions and games in which mahjong or tin kau tiles are used , are proposed to be revised from december 13 , 1997 . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the home affairs bureau said details of the increases were set out in the gambling ( amendment ) regulation 1997 gazetted today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> he said it was government policy that fees should in general be set at levels sufficient to recover the full cost of providing the services . </s>
<s> the last costing review for the issue of mahjong / tin kau licence was conducted in 1994 @-@ 95 and those for other licences in 1995 / 96 . </s>
<s> all licence fees were last revised in december 1996 based on the full cost at 1996 / 97 prices . </s>
<s> " to reflect the cost of the services at 1997 @-@ 98 prices , </s>
<s> the government proposes to increase the fees by about seven per cent , in accordance with the movement of the government consumption expenditure deflator from 1996 / 97 to 1997 / 98 , " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> the proposed new licence fees are as follows : </s>
<s> lottery $ 3,135 </s>
<s> amusements with prizes $ 3,040 </s>
<s> mahjong / tin kau $ 1,145 per table </s>
<s> the spokesman believed that the revised fees would not substantially increase the operating costs of the licensees , </s>
<s> adding that charitable organisations would continue to be qualified for a waiver or reduction of fees under section 6 of the gambling regulations . </s>
<s> licence fees for hotels and guesthouses to be revised </s>
<s> the fees for the issuing and renewal of licences for hotels and guesthouses are proposed to be increased by seven per cent from december 12 to help recover the cost of administering the hotel and guesthouse licensing scheme . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the home affairs bureau today ( friday ) said the fee revision proposed was in line with the government policy that fees should in general be set at levels to recover the full cost of providing the services . </s>
<s> he said the existing fees were last revised in august 1996 , noting that they were able to recover only about 24 per cent of the full cost of the licensing system . </s>
<s> the new fees for the issue and renewal of licences will range from $ 3,000 to $ 31,460 , depending on the number of rooms of the licensee . </s>
<s> " the proposed fee increase will have an insignificant impact on the operating costs of the trade and no impact on the consumer price index , " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> details of the new fees are set out in the hotel and guesthouse accommodation ( fees ) ( amendment ) regulation 1997 which was gazetted today . </s>
<s> hotel and guesthouse licence holders , operators and new applicants will be notified of the new fees when they submit their licence applications or apply for renewal of licences , the spokesman added . </s>
<s> the hotel and guesthouse accommodation ordinance , enacted in may 1991 and came into operation in june 1991 , </s>
<s> provides for a licensing scheme to regulate the building safety and fire safety of hotels and guesthouses . </s>
<s> under the ordinance , a person operating a hotel or guesthouse is required to obtain a licence or a certificate of exemption from the office of the licensing authority of the home affairs department . </s>
