<s> gross domestic product ( gdp ) grew by 6.4 % in real terms in the second quarter of 1997 over a year earlier , further up from the 6.1 % increase in the first quarter . </s>
<s> these are shown in the preliminary estimates of the expenditure @-@ based gdp for the second quarter of 1997 and revised estimates for earlier periods released today ( monday ) by the census and statistics department . </s>
<s> amongst the major gdp components , private consumption expenditure rose strongly by 8.7 % in real terms in the second quarter of 1997 over a year earlier . this was the fastest growth rate recorded since the first quarter of 1994 . </s>
<s> government consumption expenditure had a 5.8 % increase in real terms . </s>
<s> on investment spending , gross domestic fixed capital formation recorded a large year @-@ on @-@ year increase of 16.2 % in real terms in the second quarter of 1997. within this total , </s>
<s> expenditure on machinery and equipment increased significantly by 15.4 % in real terms . </s>
<s> construction output in the private sector also registered a robust growth , by 17.8 % in real terms , mainly due to intensive work on private housing projects . </s>
<s> on the other hand , construction output in the public sector fell by 10.8 % in real terms , as more projects under the airport core programme approached completion . </s>
<s> taken together , overall expenditure on construction rose by 6.0 % in real terms . as to external trade in goods , </s>
<s> re @-@ exports registered a year @-@ on @-@ year growth rate of 7.3 % in real terms in the second quarter of 1997 , </s>
<s> while domestic exports decreased marginally by 0.1 % in real terms . taken together , total exports of goods increased by 6.2 % in real terms . </s>
<s> imports of goods recorded a 6.9 % growth in real terms . exports of services increased only modestly by 2.0 % in real terms in the second quarter of 1997 over a year earlier , amidst a decline in tourist receipts over the same period . </s>
<s> concurrently , imports of services declined by 1.2 % in real terms , partly due to a slower growth in spending on overseas trips by hong_kong residents . </s>
<s> the implicit price deflator of the gdp , as a broad measure of overall inflation in the economy , </s>
<s> rose by 7.0 % in the second quarter of 1997 over a year earlier . this was broadly similar to the 6.8 % increase in the first quarter . </s>
<s> along with release of the preliminary gdp estimates for the second quarter of 1997 , the gdp estimates for the earlier periods have also been revised . </s>
<s> taking into account information newly available , the gdp growth rate for 1995 is revised downwards from 4.5 % to 3.9 % . </s>
<s> this was mainly due to adjustment to the estimates for trade in services , </s>
<s> which grew less rapidly amidst the economic down @-@ cycle in 1995 than was reckoned earlier , </s>
<s> as indicated by finalised figures which could only be available after a considerable time lag . </s>
<s> the revisions to the estimates for 1996 and the first quarter of 1997 are nevertheless marginal , with the respective overall gdp growth rates of 4.9 % and 6.1 % remaining unchanged . </s>
<s> commenting on the latest quarterly gdp figures , a government secretariat spokesman noted that the growth momentum in the economy continued to be strong , with the gdp growth rate for the second quarter of 1997 representing a further rise from the continuously accelerating trend since the beginning of last year . </s>
<s> domestic demand was robust , reflecting a very positive sentiment , </s>
<s> and this bolstered overall growth even when the performance on the external sector front was relatively moderate . </s>
<s> the intensity of real investment was particularly noteworthy . </s>
<s> the spokesman also observed that overall inflation in the economy remained stable , even as economic activity intensified further . </s>
<s> the recent trend in the consumer price index also showed that inflationary pressures were moderate . </s>
<s> productivity improvement was amongst the factors that helped to keep costs in check . </s>
<s> the update will take into account the likely effect of the recent turmoil in the financial markets on economic performance for the rest of the year . </s>
<s> more details on the annual and quarterly estimates of gdp are published in a report entitled " quarterly report of gross domestic product estimates second quarter 1997 " . </s>
<s> the report is now on sale at $ 13.0 per copy at the government publications centre , </s>
<s> ground floor , low block , queensway government offices , 66 queensway , hong_kong . </s>
<s> it may also be purchased at the publications unit of the census and statistics department , 19 th floor , wanchai tower , 12 harbour road , </s>
<s> wan chai , hong_kong . </s>
<s> enquiries about this publication may be directed to the national income branch ( 1 ) of the census and statistics department ( tel no : </s>
<s> 2582 5077 ) . </s>
