<s> had devotes great effort to improve building management </s>
<s> the home affairs department ( had ) attaches great importance to effective building management and will launch a package of measures to improve the services to owners of buildings , </s>
<s> the director of home affairs , mrs shelley lau , said today ( monday ) . </s>
<s> responding to recent press reports on had 's work concerning the promotion of effective building management , </s>
<s> mrs lau said had has been recruiting more staff as well as introducing new ways in the coming few months to assist owners to better manage their buildings . </s>
<s> " one of the measures is the setting up of a building management resource centre ( bmrc ) to provide information , services and professional advice to building owners , </s>
<s> residents and management bodies to help them improve the standards of management and safety and the maintenance of their buildings , " mrs lau said . </s>
<s> we are pleased that they welcome this project and have promised to give their support as much as possible . </s>
<s> " the first bmrc is expected to come into operation in kowloon next year . more centres will be planned on a territory wide basis , </s>
<s> " she added . </s>
<s> to tie in with the bmrc , </s>
<s> mrs lau said that had is working on the production of a tv series to drive home to the public the need and importance of proper building management . </s>
<s> " we are now working closely with the radio television hong_kong and many experts on the tv series which will be produced in a docu @-@ drama form . it will highlight the various aspects of effective building management and the bmrc . </s>
<s> " representatives of the professional bodies in the bmrc will also be invited to share respective areas of expertise in the tv programme , " mrs lau said . </s>
<s> meanwhile , </s>
<s> had is holding a series of receptions and workshops in october and november for members of owners ' corporations ( ocs ) and mutual aid committees ( macs ) in the 18 districts to provide them with an opportunity for experience sharing in building management and for had to listen to their views at the same time . </s>
<s> " such receptions have already been held in yuen long , sham shui po and wan chai last week , </s>
<s> and the next one will be held at the tuen mun town centre community hall , trend plaza , tuen shun street , tuen mun at 8.30 pm tomorrow ( tuesday ) , </s>
<s> " mrs lau said . </s>
<s> she and her deputy directors will be attending the receptions separately to listen to owners ' views and suggestions . </s>
<s> had and its district offices regularly organise building management seminars to promote effective building management among owners , ocs and macs . </s>
<s> over the past 10 months , the district offices have organised more than 20 seminars and training courses for local residents . </s>
<s> " every year , </s>
<s> the had headquarters organises a large @-@ scale territory @-@ wide building management seminar to provide a forum for owners from various districts to exchange their views . the building management seminar '98 is scheduled to be held in june next year . " </s>
<s> as to buildings already beset with management problems , </s>
<s> mrs lau said they should seek the assistance of the building management co @-@ ordination teams ( bmcts ) which had has set up in nine districts since 1985 . </s>
<s> " the teams give owners practical advice on the improvement of building management and act as a co @-@ ordinator with various government departments in rendering assistance to ocs , </s>
<s> " she said . </s>
<s> about 1,000 buildings have been selected by bmcts for inclusion in its target improvement programme . more than 400 of them have seen significant improvements and the department will continue to work on the remaining buildings on the action list . </s>
<s> " to meet the increasing demands for such assistance , we are planning to set up bmcts in other districts . " </s>
<s> the had has been allocating considerable resources and manpower in carrying out the building management work to encourage more active participation of property owners in managing their own buildings , mrs lau stressed . </s>
