<s> at the meeting held this afternoon ( tuesday ) , the transport advisory committee ( tac ) examined the fare increase applications from kowloon motor bus company ( 1933 ) limited ( kmb ) , china motor bus company limited ( cmb ) and citybus limited ( citybus ) . </s>
<s> after deliberations , members endorsed the administration 's recommendations of a 7 % fare increase for kmb 's routes ( a reduction of 2.5 % on the 9.5 % increase sought by kmb ) , </s>
<s> an 8 % fare increase for cmb 's routes ( a reduction of 3 % on the 11 % increase sought by cmb ) , </s>
<s> and a 6 % fare increase for citybus 's routes ( a reduction of 2.7 % on the 8.7 % increase sought by citybus ) . </s>
<s> the above recommendations will be submitted to the executive council for consideration . if approved , the new fares will take effect in december 1997 . </s>
<s> members noted that kmb last increased the fares on its cross @-@ harbour routes in march 1996 and its kowloon and new territories routes in april 1996 . </s>
<s> cmb and citybus last increased their fares in march 1996 . </s>
<s> by december 1997 , the bus companies would have gone without any fare adjustments for over 20 months . </s>
<s> the forecast inflation between the last increase and the proposed date of fare increase in december 1997 is 9.5 % in the case of kmb , and 10 % in the case of cmb and citybus . </s>
<s> in their deliberations , members considered carefully the need to pitch bus fares at a level acceptable to the public , and the need to provide bus companies with a reasonable rate of return as an incentive for further service improvements . </s>
<s> other factors such as increases in operating costs , service development plans , cost economy measures and public acceptability were also taken into consideration . </s>
<s> in putting these recommendations to the executive council , members were mindful of the impact of the increase on inflation and public acceptability . </s>
<s> the recommended fare increase rates for kmb , </s>
<s> cmb and citybus are 2.5 % , 2 % and 4 % below the forecast accumulated inflation respectively since the last fare rises . </s>
<s> the recommended fare rises together would only increase the consumer price index ( a ) by 0.14 % . </s>
<s> with the recommended overall weighted average fare increase of 7 % , kmb 's forecast profit in 1998 will be similar to its 1996 level . </s>
<s> tac believed that a 7 % fare increase would give the company a sufficient incentive to improve its operating efficiency , so as to achieve profit growth . </s>
<s> as for cmb , members noted that cmb had suffered from a continuous decline in patronage in recent years with a corresponding drop in its profitability . </s>
<s> improvements to its staff retirement scheme since january 1997 had pushed up cmb 's operating costs by $ 40 million for 1996 / 97 . </s>
<s> as a result , cmb was hardly able to break even in 1996 / 97 . </s>
<s> members also noted that without a fare increase , cmb would suffer a sizeable loss in 1997 / 98 . </s>
<s> the recommended overall weighted average fare increase of 8 % would enable cmb to recover the operating costs and to improve its services . </s>
<s> in addition , members noted that cmb had a low fare base . </s>
<s> even with a higher fare increase rate , its fares were still among the lowest of the three franchisees , and so were its profit levels . </s>
<s> tac noted that without a fare increase , citybus 's forecast profit in 1998 would be much lower than those in 1996 and 1997 . </s>
<s> the recommended overall weighted average fare increase of 6 % would give citybus an incentive for further investment to improve its services . </s>
<s> tac believed the recommended fare increase rate would provide enough incentive for the rapidly expanding company to improve its operating efficiency in order to achieve profit growth , and should be acceptable to the public . </s>
<s> additional fare for taxi passengers using harbour crossings </s>
<s> 1998 . </s>
<s> " on january 1 , 1998 , </s>
<s> the ehc will increase its tolls for private cars and taxis from $ 10 to $ 15 , " an sar government spokesman today ( tuesday ) explained . </s>
<s> " it is therefore necessary to revise the return toll for cross @-@ harbour taxi passengers to ensure that the taxi driver does not have to pay out of pocket , </s>
<s> even if he cannot obtain a hire on his return journey . " </s>
<s> cross @-@ harbour taxi passengers are required to pay an additional fare which comprises two parts : the tunnel toll already paid by taxi drivers during the hiring and the return toll . </s>
<s> those who hire a taxi at cross @-@ harbour taxi stands will only be required to pay the tunnel toll in addition to the normal taxi fare . </s>
<s> at present , the return toll is set at $ 10 to provide taxi drivers who fail to obtain a hire on the return journey with two cross @-@ harbour routes , </s>
<s> i.e. the cross @-@ harbour tunnel ( cht ) or the ehc , without having to pay out of pocket . </s>
<s> in line with this policy , </s>
<s> the return toll for passengers using the whc will also be revised from $ 10 to $ 15 from january 1 , 1998 , so that a taxi driver who cannot obtain a hire on the return journey may use either the cht or eht without having to pay out of pocket . </s>
<s> the return tolls for taxi passengers using cht will remain at $ 10. </s>
<s> the revised return tolls for cross @-@ harbour taxi passengers will be as follows : </s>
<s> harbour cross existing starting from january 1 , 1998 </s>
<s> ehc $ 10 $ 15 </s>
<s> whc $ 10 $ 15 </s>
<s> passengers who hire a taxi at cross @-@ harbour taxi stands will not be required to pay a return toll as at present . </s>
