<s> land registry statistics for october released </s>
<s> a total of 14,967 sale and purchase agreements for building units , including residential and non @-@ residential properties , were lodged with the land registry last month ( october ) . </s>
<s> the figure represented an increase of 6.3 per cent from the previous month and an increase of 7.8 per cent over october last year . </s>
<s> the total consideration of these agreements was $ 60.8 billion , </s>
<s> up 2.8 per cent and 25.8 per cent respectively when compared with the amounts in september 1997 and october last year . </s>
<s> the figures were contained in the monthly statistics released today ( tuesday ) by the land registry on deeds relating to property transactions received for registration in the urban and new territories land registries in october 1997 . </s>
<s> relevant statistics for september 1997 and october 1996 were provided for comparison . </s>
<s> figures on sale and purchase agreements received for the past 12 months and the year @-@ on - year rate of change were also released . </s>
<s> these statistics generally relate to land transactions executed up to four weeks prior to their submission for registration as there is usually a time lag between the execution of deeds and their lodgement for registration . </s>
<s> operator of unlicensed guesthouse fined </s>
<s> a guesthouse operator was fined $ 20,000 in fanling magistracy today ( tuesday ) after pleading guilty to running a guesthouse in yuen long without a licence . </s>
<s> the court heard that officers of the home affairs department 's office of the licensing authority ( ola ) inspected a premises at 75 castle peak road , yuen long , on april 30 and found it being operated as a guesthouse without a licence . </s>
<s> a letter was sent in may to warn the operator that a licence had to be obtained before operating the guesthouse ; otherwise , the operator would be prosecuted . </s>
<s> ola officers inspected the guesthouse again on june 5 and found that it was still in operation . </s>
<s> its operator was later charged under section 5 of the hotel and guesthouse accommodation ordinance . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the department said illegal guesthouses would not be tolerated and enforcement action would continue to be taken to eliminate such premises . </s>
<s> he said efforts would be stepped up to ensure all guesthouses met the required building and fire safety standards and were properly licensed . </s>
<s> he also appealed to the public to help in the effort to crack down on unlicensed guesthouses by reporting them to the ola on 2881 7034 . </s>
