<s> safe use of hoists on construction sites urged </s>
<s> building contractors must comply strictly with the safety requirements relating to the construction , maintenance and safe operation of hoists on construction sites . </s>
<s> acting chief factory inspector ( operations ) of the labour department , </s>
<s> mr wong ching @-@ kwok , today ( thursday ) warned contractors that it was their duty to ensure that the hoists used on construction sites were of good mechanical construction and properly maintained . </s>
<s> " the hoistway of the hoist must be protected by substantial enclosure and the enclosure must be , where access to and egress from the hoist is required , </s>
<s> fitted with secure gates , " mr wong added . </s>
<s> he pointed out that proper maintenance of the mechanical parts of the hoists could help prevent the occurrence of accidents . </s>
<s> " contractors must ensure that the hoists are not used unless they have been tested and examined by competent personnel and are certified in safe working order , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> under the construction sites ( safety ) regulations , contractors who fail to observe the regulations pertaining to safe operation of hoists on construction sites are liable to a fine of $ 200,000 . </s>
<s> workers who fail to use the safety equipment so provided are liable to a fine of $ 10,000 . </s>
<s> mr wong said that occupational safety officers of the department are taking vigorous enforcement action against the persons who fail to comply with the law . </s>
<s> tang chung ling ancestral hall in fanling , one of the largest ancestral halls in hong_kong , </s>
<s> will be declared a historical building under the antiquities and monuments ordinance in the gazette tomorrow ( friday ) . </s>
<s> reputed to have been built in 1525 , tang chung ling ancestral hall is the first deemed building formally declared a historical building . situated to the north @-@ west at the foot of lung shan , </s>
<s> fanling , tang chung ling ancestral hall overlooks the 11 old villages of the tang clan in lung yeuk tau and has been serving the clansmen for about 470 years . </s>
<s> tang chung ling ancestral hall was reputed to have been built in honour of the founding ancestor , tang chung ling ( 1302 @-@ 1387 ) , and has since then been the main ancestral hall of the lung yeuk tau lineage . </s>
<s> the tangs in lung yeuk tau have much stronger claims to royal descent than their fellow clansmen elsewhere in hong_kong . </s>
<s> according to their genealogical records , the princess of the southern song ( 1127 @-@ 1279 ) was married to an ancestor of the lineage . </s>
<s> the soul tablets of the royal couple are still being worshipped at the ancestral hall . </s>
<s> the last major renovation was probably completed in 1921 as both the fascia board at the main entrance and the board with the three characters " shui wen tong " at the central hall bear the same year . </s>
<s> this magnificent ancestral hall is a three @-@ hall building with two spacious internal courtyards . an annex attached to its right is the kitchen . </s>
<s> the whole building is exquisitely decorated with fine wood carvings , polychrome plaster mouldings and murals of auspicious chinese motifs , fully reflecting the superb craftsmanship of the olden days . </s>
<s> motifs adopting plants , clouds , natural and mythical animals , chinese legends and literature are elaborately depicted on the altars , </s>
<s> brackets , beams , eaves and wall friezes . </s>
<s> the boat @-@ shaped roof ridge decorated with shiwan ceramic fishes and lions is another attractive feature . </s>
<s> with the consent and support of the tong management , tang chung ling ancestral hall was deemed a monument on october 18 , 1990 . </s>
<s> a major restoration was carried out in 1991 with a generous donation from the hong_kong jockey club . </s>
<s> which was completed in mid 1992 , was under the supervision of the antiquities group of the architectural services department and the antiquities and monuments office of the broadcasting , culture and sport bureau . </s>
<s> the ancestral hall remains in use in the traditional manner , as a place of worship of ancestors , </s>
<s> holding of festival celebrations , ceremonies and meetings of indigenous villagers of the tang clan . </s>
<s> revised prohibition for tung chung road </s>
<s> the transport department will put on trial a further relaxation of the prohibition on tung chung road early next month ( december ) . </s>
<s> the trial scheme was endorsed by members of the islands provisional district board and local representatives in a working group meeting today ( thursday ) . </s>
<s> speaking on the trial scheme , a spokesman for the department said : " the existing 7 am - 9 pm prohibited zone on tung chung road between shek mun kap road and south lantau road will be shortened to 7 am - 7 pm daily every mondays to fridays , </s>
<s> during the specified periods , </s>
<s> all motor vehicles , except franchised buses , lantau taxis , emergency vehicles and those with valid permits , </s>
<s> will be banned from entering tung chung road prohibited zone . </s>
<s> " however , </s>
<s> the existing 24 @-@ hour prohibition on saturdays , sundays and public holidays will be further reviewed , taking into account recommendations of the working group and related enforcement problems . " besides , </s>
<s> to enhance safety after the relaxation of the restriction , </s>
<s> heavy goods vehicles will be banned from using the road from 7 pm to 9 pm daily , " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> the prohibition hours on mondays to fridays ( except public holidays ) was relaxed to 7 am - 9 pm on a trial basis from july 28 . </s>
<s> since then , members of the islands provisional district board and various residents associations have requested for further relaxation of the restriction . </s>
<s> commenting on reasons for the new arrangement , the spokesman said : </s>
<s> " the department has sped up the reviews on the traffic situation on tung chung road to address the concerns of the localities . </s>
<s> " a recent survey shows that traffic volume on tung chung road in the late evenings is below its designed capacity and there is room for short @-@ term relaxation . </s>
<s> " having re @-@ assessed the traffic condition , taking into consideration public opinions , </s>
<s> the department has decided to put on trial this modified traffic control scheme . </s>
<s> the traffic situation will be closely monitored and the prohibition will be reinstated to 7 am - 9 pm if the traffic flow in both directions reaches 100 vehicles per hour , or when serious congestion or an increase in the number of incidents is observed on tung chung road . " </s>
<s> traffic pattern will be different as tung chung new town begins to incorporate more entertainment facilities and upon the commissioning of the new airport in chek lap kok . </s>
<s> " a review of the new scheme will then be conducted to tie in with the anticipated changes in the traffic conditions , </s>
<s> " the spokesman added . </s>
<s> the trial is also made possible with the completion of a number of minor road improvement works , </s>
<s> which are in progress , to enhance safety and traffic flow of tung chung road . </s>
<s> this includes extension of existing laybys and provision of additional ones , widening of bends and sightline improvements . </s>
<s> after the completion of the improvement work early next month , the trial scheme will begin to take effect . </s>
<s> " the department is also pursuing an additional lane on tung chung road near pak kung au and the catchwater in the vicinity of cheung sha . the works are expected to commence in late 1998 for completion in 1999 , </s>
<s> " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> " in the longer term , </s>
<s> the transport and highways departments are studying the feasibility of constructing a new road between mui wo and tai ho wan linking south and north lantau . </s>
<s> " the study will be completed in february 1998 . </s>
<s> " both departments will also examine the feasibility of a new road link between sham wat and tung chung . the study is expected to start next year for completion in eight months , </s>
<s> " the spokesman added . </s>
<s> vehicles must apply for a tung chung road prohibited zone permit ( pzp ) before they are allowed to enter the restricted part of tung chung road . </s>
<s> there are three categories of persons in need of pzp , </s>
<s> namely , existing permit holders , commercial undertakings with business and operation needs and residents of south lantau and tung chung road . </s>
<s> at present , there are about 260 pzps issued to these people , including a total of 150 new pzps issued after the opening of the lantau link . </s>
<s> the spokesman reminded the public that vehicles with closed road permit ( crp ) and pzp for access to the urban areas will required to pay full vehicle licence fee as they can drive on all public roads in the territory . </s>
<s> however , those permit holders who only use tung chung road to travel between tung chung and south lantau are required to pay the lower licence fee specified for vehicles operated on just the lantau island . </s>
<s> all roads on lantau island including the whole of tung chung road are closed roads , </s>
<s> except those in tung chung new town and the new airport and private roads in the discovery bay . </s>
<s> vehicles without valid closed road permits are not allowed to travel on lantau island closed roads . </s>
<s> awards for excellent industrial performance </s>
<s> the 1997 hong_kong awards for industry were presented by the chief executive , mr tung chee hwa , this ( friday ) evening to seven companies in recognition of their excellence in industrial performance . </s>
<s> this year 's winners are : techtronic industries co. ltd for the consumer product design category ; </s>
<s> po yuen ( to 's ) machine factory ltd for the machinery & equipment design category ; sylva industries ltd for the productivity category ; philips hong_kong ltd for the quality category ; mobil oil hong_kong ltd for the environmental performance category ; vtech holdings ltd for the export marketing category ; </s>
<s> the last category - technological achievement - is introduced as from 1997 to underscore the importance of technological development and application of new technologies in hong_kong 's manufacturing sector and recognise achievements of local companies in high technology sectors . </s>
<s> the winners are entitled to display the official logo of the awards scheme on the company letterheads , </s>
<s> envelopes , complimentary slips , press advertising and other promotional materials for a period of three years . </s>
<s> they also receive a trophy , an individually @-@ crafted sculpture , as a memento of their achievement . </s>
<s> introduced in 1989 , the award scheme is held annually to commend distinguished companies which have achieved excellence in different aspects of industrial performance . </s>
<s> competitions in the seven award categories are each organised by a different organisation . </s>
<s> the federation of hong_kong industries is responsible for the consumer product design category ; the chinese manufacturers ' association of hong_kong for the machinery and equipment design category ; the hong_kong productivity council for the productivity category ; the industry department for the quality category ; the private sector committee on the environment for the environmental performance category ; </s>
<s> apart from the hong_kong awards for industry , which are presented to the most outstanding entry in each category , each of the seven organisations also gives out a number of awards and certificates of merit in its own name to deserving entries in the category for which it is responsible . </s>
<s> chief executive views welfare services delivery </s>
<s> the chief executive , mr tung chee hwa , was thoroughly briefed on the development of social welfare during his visit to social welfare department offices this ( friday ) afternoon . </s>
<s> mr tung called on the department 's eastern and wan chai district office in north point and was greeted by the director of social welfare , mr andrew leung kin @-@ pong , and his directorate officers . </s>
<s> the chief executive exchanged views with the officers on the challenges ahead . </s>
<s> these include a rapidly ageing population and improved services for the elderly , social integration , encouraging and mobilising family support in caring for family members , </s>
<s> the promotion of volunteerism and the need to build a caring community . </s>
<s> this was followed by a tour of the adjacent causeway bay social security field unit and the quarry bay family services centre where mr tung saw the processing of social security applications and the delivery of various family services to people in need . </s>
<s> imf endorses linked exchange rate systems </s>
<s> the recent mission of the international monetary fund ( imf ) gave a very positive assessment of hong_kong 's economic fundamentals and a firm and clear endorsement of the territory 's economic policy framework . </s>
<s> the assessment was made in a concluding statement by an imf staff mission ( imf mission ) following annual consultation discussions with hong_kong . </s>
<s> the financial secretary , mr donald tsang , today ( friday ) said : </s>
<s> " we are pleased that the imf has given us a clean bill of economic health . </s>
<s> we have successfully demonstrated to the imf that our sound economic fundamentals and effective economic policy framework have enabled us to ride the market turbulence with confidence . </s>
<s> " the imf 's endorsement of our linked exchanged rate system further strengthens our commitment to maintain the system . " </s>
<s> in its concluding statement , the imf mission noted that the underlying fundamentals of the hong_kong economy are sound . </s>
<s> the imf mission projected a real gross domestic product ( gdp ) growth of 5.25 per cent to 5.5 per cent this year , in line with the government forecast of 5.5 per cent . </s>
<s> the imf noted that assessing prospects for 1998 is unusually difficult in light of the unsettled state of the financial markets , but projected growth to slow to 4.25 per cent next year . </s>
<s> this is not much below the government 's projected trend gdp growth rate over the medium term at five per cent per annum . </s>
<s> the imf mission noted that the existing policy framework , including the linked exchange rate system , </s>
<s> prudent fiscal policy , careful supervision of the financial sector and non @-@ interventionist approach in factor markets , has proved to be effective and resilient in withstanding external pressures on the hong_kong market . </s>
<s> the imf mission said that continuation of this policy framework should reassure markets that the impact of recent events on hong_kong would be relatively short lived . </s>
<s> the imf mission also commended the hong_kong monetary authority ( hkma ) for taking decisive action to allow a tightening of the monetary conditions and for successfully demonstrating its ability and commitment to defend the linked exchange rate system . </s>
<s> " we were impressed by the successful demonstration of the ability of the authorities in recent events to defend the link . we strongly support continued steadfast adherence to this policy framework , </s>
<s> " said mr david goldsbrough , senior adviser who headed the imf mission . </s>
<s> the chief executive of the hkma , </s>
<s> mr joseph yam , said : " the visit by the imf mission is timely and important . </s>
<s> i am glad that the imf , having seen how our system was put to test and how we responded , </s>
<s> has given a firm endorsement of the linked exchange rate system and top rating to our monetary management . " </s>
<s> the imf mission recognised that allowing interest rates to rise in response to exchange market pressures was an essential element of the currency board mechanism which lies at the heart of hong_kong 's monetary arrangement . </s>
<s> " despite the short @-@ term pain that high interest rates bring , </s>
<s> a period of tighter monetary conditions is appropriate and desirable in cooling certain overheated sectors of the economy and enabling growth to be more sustainable in the longer term , </s>
<s> " said mr goldsbrough . </s>
<s> the imf mission commended the authorities on their strong prudential and regulatory oversight of the financial sector . </s>
<s> the imf mission said that conservative loan @-@ to - value ratios and high levels of capital adequacy of the banking system in hong_kong provided reassurances that it would be able to withstand the effects of the recent financial market volatility . </s>
<s> the imf mission strongly supported the authorities ' commitment to prudent fiscal policies , including the commitment under the basic law to avoid fiscal deficits . </s>
<s> the imf mission urged the continued adherence in 1998 @-@ 99 to the policy of significant fiscal surpluses in view of the recent turmoil , noting the importance of large fiscal reserves in instilling confidence in the authorities ' policy framework . </s>
<s> the imf mission was in hong_kong from october 28 to november 5 , 1997 . </s>
<s> it held discussions with both the private sector and government officials . </s>
<s> at the end of the visit , the imf mission issued the concluding statement , </s>
<s> and on the basis of its finding , it will prepare a report that will be presented to the executive board of the imf for consideration and endorsement . </s>
<s> imf concluding statement </s>
<s> following is the international monetary fund 's concluding statement in respect of the hong_kong special administrative region : </s>
<s> concluding statement for the article iv consultation discussions with the people 's republic of china in respect of the hong_kong special administrative region </s>
<s> november 4 , 1997 </s>
<s> economic prospects and the policy environment in hong_kong sar have been overshadowed recently by the disruptions in many of the southeast asian economies , as well as by volatility within local financial markets . </s>
<s> despite these events , we continue to be of the view that the underlying fundamentals in hong_kong sar are sound . </s>
<s> moreover , the resumption of sovereignty by the people 's republic of china was accomplished smoothly , </s>
<s> and we have been impressed by the confidence that market participants place in the continued commitment to the existing economic policy framework and the rule of law . </s>
<s> looking ahead , the key policy challenge will be to ensure that financial and other policies remain supportive of the economy 's historical resilience and flexibility , </s>
<s> so that the adverse impact of the present financial market volatility is relatively modest and short @-@ lived . </s>
<s> while this may require some adjustment of factor prices - including in the property markets - in order to maintain competitiveness , </s>
<s> the willingness in hong_kong to let this process work is impressive . </s>
<s> indeed , with the recent tightening of liquidity , </s>
<s> the policy framework has responded as envisaged to pressures on the hong_kong dollar , and has provided a welcome element of stability domestically and within the region . </s>
<s> a. near @-@ term economic developments and prospects </s>
<s> recent data provide evidence that the economy continues to recover from the growth slowdown of 1994 @-@ 5 . </s>
<s> real gdp growth accelerated further to an annual rate of 6.25 per cent during the first six months of 1997 , from 5 per cent in 1996. this reflected a pickup in consumption , </s>
<s> which seems to have been boosted by strengthened confidence , as well as higher investment spending . </s>
<s> while inflation remains broadly unchanged from its level last year , in large part because of low import prices , </s>
<s> pressures on resource utilisation appeared to emerge and the unemployment rate has dipped to 2.25 per cent . </s>
<s> we expect that activity will slow to a more sustainable pace during the second half of the year . </s>
<s> household consumption appears to have been strong in the third quarter , but is likely to decelerate thereafter due to the volatility in domestic financial markets , and investment growth also should moderate in late 1997 . </s>
<s> nonetheless , given the strength in the first half , growth is expected to average 5.25 - 5.5 per cent for the year as a whole . </s>
<s> this would leave output at close to capacity , which we estimate to be growing at an annual rate of about 5 per cent . </s>
<s> the unsettled state of financial markets makes it unusually difficult to assess prospects for 1998 . </s>
<s> however - even on the assumption of a relatively early firming of market sentiment - a persistence of somewhat higher interest rates , </s>
<s> the drop in stock prices , and turbulence within the region could slow growth to about 4.25 per cent in 1998 . </s>
<s> household consumption and private investment are likely to be adversely affected by the rise in lending rates and the wealth effect of stock price declines . </s>
<s> the significant slowdown that is expected among many of the southeast asian economies , as well as the devaluations within the region , also would negatively affect hong_kong 's external trade . </s>
<s> however , the impact should be moderate , since these countries represent a relatively small share of hong_kong 's trade , </s>
<s> and the product composition of their exports means that their direct competition in third markets is relatively limited . </s>
<s> thus , we project a moderate improvement in hong_kong 's overall trade position , partly owing to an expected pickup in imports by the mainland . </s>
<s> b. policy issues </s>
<s> the authorities ' commitment to a rules @-@ based and non @-@ interventionist approach should enhance the economy 's ability to withstand the recent regional and financial market turmoil . </s>
<s> in our view , the existing policy framework - which includes the linked exchange rate system , a prudent fiscal policy , </s>
<s> the careful supervision of the financial sector , and a non @-@ interventionist approach to factor markets - has been extremely successful in fostering strong and sustainable growth in the past . </s>
<s> we are encouraged by the authorities ' steadfast adherence to this framework , which provides an environment that facilitates the flexible adjustment of costs and prices to external shocks , </s>
<s> and which should reassure markets that the impact of recent events on hong_kong will be relatively short lived . </s>
<s> as in the past , the mission strongly endorses the authorities ' continued commitment to the linked exchange rate system . </s>
<s> the system has proven its ability as an anchor for economic stability since 1983 . </s>
<s> looking ahead , fundamentals indicate that the link can continue to successfully play this role . </s>
<s> foreign exchange reserves are large and fiscal situation is sound . </s>
<s> moreover , </s>
<s> there is little or no pressure on the current account of the balance of payments , since the goods and services trade deficit is largely offset by net factor income inflows . </s>
<s> the link also plays a critical role in maintaining confidence in hong_kong 's role as an international financial centre , to a significant degree because it demonstrates the continued commitment to free @-@ market policies and monetary autonomy under the " one country , </s>
<s> two systems " approach . </s>
<s> recent events have illustrated that the openness of the domestic financial market means that hong_kong can be subject to external pressures arising from sudden shifts in market sentiment . </s>
<s> appropriately , the authorities have taken forceful action during the past two weeks to tighten significantly monetary conditions , </s>
<s> and have successfully demonstrated their ability and commitment to defend the link . </s>
<s> it is important to recognise that allowing interest rates to rise in response to exchange market pressures is an essential element of the currency board mechanism that lies at the heart of hong_kong 's monetary arrangements . </s>
<s> recent events demonstrate that the system is working exactly as intended , and there are encouraging signs that speculative pressures are easing . </s>
<s> however , confidence could still be easily buffeted by events with the region that are beyond the authorities ' control . </s>
<s> we are confident that the authorities will be cautious and avoid a premature loosening of monetary conditions , despite the short @-@ term pain that high interest rates bring . </s>
<s> a period of tighter monetary conditions may help facilitate a desirable unwinding of the asset price inflation , rapid credit growth , and labour market tightness that emerged during the past year . </s>
<s> our discussions with market participants have indicated a widely @-@ held consensus that the prudential and regulatory oversight of the financial sector is strong , </s>
<s> which has helped underpin confidence in the system . </s>
<s> conservative loan @-@ to @-@ value ratios and high levels of capital adequacy provide reassurance that the banking system will be able to withstand the effects of the recent financial market volatility . </s>
<s> nonetheless , further steps to enhance disclosure and transparency could help reduce market uncertainty , </s>
<s> thereby limiting the risk of unwarranted contagion . </s>
<s> in addition , </s>
<s> further improvements in financial disclosure by foreign and mainland @-@ related banks and nonbanks would also be beneficial , particularly given the growing financial integration between hong_kong and the mainland . </s>
<s> development of a market for mortgage @-@ backed securities will allow banks to enhance their liquidity and risk management , but it will be important to ensure that the mortgage corporation does not create a significant contingent liability for the public sector . </s>
<s> the mission strongly endorses the commitment to prudent fiscal policies , including the commitment under the basic law to avoid fiscal deficits . </s>
<s> we expect the fy 1997 fiscal surplus to be significantly higher than projected in the budget , mainly due to the unusual surge in land @-@ related receipts during the first quarter of the fiscal year . </s>
<s> as these receipts are expected to moderate , </s>
<s> the surplus would narrow automatically in the coming fiscal year , but remain at a comfortable level . </s>
<s> despite the strong fiscal position , and the possibility of a growth slowdown next year , </s>
<s> we would caution against the introduction of substantial expansionary measures in the fy 1998 budget . particularly in view of the recent turmoil in financial markets , </s>
<s> this would not be a propitious moment to signal a shift away from the traditional policy of significant surpluses . </s>
<s> moreover , a discretionary easing of fiscal policy could impede a desirable unwinding of demand pressures . </s>
<s> there remains the issue of the longer @-@ term objective for fiscal policy , especially with regard to the appropriate size of the fiscal surplus and reserves . </s>
<s> in our view , a number of factors argue in favour of maintaining a substantial level of fiscal reserves over the medium term . </s>
<s> large fiscal reserves will play an important role in ensuring that confidence in the authorities ' policy framework - including the exchange rate link - is sustained . </s>
<s> they would also appear to be prudent in view of the heavy dependence of the revenue system on relatively volatile land @-@ related revenues . demographic trends also argue in favour of maintaining a significant fiscal reserve . </s>
<s> the expected rise in the old @-@ age dependency ratio during the next 20 years could result in a substantial increase in the burden on the government for social welfare payments and medical care . </s>
<s> while the mandatory provident fund ( mpf ) will assist in providing for an ageing society , there will still likely be significant fiscal costs associated with a rapid increase in the elderly population . </s>
<s> we support the government 's effort to address the chronic undersupply of housing , especially the emphasis on rationalising housing policy and streamlining its implementation . </s>
<s> however , </s>
<s> public sector intervention in the housing market is large - roughly half the population lives in public housing or receives some form of housing assistance - and there appears to be substantial scope for improved targeting of subsidies . </s>
<s> therefore , the emphasis should be on reducing government intervention in the housing market , particularly by increasing the supply of land for private sector development and more strictly targeting subsidies to the truly needy . </s>
<s> while the near @-@ term outlook is inevitably subject to risks , hong_kong 's medium @-@ term economic prospects are favourable . </s>
<s> productivity is high , particularly within the tradable goods and services sectors , </s>
<s> and hong_kong is in a unique position to benefit from the growing demand by the mainland for financial , business and trade @-@ related services . </s>
<s> moreover , the continued flexibility of goods and labour markets gives confidence that the necessary adjustments will be made as needed to changing economic circumstances . </s>
<s> thus , we would support the intention to avoid an expansion of programs designed to promote specific industries . </s>
<s> rather , </s>
<s> the emphasis should be on measure to increase the competitive environment in the nontraded services sector as a means of reducing business costs . </s>
<s> the ongoing deregulation of the telecommunications sector is an important example of the potential benefits from such efforts . </s>
<s> we also welcome the government 's intentions to streamline administrative procedures , carefully assess the cost of compliance with new regulations , and transfer the provision of services out of the public sector . </s>
<s> finally , the availability of timely and accurate economic data for hong_kong sar , </s>
<s> including hong_kong 's subscription to the fund 's special data dissemination standard , is consistent with the authorities ' commitment to open and transparent policy making . </s>
<s> we would encourage continued improvement in this area , especially with regard to the timely provision of external current and capital account data . </s>
<s> barriers against foreign lawyers not favoured </s>
<s> the secretary for justice , ms elsie leung , </s>
<s> speaking at a pearl river delta law conference organised by the law society of hong_kong and the macau lawyers association , </s>
<s> ms leung pointed out that the provision of legal services is crucial to developed and service @-@ oriented economies . </s>
<s> great advantages will be gained from removing discriminatory barriers that restrict the entry of foreign lawyers to any particular market . </s>
<s> in her speech to the conference on the impact of gats ( general agreement on trade in services ) on the legal profession , ms leung said that removal of automatic recognition of commonwealth qualifications , </s>
<s> and the provision of a competency @-@ based scheme under which all foreign lawyers can gain admission as hong_kong solicitors through specified examinations , have brought hong_kong into line with its general obligations under the agreement . </s>
<s> currently , there are in the sar 413 registered foreign lawyers and 53 registered foreign law firms . </s>
<s> these foreign lawyers come from 16 different jurisdictions , and include 26 lawyers qualified in the mainland . </s>
<s> in addition , there are nine registered associations between foreign and hong_kong law firms . </s>
<s> ms leung said it is clear that in order for hong_kong to comply with the gats requirements , the criteria for admission must be made objective , </s>
<s> reasonable , non @-@ discriminatory and standards @-@ based . </s>
<s> " one way of achieving this would be to provide for an examination to be taken by foreign lawyers who wish to practise as barristers . </s>
<s> the nature of the examination and other requirements could properly differ as between those who are qualified in a common law jurisdiction and those who are not , " she explained . </s>
<s> she said detailed proposals are being formulated by the bar association for consideration by the hksar government , </s>
<s> and she looked forward to the elimination of the current discriminatory admission criteria . </s>
<s> gats has an indirect impact on the way in which law firms are organised , ms leung further commented . </s>
<s> at present in hong_kong there is a rigid demarcation between local and foreign law firms , </s>
<s> although associations may be formed between the two types of firms , and it is not yet possible for multinational legal practices to be established . </s>
<s> world @-@ wide , there is an increasing demand for legal services , offered as a package in respect of the laws of several jurisdictions , </s>
<s> by a single service entity offering one @-@ stop shopping facilities ; and this is particularly true in hong_kong which operates as a regional centre of international trade in goods and services , ms leung said . </s>
<s> in its consultation on legal services reforms , the former hong_kong government solicited views from the legal profession and the wider public as to whether partnerships of local and foreign lawyers should be permitted . </s>
<s> the public response was mixed and the law society was against such partnerships both because it wished to ensure that the practice of hong_kong law remains under the direction of solicitors admitted in hong_kong , </s>
<s> and because it believed that a measure of caution was appropriate during the transition to reunification . </s>
<s> " in my view , the long @-@ term effect of gats on the legal profession is that it will act as a catalyst for the development of multinational legal practices . </s>
<s> " this is because the admission of foreign lawyers and the ability of foreign lawyers to qualify as local lawyers will gradually lead to a break @-@ down of the barriers between local and foreign firms . </s>
<s> " in addition , </s>
<s> the need of consumers of legal advice from various jurisdictions is likely to generate a growing and irresistible consumer tide for the recognition of multinational practices , " ms leung said . </s>
<s> " beyond the commitments of the sar government , the gats has a life of its own . </s>
<s> " the unstoppable consumer @-@ led demand for one @-@ stop shopping will lead inevitably to the establishment of multinational legal practices which will help to fuel the engine of the pacific century , </s>
<s> " she said . </s>
<s> while in macau today , ms elsie leung was welcomed by the secretary for justice of macau , dr jorge noronha e silveira , </s>
<s> at a courtesy meeting before the law conference . </s>
<s> new regulations to ensure safety of building works </s>
<s> consequential to the buildings ( amendment ) ordinance 1996 and the technical memorandum for supervision plans passed in september 1997 by the provisional legislative council , </s>
<s> the government today ( friday ) introduced four regulations to ensure greater safety of building works and street works . </s>
<s> a government spokesman said one of the regulations , </s>
<s> the building ( administration ) ( amendment ) ( no. 4 ) regulation 1997 provides for the administrative frameworks for the supervision plan system scheduled for implementation by the end of this year . </s>
<s> " together with another regulation , namely , the building ( demolition works ) ( amendment ) regulation , </s>
<s> the no. 4 regulation provide additional requirements for demolition works so as to safeguard greater safety of such works which have higher inherent risks as compared with other building works , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> besides these two regulations , </s>
<s> the remaining two which have been made and published in the gazette today are : building ( standards of sanitary fitments , plumbing , </s>
<s> drainage works and latrine ) ( amendment ) ( no. 2 ) regulation 1997 and building ( ventilating systems ) ( amendment ) regulation 1997 . </s>
<s> the spokesman said all the four regulations replaced references to " registered contractors " with " registered general building contractors and registered specialists contractors " and " registered ventilation contractors " with " registered specialist contractors " . </s>
<s> the provisions with respect to the replacement of terms of " registered contractors " with " registered general building contractors " come into operation today , to coincide with the commencement of the new registration system . </s>
<s> " all the other provisions shall come into operation on a date to be appointed by the secretary for planning , environment and lands , " the spokesman added . </s>
<s> new registration system for contractors introduced </s>
<s> the buildings department introduces a new registration system for contractors today ( friday ) to raise their standards and improve the quality of their output . </s>
<s> under the new system , the building authority will maintain separate registers for contractors of general building works and specialised works . </s>
<s> initially , the building authority intends to designate demolition , ventilation , foundation and site formation works as specialised works . </s>
<s> " the registration of general building contractors begins today and that of specialist contractors early next year , " the assistant director of buildings ( legal and management ) , </s>
<s> mr cheung hau @-@ wai , said . </s>
<s> " this arrangement aims to introduce the changes in the building industry in a smooth manner , " mr cheung added . </s>
<s> mr cheung said the registration requirements included qualifications , competence and experience . </s>
<s> individual applicants had to produce documentary evidence to support their claims and their ability to have access to plant and resources , he said . </s>
<s> " corporate applicants will be considered on the adequacy of the management structure and the qualifications , competence and experience of the directors responsible for technical administration , </s>
<s> " he added . </s>
<s> " the more stringent admission criteria under the new registration system will ensure satisfactory standards of the practitioners in the building industry , </s>
<s> " mr cheung said . </s>
<s> all applications will be considered by a contractors registration committee comprising representations from the building authority , </s>
<s> hong_kong institute of architects , hong_kong institute of surveyors , hong_kong institution of engineers , hong_kong construction association and hong_kong electrical & mechanical contractors ' association . </s>
<s> mr cheung said contractors who were registered at the date of the commencement of the amendment legislation would remain registered general building contractors for a two @-@ year transitional period . </s>
<s> " when a registered contractor applies for renewal upon expiry of the transitional period , he should satisfy the building authority that he meets the registration criteria current at the time of application , </s>
<s> " mr cheung said . </s>
<s> registration procedures and details are contained in the practice note for authorised persons and registered structural engineers as well as the practice note for registered contractors . </s>
<s> guidance notes for applicants are also available at the buildings department , 12 th floor , pioneer centre , </s>
<s> 750 nathan road , mongkok , kowloon . </s>
<s> a notice on the commencement of the new registration system is published in today 's gazette . </s>
<s> board amends tuen mun ozp </s>
<s> the town planning board today ( friday ) announced amendments to the approved tuen mun outline zoning plan ( ozp ) . </s>
<s> the major amendments are to reflect the land use proposals for the ex @-@ military sites in tuen mun east , namely the former perowne barracks , gordon hard camp and the pearl island married quarters . </s>
<s> a number of zoning amendments to other areas in tuen mun new town have also been made , </s>
<s> including the recommendations of a land @-@ use review in area 56 of so kwun wat to adjust the zoning boundaries and to reflect existing uses . </s>
<s> two " other specified uses " zones annotated " military camp " on the plan , </s>
<s> which are ex @-@ military sites in tuen mun east measuring about 17.71 hectares and 15.56 hectares respectively , have been rezoned for " residential " and " government , institution or community " uses . </s>
<s> for residential purpose , about 11.9 hectares of land in the former perowne barrack north , area 48 of tuen mun , </s>
<s> has been zoned " residential ( group b ) 1 " for a low @-@ density private residential development , </s>
<s> while 3.64 hectares in the former perowne barracks south has been rezoned " residential ( group b ) 2 " for sandwich @-@ class housing . </s>
<s> another 1.82 hectares in the former pearl island married quarters in area 58 has been rezoned " residential ( group b ) 3 " for a low @-@ density private residential development ; </s>
<s> and 0.35 hectares in the former gordon hard camp in area 48 has been rezoned " residential ( group b ) " to reflect an existing residential development on the site . </s>
<s> for government , institution or community uses , </s>
<s> a 7. 46 @-@ hectare site in the former gordon hard camp has been rezoned " government , institution or community " for a training school and other facilities of the immigration department and for public water @-@ related recreational facilities and a public holiday camp . </s>
<s> furthemore , about 2.97 hectares of land in the former perowne barracks south has been rezoned " government , </s>
<s> institution or community " for a primary school and open space to serve the proposed residential developments and 5.13 hectares in the former perowne barrack north have also been rezoned to meet future demand . </s>
<s> meanwhile , </s>
<s> two sites covering 0.34 hectare in area 16 have been rezoned from " government , institution or community " and " undetermined " to " residential ( group a ) " for private housing developments . </s>
<s> another site covering about 8.47 hectares in area 56 of so kwun wat has been rezoned from " undetermined " to " comprehensive development area " for low @-@ density residential development . </s>
<s> the boundary of a site measuring about 8.02 hectares in area 56 , </s>
<s> which is a private sector participation scheme zoned as " residential ( group a ) " has been slightly adjusted . </s>
<s> another minor adjustment of the zoning boundary is on an existing " residential ( group b ) " site measuring about 0.02 hectare to the south of peridot court in area 58 . </s>
<s> about 0.45 hectare to the north of leung tin village in area 4 and 4.19 hectares near so kwun wat village in area 56 have been rezoned from " green belt " , </s>
<s> " undetermined " and " residential ( group b ) " to " village type development " to provide land for village resite or village expansion respectively . </s>
<s> about 0.15 hectare at yip wong road in area 33 has been rezoned from " green belt " to " other specified uses " annotated " petrol filling station " to meet demand in the area . </s>
<s> about 2.24 hectares of land at so kwun wat road in area 56 has been rezoned from " residential ( group b ) " to " government , </s>
<s> institution or community " for the provision of a community centre cum joint government uses and a primary school . </s>
<s> there is a minor adjustment in the boundary of the existing " government , institution or community " zone at so kwun wat road in area 55 measuring about 2.42 hectares to include two primary schools , </s>
<s> an electricity station , a divisional police station , a fire station and a refuse collection point in the area . </s>
<s> about 3.96 hectares have been rezoned from " residential ( group b ) " and " undetermined " to " open space " to meet the need of the anticipated population growth in the area . </s>
<s> there is also a minor adjustment in the existing " open space " zone measuring about 0.56 hectare in area 55 of so kwun wat . </s>
<s> about 22.17 hectares of land in area 56 of so kwun wat has been rezoned from " undetermined " , </s>
<s> " residential ( group b ) " and " village type development " to ' green belt " to preserve the natural landscape amenity there . </s>
<s> about 2.20 hectares of land in area 56 of so kwun wat has been rezoned from " residential ( group b ) " and " undetermined " to " road " for a proposed road extension branching off from so kwun wat road . </s>
<s> remarks have been added to the notes of the plan for the " residential ( group b ) " zone to incorporate the development restrictions on the " residential ( group b ) 1 " , </s>
<s> " residential ( group b ) 2 " and " residential ( group b ) 3 " zones . </s>
<s> several amendments have also been made to the remarks of the notes for the " comprehensive development area " zone . </s>
<s> the building height restriction has been revised for the " comprehensive development area " at so kwun wat road in area 55 . </s>
<s> development restrictions have been added to the new " comprehensive development area " at tuen mun road in area 56 . </s>
<s> carports , recreational facilities , utility structure , plantroom , </s>
<s> caretaker 's office and caretakers ' accommodation ancillary to the development within the " comprehensive development area " zone have been excluded from gross floor area or plot ratio calculations . </s>
<s> floors used only for ancillary car @-@ parking and caretaker 's accommodation have been excluded from the calculation of number of storeys . </s>
<s> provision has also been added to relax of the development restrictions on application to the town planning board . </s>
<s> remarks have been added to the notes of the " village type development " zone to incorporate the maximum building height for this zone . the " social welfare facility " use has also been added to column 2 of the user schedule of the " open space " zone . </s>
<s> the amendment plan ( no. s / tm / 10 ) is available for public inspection during office hours at : * planning department , </s>
<s> 16 th floor , murray building , garden road , central , hong_kong ; * tuen mun and yuen long district planning office , </s>
<s> 223 hing fong road , kwai chung , new territories ; </s>
<s> 2 nd floor , tuen mun government offices , 1 tuen hi road , tuen mun , new territories . </s>
<s> any person affected by the amendments on the plan may submit written objection to the secretary of the town planning board , c / o planning department , </s>
<s> 13 th floor , murray building , garden road , central on or before january 7 , 1998 . </s>
<s> copies of the draft plan are available for sale at the survey and mapping office , lands department , 14 th floor , murray building , garden road , hong_kong and the kowloon map sales office , ground floor , </s>
<s> govt committed to improving planning system </s>
<s> the government is committed to improving the planning system to make it more open , fair , accountable and efficient , </s>
<s> the director of planning , dr peter pun , said in beijing today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> speaking at the opening ceremony of the " planning with vision " exhibition in beijing , </s>
<s> dr pun said the government hoped to use the town planning white bill as a blueprint for a new ordinance to replace the existing town planning ordinance which had been in force for more than half a century . </s>
<s> public consultation on the town planning white bill was completed last year . </s>
<s> dr pun pointed out that before the new ordinance was in place , there were statutory procedures for residents affected by development plans to raise objections and views . </s>
<s> the government will handle the conflicts of interest in land use between the individual and the public in a fair and objective manner . </s>
<s> he said that while statutory plans provided sufficient clarity for land uses , </s>
<s> the government would change these uses in a flexible manner through the planning application system in order to meet the community 's ever @-@ changing needs . </s>
<s> he said the government would , through strategic planning , </s>
<s> set guidelines for hong_kong 's long @-@ term development to balance the short @-@ term and long @-@ term interests of the individual , private organisations and the community at large as well as to resolve their conflicts . </s>
<s> " we have also launched a detailed study with a view to drawing up a sustainable development system to meet hong_kong 's long @-@ term development strategy and to balance the economic , </s>
<s> social and environmental needs of various quarters , " he explained . </s>
<s> dr pun pointed out that a professional planner should play a co @-@ ordinating role . </s>
<s> on one hand , he had to co @-@ ordinate contributions from various disciplines while on the other , consult different sections of the community on planning in order to defuse possible social conflicts in the course of development . </s>
<s> " we also have to be capable of turning challenges into opportunities , optimising planning options by creative solutions , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> dr pun noted that the " planning with vision " exhibition , was not only the first exhibition on hong_kong 's town planning held in china since the reversion of sovereignty , but also a event to celebrate the 50 th anniversary of the setting up of a delicated planning office within the government . </s>
<s> " we hope to introduce this exhibition to our counterparts in the mainland hong_kong 's town planning system , the difficulties in the course of city development as well as our experiences in overcoming them , " he said . </s>
<s> the " planning with vision " exhibition will be staged at the hall of the national committee of the chinese people 's political consultative conference in beijing from today to november 13 . it will then move to the beijing new world centre from november 22 to december 7 . </s>
<s> the exhibition will also be staged at the exhibition hall of guangzhou city from november 24 to december 21 . </s>
<s> the director general of trade has made an amendment order to the import and export ( general ) regulations , </s>
<s> which introduces licensing requirements for the import into and export from hong_kong equipment for the manufacturing of optical discs ( including compact discs ) . </s>
<s> the amendment order , </s>
<s> which will be tabled at the provisional legislative council ( plc ) on wednesday ( november 12 ) for the council 's negative vetting , </s>
<s> was published in the sar government gazette today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> subject to the approval of the plc , the amendment order will come into effect on december 29 , 1997 . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the trade and industry bureau ( tib ) said that the proposed licensing requirement was one of the measures taken by the government to prevent hong_kong from becoming a haven for the manufacture of pirated optical discs . </s>
<s> it would enable customs officers to better trace the origin and destination of legally imported equipment and facilitate the gathering of intelligence on suspected copyright piracy activities . </s>
<s> " the proposed amendment order stipulates that any person who imports into or exports from hong_kong optical disc manufacturing equipment without a valid licence commits an offence and is liable to a maximum fine of $ 2 million and imprisonment of seven years . </s>
<s> " we are conscious of the need to be business @-@ friendly , </s>
<s> and the licensing requirements will be simple and straight @-@ forward . there will be no charge for application of such a licence , " he said . </s>
<s> applications for licences can be made at the licensing unit of the valuation and verification division , customs and excise department , room 1012 , </s>
<s> canton road government offices building , 393 canton road , kowloon . </s>
<s> enquiries can be made on 2723 3196 or through facsimile 2377 1875 . </s>
<s> animals and birds fees to be revised next month </s>
<s> fees collected by the agriculture and fisheries department for licences , permits and services under five ordinances will be revised from december 19 , 1997 . </s>
<s> the new fees , the majority of which mean an increase of seven per cent or less , were published in the government gazette today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> the five ordinances which cover these licences , permits and services are : </s>
<s> ( a ) public health ( animals and birds ) ordinance ; </s>
<s> ( b ) pounds ordinance ; </s>
<s> ( c ) animals and plants ( protection of endangered species ) ordinance ; </s>
<s> ( d ) plant ( importation and pest control ) ordinance ; </s>
<s> ( e ) marine fish culture ordinance . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the economic services bureau said the public health ( animals and birds ) ordinance provided for the prevention of animals and birds diseases and protection of the public at places where animals or birds were kept . </s>
<s> " the director of agriculture and fisheries ( daf ) can issue various licences and permits and provide services for the administration of the ordinance . fees are charged for these licences and services , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> " the pounds ordinance provides for impounding and disposal of stray animals . </s>
<s> daf will release an impounded animal to its owner upon payment of a pound fee and the relevant expenses within three days of the impounding . </s>
<s> " under the animals and plants ( protection of endangered species ) ordinance , </s>
<s> daf may issue a licence to import , export or possess any scheduled species or controlled medicine , and fees are charged for these licences . </s>
<s> " the plant ( importation and pest control ) ordinance empowers daf to control the importation of plants , </s>
<s> plant pests and soil to prevent possible spread of plant pests and disease . </s>
<s> " fees are charged for the examination of plants and issue of a phytosanitary certificate , for visiting the applicant 's premises for examination of plants , and for the maintenance and treatment of plants and soil under quarantine . </s>
<s> " the marine fish culture ordinance provides for the regulation and protection of marine fish culture . </s>
<s> fees are charged for the grant or renewal of a marine fish culture licence , " he said . </s>
<s> he said the licence fee for marine fish culture was last revised in october 1994 and all other fees in july 1996 . </s>
<s> it was government policy that fees charged should in general be set at levels sufficient to recover the full cost of providing the services . </s>
<s> most of the fees were therefore revised to reflect fully the corresponding costs at 1997 / 98 prices , he said . </s>
<s> licence fees for atv and tvb to be revised </s>
<s> the television ( royalty and licence fees ) ( amendment ) ( no. 2 ) regulation 1997 , </s>
<s> which seeks to revise the annual licence fees payable by the two commercial television broadcasting licensees under the television ordinance , is published in the gazette today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the broadcasting , culture and sport bureau said : </s>
<s> " the licence fee for asia television limited ( atv ) and television broadcasts limited ( tvb ) for the year 1998 will be $ 3,944,000 each . </s>
<s> " subject to negative vetting of the amendment regulation by the provisional legislative council , the new fee will take effect on january 1 , 1998. " </s>
<s> in november 1996 , the government decided that the full @-@ cost licence fees of atv and tvb should be phased over five years . </s>
<s> under the phasing @-@ in arrangement , the licensees have to pay 20 per cent of the full cost of administering the licences in 1997 , 40 per cent in 1998 and so on until full @-@ cost recovery is achieved in 2001 . </s>
<s> " the proposed fee revision is to implement the second phase of the full @-@ cost recovery programme , " he noted . </s>
<s> authorisation and annual fees for captive insurers gazetted </s>
<s> the insurance companies ( authorisation and annual fees ) ( amendment ) regulation 1997 , </s>
<s> gazetted today ( friday ) , introduces a set of new fees for captive insurers . </s>
<s> a captive insurer is an insurer formed by a group of companies to enable them to better manage their risks and insurance costs . </s>
<s> " the government is committed to promoting captive insurance in hong_kong as one of the initiatives to further enhance hong_kong 's position as an international financial centre , " a government spokesman said . </s>
<s> " to this end , the insurance companies ordinance was amended in may 1997 which has , </s>
<s> inter alia , introduced captive insurers as a new class of insurers . " </s>
<s> " as business of captive insurers is restricted to underwriting exclusively general business of its group companies and it is not permitted to engage in statutory insurance businesses like motor and employees ' compensation insurance , captive insurers are subject to a much less stringent regulatory regime than that applicable to ordinary insurers , " he said . </s>
<s> " hence it is necessary to introduce a separate set of fees for them . " </s>
<s> both the authorisation and annual fees payable by a captive insurer are $ 22,600 each . </s>
<s> " the new fees level for captive insurers is significantly lower than the fees level for ordinary insurers , </s>
<s> which is $ 227,300 . it is because the resources for supervising captive insurers are much lower than those for ordinary insurers due to the relaxed regulatory requirements applicable to them . </s>
<s> " the lower level of fees for captive insurers will also help us compete more effectively with other territories in attracting multinational business conglomerates to set up their captive insurers in hong_kong , </s>
<s> " the spokesman explained . </s>
<s> " we are taking various measures to promote captive insurance in hong_kong including the production of information pamphlets and a video on hong_kong 's business environment and regulatory concessions . </s>
<s> " we will also publicise through the overseas economic and trade offices of the sar government and the homepage of the office of the commissioner of insurance on the internet . </s>
<s> at the same time , we are working with relevant government departments and higher educational institutions with a view to enhancing the professional level of insurance education in hong_kong , </s>
<s> which is important for the promotion of captive insurance , " the spokesman added . </s>
