<s> volume and price statistics of external trade in august 1997 </s>
<s> in august 1997 , the volume of hong_kong 's re @-@ exports increased by 4.4 % over a year earlier , while that of domestic exports increased by 10 % . </s>
<s> taken together , the volume of total exports increased by 5.3 % . </s>
<s> concurrently , the volume of imports increased by 7.7 % . </s>
<s> the census and statistics department today ( friday ) released volume and price statistics of external trade for august 1997 . </s>
<s> comparing the first eight months of 1997 with a year earlier , the volume of hong_kong 's re @-@ exports increased by 6.1 % , while the volume of domestic exports recorded no significant change . </s>
<s> taken together , the volume of total exports increased by 5.2 % . </s>
<s> meanwhile , imports increased by 7.2 % in volume . </s>
<s> the growth in volume of trade is derived from the growth in trade value with the effect of price changes discounted . </s>
<s> comparing august 1997 with august 1996 , the prices of re @-@ exports and domestic exports decreased by 1.7 % and 2.8 % respectively . </s>
<s> import prices also decreased , by 2.2 % . </s>
<s> as regards price changes in the first eight months of 1997 over the same period last year , the prices of re @-@ exports and domestic exports decreased by 1.5 % and 2.2 % respectively , </s>
<s> while import prices decreased by 2.2 % . </s>
<s> price changes are reflected by changes in unit value indices which are compiled based on average unit values or , for certain commodities , specific price data . </s>
<s> the terms of trade index , defined as the ratio of total export price index to import price index , </s>
<s> rose by 0.3 % in august 1997 , and by 0.6 % in the first eight months of 1997 over the same period last year . </s>
<s> analysed by end @-@ use category , increases in re @-@ export volume in august 1997 over a year earlier were recorded for most of the categories , </s>
<s> namely , capital goods ( + 9 % ) ; </s>
<s> raw materials and semi @-@ manufactures ( + 8 % ) ; </s>
<s> and consumer goods ( + 1 % ) . </s>
<s> on the other hand , re @-@ export volume of foodstuffs and fuels decreased by 3.2 % and 1.5 % respectively . </s>
<s> over the same period of comparison , the prices of re @-@ exports for all end @-@ use categories , namely , </s>
<s> fuels ; raw materials and semi @-@ manufactures ; capital goods ; </s>
<s> consumer goods ; and foodstuffs decreased , by 6.4 % , 2.8 % , 2.3 % , 0.7 % and 0.6 % respectively . </s>
<s> comparing august 1997 with august 1996 , the volume of domestic exports of electronic components ; and clothing recorded notable increases of 27 % and 21 % respectively . </s>
<s> on the other hand , </s>
<s> the volume of domestic exports of footwear ; and domestic electrical appliances decreased significantly , by 58 % and 55 % respectively . </s>
<s> over the same period of comparison , domestic export prices of metal ores and scrap showed a notable increase of 10 % . </s>
<s> on the other hand , </s>
<s> domestic export prices of electronic components ; and textile yarn and thread decreased significantly , by 13 % and 10 % respectively . </s>
<s> the import volume of foodstuffs increased by 13 % in august 1997 compared with august 1996 . </s>
<s> significant increases in import volume were noted of soya bean oil , peanut oil , vegetable oil and lard ; </s>
<s> and sugar . </s>
<s> notable decreases were recorded in the import volume of tea and coffee ; and animals of the bovine species , live . </s>
<s> over the same period of comparison , the import volume of consumer goods increased by 4 % . </s>
<s> notable increases in import volume were noted of passenger motor cars and alcoholic beverages . </s>
<s> however , the import volume of tobacco manufactures decreased significantly . </s>
<s> the import volume of raw materials and semi @-@ manufactures increased by 9.9 % in august 1997 compared with august 1996 . </s>
<s> rapid increases in import volume were noted of lime , cement , and fabricated building materials except glasses , clay construction materials and refractory construction materials ; </s>
<s> and man @-@ made fibres . </s>
<s> however , significant decreases were noted of inedible animal and vegetable materials ; and woven fabrics of man @-@ made fibres . </s>
<s> imports of fuels decreased by 3 % in volume in august 1997 compared with august 1996 . </s>
<s> as regards capital goods , the volume of imports increased by 11 % in august 1997 over august 1996 . </s>
<s> notable increases were recorded in the import volume of office machinery and construction machinery . </s>
<s> the import volume of transport equipment and textile machinery however decreased . </s>
<s> comparing august 1997 with august 1996 , import prices of capital goods ; </s>
<s> consumer goods ; foodstuffs ; </s>
<s> and raw materials and semi @-@ manufactures decreased by 3.1 % , 2.4 % , 1.9 % and 1.4 % respectively . </s>
<s> on the other hand , import prices of fuels increased by 0.6 % . </s>
<s> details of the above statistics are published in the august 1997 issue of the hong_kong trade index numbers . </s>
<s> the report will be available on sale around november 11 at $ 13 per copy at the government publications centre , ground floor , </s>
<s> low block , queensway government offices , 66 queensway or the publications unit of the census and statistics department , 19 th floor , wanchai tower , 12 harbour road , wan chai . </s>
<s> enquiries regarding regular subscription to this report may be directed to the publications ( sales ) office of the information services department , 28 th floor , siu on centre , </s>
<s> 188 lockhart road , wan chai , hong_kong ( tel no. : </s>
<s> 2598 8194 ) and enquiries on trade indices to the census and statistics department ( tel no. : </s>
<s> 2582 4918 ) . </s>
<s> lions clubs pledges support for voter registration </s>
<s> lions clubs , one of the leading community service organisations in the territory , has pledged its full support to the voter registration drive for the legislative council election next may . </s>
<s> this was noted by the secretary for home affairs , mr david lan , during a speech at the lions clubs ' joint dinner meeting this ( friday ) evening . </s>
<s> praising the civic @-@ mindedness of the lions movement , mr lan said the club had agreed to help disseminate the voter registration message during the registration period which will end on january 16 next year . </s>
<s> the club will encourage its members and service recipients to register as voters and help distribute and collect registration forms . </s>
<s> mr lan added that home affairs department ( had ) would hire temporary staff to make house calls during the voter registration week between december 6 and 12. </s>
<s> " about 30,000 persons , including teachers , students , </s>
<s> temporary community organisers and had staff , will be mobilised to visit two million households in hong_kong . </s>
<s> " during the visits , </s>
<s> they will encourage eligible persons to register as voters and take the opportunity to update the existing electoral roll , " he said . </s>
<s> mr lan said the legislative council election on may 24 , 1998 is very important to hong_kong and no effort would be spared to ensure its success . </s>
<s> apart from the lions clubs , six leading local charities had earlier pledged their support to the voter registration campaign . </s>
