<s> the csd website will include a message from the commissioner of correctional services , mr raymond lai ming @-@ kee . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the department said the process of putting the csd on the internet had taken 18 months at a cost of about $ 80,000 . </s>
<s> new publications on occupational safety and health </s>
<s> the occupational safety and health branch ( oshb ) of the labour department has recently published three publications to enhance the understanding of the employers and employees on the newly @-@ introduced occupational safety and health ordinance and its subsidiary legislation . </s>
<s> these publications are working with employers ; guidance notes on fire safety at workplaces and five @-@ steps to risk assessment . </s>
<s> the booklets are intended to help employers assess the risks at work and weigh up whether enough precautions have been taken to prevent harm . also , </s>
<s> they give basic guidance on fire precautions to be taken to reduce the risk of fire and to ensure that everyone employed in the workplace knows what action to take if a fire occurs . </s>
<s> about 94 000 copies of each of these publications have been sent to industrial and non @-@ industrial establishments employing five persons or more in hong_kong . </s>
<s> additional copies of these booklets can be obtained from field offices of the oshb and district offices of the home affairs department . </s>
<s> record fine for unauthorised building works </s>
<s> the owners of two residential houses in marina cove , sai kung , </s>
<s> were fined $ 160,200 in total recently for failing , without a reasonable excuse , to comply with a statutory order to remove unauthorised building works . </s>
<s> both cases were convicted at the kwun tong magistracy last month . </s>
<s> in the first case , </s>
<s> the registered owner of the house was given a record fine of $ 81,200 which included a principal fine of $ 20,000 and a daily fine of $ 200 for 306 days . </s>
<s> the building authority issued a statutory order on november 24 , </s>
<s> 1995 after discovering illegal structures in the courtyard , on the first floor flat roof , at side of the house on the ground floor and a concrete canopy to the external wall . </s>
<s> these illegal structures had a built @-@ up area of about 90 square metres . </s>
<s> in addition , the void area above the living room on the first floor was slabbed over , and part of the external structural wall facing the courtyard at the ground floor was removed . </s>
<s> the structural party wall with the adjacent house on the ground floor , first floor and the roof was removed and the internal staircase from the lower ground floor to the roof was replaced . </s>
<s> the building authority issued a statutory order on december 28 after discovering an elevated concrete platform extending from the living room to over the rear garden , illegal structures erected on the front and rear flat roofs and an aluminum framed glass structure covering the whole roof . </s>
<s> these illegal structures had a built @-@ up area of about 100 square metres . </s>
<s> the owners were given 60 days to remove all the illegal structures . the assistant director of buildings ( control and enforcement ) , </s>
<s> mr leung shiu @-@ hong , today ( sunday ) urged owners who had been served with statutory orders to comply with the orders without delay . he stressed that approval and consent from the building authority were required before building works should commence . </s>
<s> " property owners intending to carry out building works should appoint an authorised person and , </s>
<s> where necessary , a registered structural engineer , </s>
<s> to prepare plans for the consideration of the building authority in accordance with the provisions of the buildings ordinance , " mr leung said . </s>
<s> " any alterations or additions to buildings without the approval of the building authority are regarded as unauthorised building works and will have to be demolished , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> the maximum penalty for carrying out unauthorised building works is two years ' imprisonment , a principal fine of $ 100,000 and a daily fine of $ 5,000 . </s>
<s> the maximum penalty for failing to comply with a demolition order is one year 's imprisonment , a principal fine of $ 50,000 and a daily fine of $ 5,000 . </s>
<s> mr leung said his department took a very serious view of non @-@ compliance with statutory orders and would invariably take out prosecution in such cases to protect public interest and to ensure building safety . </s>
<s> registration of certification bodies starts </s>
<s> the electrical and mechanical services department ( emsd ) is registering recognised certification bodies ( rcb ) and recognised manufacturers ( rm ) in preparation for the full implementation of the electrical products ( safety ) regulation in may next year . </s>
<s> under the regulation , any household electrical product intended to be supplied in hong_kong must be accompanied by a certificate of safety compliance . </s>
<s> rcb and rm are recognised bodies under the regulation to issue the certificate aside from self @-@ declaration of conformity issued by the product manufacturers . </s>
<s> an emsd spokesman said today ( sunday ) that organisations which were satisfied that they or their overseas principals could meet the criteria and who wished to apply for recognition , </s>
<s> should submit the completed application form , together with supporting documents and application fees , to the department . </s>
<s> application forms are available at the emsd headquarters , 10 / f , 98 caroline hill road , causeway bay , hong_kong . </s>
<s> " the registration is an on @-@ going exercise . we plan to publish the first register of rcbs and rms in the gazette early next year for suppliers ' reference , </s>
<s> " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> meanwhile , more than 450 invitation letters have been sent to potential rcbs and rms worldwide . </s>
<s> organisations qualified to apply for recognition as rcbs are : </s>
<s> * those which have been accepted as national certification bodies under the iecee cb ( international electrotechnical commission system </s>
<s> * those which have been accredited by the hong_kong laboratory accreditation scheme ( hoklas ) ; or </s>
<s> * those which have been accredited by overseas accreditation schemes having mutual recognition agreements with hoklas . </s>
<s> to qualify for application for recognition as an rm , a manufacturer must first have his laboratories accredited under : - the hoklas ; </s>
<s> or </s>
<s> - overseas accreditation schemes having mutual recognition agreements with hoklas ; or - schemes for assessment of testing laboratories as </s>
<s> conference handbook and directory published by the national association of testing authorities of australia on behalf of the international laboratory </s>
<s> accreditation conference , and secondly must have quality systems that conform to iso 9002 and the relevant quality assurance certificates . </s>
