<s> in response to press enquiries on the future use of government house , the chief executive 's office issued the following statement today ( monday ) : </s>
<s> " the chief executive 's office announced in may this year that the chief executive had decided to make government house , a building of significant historical value , </s>
<s> more accessible to the public after the handover . </s>
<s> the chief executive has decided to continue living in grenville house and not in the government house as he feels that it would be a more appropriate way to mark the beginning of a new era after the establishment of the hong_kong special administrative region . </s>
<s> the chief executive has accordingly asked the administration to prepare a proposal on the long term uses of the government house , including the feasibility of converting part of the government house into a museum . </s>
<s> the administration is presently examining various options regarding the long term uses of the government house . </s>
<s> in line with usual government policy on uses of historic monuments , advice of the antiquities advisory board will be sought . </s>
<s> in the course of deciding the long term uses of the government house , we will also consider the frequency of opening the government house to the public . </s>
<s> meanwhile , the government house is being used by the chief executive and mrs tung for official functions . </s>
<s> in addition , the chief executive welcomes applications by government bureaux and departments , charitable organisations and other public organisations to host major events which promote public interests . </s>
<s> based on the existing staffing resources available at the government house , we envisage that the government house could be open for such uses roughly twice a month . </s>
<s> the relevant selection criteria and application procedures are being worked out by the administration . we would make an appropriate announcement on the details in the near future . " </s>
<s> revised recommendations on nine @-@ year compulsory education </s>
<s> the board of education ( boe ) today ( monday ) published the revised edition of the report on review of nine @-@ year compulsory education , which contains recommendations addressing major concerns and highlighting directions for future development in school education . </s>
<s> the report , compiled by the boe sub @-@ committee on review of nine @-@ year compulsory education and accepted by the boe , has been submitted for the consideration of the sar government . </s>
<s> it followed eight weeks ' public consultation on the original recommendations released in march 1997 . </s>
<s> the report notes that during the consultation exercise , the spirit of improving the quality of basic education received strong support and the original recommendations were in general welcomed and endorsed by the public . </s>
<s> there was overwhelming support for continuing with the present policy of offering free and compulsory education to all children of the relevant age , but concern was expressed that the term " compulsory education " may carry derogatory implications . </s>
<s> as a replacement , the sub @-@ committee recommends " universal basic education " which would reflect more accurately and positively the good intention of the policy . </s>
<s> the sub @-@ committee also recommends that a new assessment instrument , academic ability assessment ( aaa ) which tests pupils ' higher @-@ order thinking skills , be devised to replace the academic aptitude test ( aat ) in the secondary school places allocation system . </s>
<s> the proposal received wide support especially from major school councils , sponsoring and educational bodies . </s>
<s> it was felt that the aaa would be more related to curriculum and more relevant to teaching and learning . </s>
<s> to ensure the validity and reliability of aaa , </s>
<s> the sub @-@ committee recommends that the pilot tests of aaa should be run in parallel for two years with the existing aat in a research study and a significant sample size should be adopted . </s>
<s> the research study proposed to validate the new assessment should also pay attention to ensuring a balanced education and minimising unnecessary drilling of pupils . </s>
<s> there are also mixed views from the public on whether english should be tested in aaa . </s>
<s> the sub @-@ committee recommends that the decision should rest upon research findings and results of the pilot tests . </s>
<s> to ensure a quality profession , the report recommends a number of measures to raise the quality of teachers and principals , </s>
<s> namely strengthening initial and in @-@ service education for teachers , offering professional management training for principals , up @-@ grading teachers ' and principals ' entry qualifications , </s>
<s> offering external expert support ( consultancy support teams ) , enhancing incentives for teachers and introducing a performance appraisal system for teachers and principals . </s>
<s> the sub @-@ committee is glad to note that the chief executive has ascertained the move towards an all @-@ graduate and all @-@ trained entry to the teaching profession in the near future . </s>
<s> besides up @-@ grading the qualifications and professional training for new teachers , </s>
<s> the sub @-@ committee recommends that tertiary institutions offering teaching education should also provide conversion courses for serving non @-@ graduate teachers to upgrade their academic and professional qualifications to graduate status . </s>
<s> to enhance teaching and school effectiveness and staff morale , more teachers as well as other professional and clerical support should be provided to schools . </s>
<s> to determine what additional staff should be provided , </s>
<s> it is recommended that a comprehensive staff review should be conducted as soon as possible to study the adequacy , composition , duties and ranks of teaching and non @-@ teaching personnel in school . </s>
<s> the need of strengthening staff support in the use of information technology , school libraries , </s>
<s> counselling , guidance and social work , and the creation of teaching assistant posts are also recommended to be covered by the staff review . </s>
<s> in the course of curriculum development and implementation , the sub @-@ committee recommends that broad directions such as encouraging subject integration , </s>
<s> promoting individualised learning and co @-@ operative learning , giving up streaming of arts and science classes in secondary 3 and strengthening extra @-@ curricular activities should be observed . </s>
<s> the director of education , mrs helen c p lai yu , and her colleagues welcomed the recommendations in the report . </s>
<s> she noted that some of the suggested measures coincide with those in the education commission report no. 7 and have been covered by the policy address 1997 . </s>
<s> the others will be carefully considered in the context of government 's policy objective and strategy for quality education , she said . </s>
<s> the director thanked the chairman and members of the board of education , in particular the sub @-@ committee chairman and members , </s>
<s> for their hard work and thorough deliberations . </s>
<s> government statement on three ii children cases </s>
<s> in response to press enquiries , an sar government spokesman today ( monday ) confirmed that the director of immigration proposed to rescind the removal orders in three cases involving illegal immigrant children from the mainland . </s>
<s> in all three cases , </s>
<s> the application for judicial review of the removal order was made to the court before the enactment of the immigration ( amendment ) ( no. 3 ) ordinance on july 10 . </s>
<s> explaining the above , the spokesman said : </s>
<s> " it has been our practice that retrospective legislation should exempt from its effect legal proceedings which have already commenced before the enactment of the legislation . </s>
<s> this practice has been adopted in the implementation of previous retrospective legislation . " cited as an example is the immigration ( amendment ) ordinance 1991 , </s>
<s> concerning the enactment of the immigration ( amendment ) ( no. 3 ) ordinance , </s>
<s> the spokesman confirmed that there were only three cases which fell to be dealt with under this principle . </s>
<s> the spokesman said : " the director of immigration has written to the three families to propose the recission of the removal orders , </s>
<s> but none of the families have replied yet . " </s>
<s> " the court has been informed of our intention to rescind the removal orders in july this year , </s>
<s> and agreed to stay the proceedings in these three cases so that we can pursue our intention with the families , " he said . </s>
