<s> police 's capability in tackling triads strengthened </s>
<s> following is a question by dr the hon david li and a written reply by the secretary for security , mr peter lai , in the provisional legislative council today ( wednesday ) : </s>
<s> question : </s>
<s> a senior icac official has been reported as saying that triads are responsible for half of the reported crimes committed in hong_kong and that icac intelligence showed that 50 per cent of crimes was not reported . </s>
<s> in this connection , will the government inform this council : </s>
<s> ( a ) how effective is " intelligence " in detecting unreported crimes ; </s>
<s> ( b ) of the measures in place to encourage reporting of triad @-@ related crimes to the police ; and </s>
<s> ( c ) whether it has undertaken any study on the adequacy of the existing police resources for combating triad @-@ related crimes ; if so , what the findings are ? </s>
<s> reply : </s>
<s> madam president , </s>
<s> there is no evidence of a growing triad problem in hong_kong . </s>
<s> the ratio of triad involvement in overall reported crimes has remained stable at about four to five per cent during the past five years and only 3.9 per cent in the first nine months of 1997 . </s>
<s> in 1996 , the number of triad @-@ related reported crimes ( including blackmail , </s>
<s> intimidation , wounding and unlawful societies offences ) dropped by 21 per cent when compared with 1995 . </s>
<s> in the first nine months of 1997 , the downward trend continued with a decrease of 17.8 per cent when compared with the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> as regards the questions raised by the honourable member , the answers are as follows : </s>
<s> - ( a ) the police find intelligence very useful in detecting reported as well as unreported crimes . </s>
<s> this is particularly so in those cases where victims get what they want from criminals and are unlikely to report the crimes to the police , such as in the case of loansharking and drug trafficking . </s>
<s> in assisting us to assess the crime situation , </s>
<s> we also conduct regularly a crime victimisation survey to seek information from members of the public on particulars of criminal acts including those that were not brought to the police 's attention . </s>
<s> ( b ) we adopt a variety of measures to encourage members of the public to report crimes , including triad @-@ related crimes , to the police - </s>
<s> ( i ) the police public relations branch maintains close liaison with the public and runs a series of anti @-@ triad publicity programmes . </s>
<s> these include the screening of announcement of public interest on television , advertising billboards and the production of information leaflets on the channels for reporting crimes ; </s>
<s> ( ii ) the police crime prevention bureau liaises closely with shops and firms to encourage them to report triad activities ; and </s>
<s> ( iii ) the police central witness protection programme offers protection to vulnerable witnesses to encourage members of the public to come forward to give evidence , </s>
<s> particularly in triad @-@ related cases . </s>
<s> ( c ) we keep the adequacy of the existing resources for combating triad @-@ related crimes under constant review . </s>
<s> over the past three years , </s>
<s> we have strengthened the police 's capability in tackling triads by creating 277 posts devoted to anti @-@ triad activities . </s>
<s> in addition , the police have established dedicated units , namely the organised crime and triad bureau and the criminal intelligence bureau , </s>
<s> to take proactive actions against triads . </s>
<s> both the narcotics bureau and the commercial crime bureau also take special interest in triad activities within their areas of responsibility . </s>
<s> furthermore , each police region has an anti @-@ triad unit and every police district has its own anti @-@ triad squad . </s>
<s> apart from providing sufficient manpower , we also ensure that there are adequate legislative powers to tackle the triad problem . </s>
<s> on top of other ordinances , </s>
<s> the organised and serious crimes ordinance was fully implemented in 1995 to enhance the police 's ability to investigate organised and serious crimes , </s>
<s> including triad offences . </s>
<s> the ordinance makes provisions for special investigative powers and confiscation of proceeds of certain crimes including money laundering . </s>
<s> monitoring of speculative activities </s>
<s> following is a question by the hon kennedy wong ying @-@ ho and a written reply by the secretary for financial services , mr rafael hui , in the provisional legislative council today ( wednesday ) : </s>
<s> question : </s>
<s> it is reported that some banks in hong_kong lent large sums of hong_kong dollars to speculators to engage in speculative activities . </s>
<s> in this connection , </s>
<s> will the government inform this council whether it will take measures to step up the monitoring of financial institutions in hong_kong in regard to their involvement in high @-@ risk speculative activities , and whether it will conduct a comprehensive review of the existing monitoring mechanisms and legislation concerned ; </s>
<s> if so , what the details are ? </s>
<s> reply : </s>
<s> within the existing prudential supervisory framework , the hong_kong monetary authority ( hkma ) has developed prudential guidelines on banks ' foreign currency exposures . </s>
<s> through the regular returns submitted by banks , the hkma can ascertain whether banks have incurred significant short hong_kong dollar positions . </s>
<s> for banks which are more active in foreign exchange activities , they are required to submit the returns on a weekly basis . </s>
<s> compliance with the guidelines is checked through regular and ad hoc on @-@ site examinations . </s>
<s> hkma will continue to monitor closely banks ' foreign currency exposures . </s>
<s> furthermore , the real time gross settlement interbank payment system introduced in december 1996 enables the hkma to monitor interbank liquidity on a real time basis . </s>
<s> hkma is therefore capable of ascertaining whether a bank has become significantly short in the hong_kong dollar and , again , </s>
<s> as necessary , follow @-@ up on @-@ site inspections are conducted . </s>
<s> it should however be noted that hong_kong is an international financial centre and a major foreign exchange market where buying and selling of hong_kong dollar against foreign currencies is a normal part of banks ' business . </s>
<s> in the course of conducting foreign exchange transactions , it is not easy for banks to differentiate between trades for hedging purposes or for supporting normal commercial transactions and trades associated with speculation . </s>
<s> in the face of the recent asian foreign exchange market turmoil , </s>
<s> hkma has reminded banks which are major suppliers of hong_kong dollar funding that they should adequately take all relevant risks into account in their funding activities and when pricing their swap and forward transactions , </s>
<s> particularly in times when the hong_kong dollar is under pressure . </s>
<s> more recently , in response to the recent speculative attacks on the hong_kong dollar , the hkma issued a circular on october 23 , </s>
<s> 1997 to remind banks that they should organise their hong_kong dollar funding prudently and not be overly dependent upon the hkma 's liquidity adjustment facility ( laf ) for last resort liquidity support . </s>
<s> the circular also gives a warning that repeated borrowers may be charged penal laf offer rates . </s>
<s> in the interest of maintaining exchange rate stability , it is clearly inappropriate for the hkma to provide hong_kong dollar funding to banks to fund a speculative short hong_kong dollar position through laf . </s>
<s> since the issue of the reminder , no bank has been assessed any penal rate for their laf borrowings . </s>
<s> the present monetary management and prudential supervisory framework has enabled us to fend off speculative pressure against the hong_kong dollar promptly and effectively . </s>
<s> as explained by the financial secretary , we will review our monetary armoury for delivering exchange rate stability and introduce , </s>
<s> where appropriate , measures to strenghen further their robustness and effectiveness . </s>
<s> td welcomes peaceful resolution of cmb labour dispute </s>
<s> the commissioner for transport , mrs fanny law fan chiu @-@ fun , tonight ( thursday ) welcomed the union 's ( motor transport workers general union ) decision to call off the industrial action planned for tomorrow ( friday ) . </s>
<s> at a meeting convened by the labour department this evening , china motor bus ( cmb ) management and union representatives reached agreement over the terms of settlement for the dismissal of 45 mechanics . </s>
<s> cmb also agreed to offer re @-@ employment to those who are qualified , or can be trained , to be drivers . </s>
<s> commenting on the outcome , mrs law said : </s>
<s> " we are pleased to see that cmb management and staff have resolved their differences through rational discussion at the negotiation table . " </s>
<s> mrs law commended both management and staff for having adopted a pragmatic and flexible approach in reaching an amicable agreement and taking into account the interest of the commuting public . </s>
<s> through the conciliation of the labour department , </s>
<s> the dispute involving the recent dismissal of 45 china motor bus ( cmb ) company workers was settled tonight ( thursday ) . </s>
<s> the meeting was arranged by the labour department for the cmb management and its staff representatives to discuss the issue . </s>
<s> the meeting started at about 7 pm and finished at 8.10 pm . </s>
<s> chief labour officer of the labour department , miss bertha cheng wai @-@ yue , said she welcomed the agreement and praised both parties for their sincere and frank attitudes in bringing the dispute to an amicable conclusion . </s>
<s> an agreement covering the terms of settlements has been signed by the two parties immediately after the meeting . </s>
<s> response to enquiries on meeting bus passenger demand </s>
<s> in response to press enquiries on contingency measures to meet passenger demand if china motor bus ( cmb ) workers go on strike tomorrow ( friday ) morning , </s>
<s> a spokesman for the transport department said tonight ( thursday ) that : </s>
<s> " the transport department has made arrangements with other bus companies to provide replacement bus services to fill in for cmb bus services if workers decided to stage industrial action tomorrow . </s>
<s> " we understand that a tri @-@ partie meeting will be held later this evening between the workers and the management with the mediation of the labour department . </s>
<s> the outcome of the meeting may not be known until the late hours tonight . </s>
<s> " in the interest of the commuting public , the department will announce the contingency measures before 9 pm via the information services department so that the public can have a general outline to prepare for their morning journey tomorrow . </s>
<s> " if cmb workers decided to call off their industrial action , these measures will not be implemented . </s>
<s> " the public are advised to listen to radio and television news for an update before they depart for their morning journey . </s>
<s> " we can assure members of the public on hong_kong island that bus services will be maintained under any circumstances . " </s>
<s> public transport contingency plans well in hand </s>
<s> the government has worked out a set of contingency arrangements which will involve other public bus operators providing replacement services in the event that china motor bus ( cmb ) is unable to provide services to the public tomorrow morning , </s>
<s> the commissioner for transport , mrs fanny law fan chiu @-@ fun , said today ( thursday ) . </s>
<s> speaking at a press briefing today , mrs law also appealed to the management of cmb and its staff union to take public interest as their primary consideration while continuing to discuss calmly to reconcile their differences . </s>
<s> expressing government 's concern over the dispute , mrs law said : </s>
<s> " we very much regret that the union has found it necessary to even suggest industrial action but we really hope that it would have public interest in mind while seeking to reach an agreement with the management . " </s>
<s> while the daily patronage of cmb is about 500,000 , an estimated 60,000 people will be affected if the cmb workers go on strike during the morning peak hours tomorrow ( friday ) . </s>
<s> outlining the contingency arrangements in general , </s>
<s> mrs law said priority would be given to areas , like shek o and ma hang , where services were solely provided by cmb and major housing estates in southern and eastern districts , </s>
<s> which are at a distance from the mtr . </s>
<s> mrs law said : </s>
<s> " the transport department has liaised with major public bus operators including kowloon motor bus , the citybus and the public omnibus operators association to provide replacement services . </s>
<s> between 300 and 400 buses could be mobilised to serve the public during stoppage of cmb services . </s>
<s> " more details will be provided to the public when it has become necessary to implement these contingency arrangements . " </s>
<s> she also noted that shuttle bus services would be available between major housing estates and the nearest mtr stations . </s>
<s> while regretting that any cmb 's industrial action would inevitably cause some inconvenience , she advised commuters to stagger their travelling time and travel by the mtr as much as possible . </s>
<s> she also said that the department had alerted the education department of the possibility of stoppage of cmb services and would continue to liaise closely with them on the possible implementation of the contingency arrangements . </s>
<s> when asked how the incident would affect the negotiation of cmb 's renewal of its franchise next year , </s>
<s> mrs law said there was no direct relation between the two matters but the event did reveal that there were conflicts between the management and its staff and the government would take that into account in the franchise discussion . </s>
<s> " throughout the franchise negotiation , </s>
<s> we have started from the premise that we will assist cmb to further improve their services up to a level which will meet the public 's expectations . a company 's commitment and its ability to run an efficient bus operation will clearly have to be taken into account , </s>
<s> " she said . </s>
<s> on bus safety , mrs law said that since cmb had been able to meet the department 's standards on its fleet maintenance , </s>
<s> the safety of cmb buses on roads should not pose a problem if the strike was only to last for a short period of time . </s>
