<s> the value of domestic exports for september 1997 increased by 4.2 % over a year earlier to $ 19.0 billion , </s>
<s> while that of re @-@ exports , at $ 107.8 billion , showed virtually no change . </s>
<s> meanwhile , imports increased by 1.9 % to $ 133.2 billion . </s>
<s> these figures are part of the statistics on external trade with breakdown by country / territory and commodity for september 1997 released today ( thursday ) by the census and statistics department . </s>
<s> comparing september 1997 with september 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to the netherlands ( + 8.5 % ) , france ( + 6.4 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland of china ( the mainland ) ( + 5.6 % ) and singapore ( + 1.8 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to japan ( - 13 % ) , </s>
<s> south korea ( - 7.5 % ) , germany ( - 3.9 % ) , the united_states ( - 2.8 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( - 2.3 % ) and the united kingdom ( - 0.1 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first nine months of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to taiwan ( + 12 % ) , </s>
<s> the netherlands ( + 7.5 % ) , singapore ( + 6.2 % ) , the united_states ( + 5.7 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland ( + 5.5 % ) , the united kingdom ( + 5.0 % ) and france ( + 4.6 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of re @-@ exports to germany ( - 4.7 % ) , </s>
<s> japan ( - 2.8 % ) and south korea ( - 2.7 % ) . </s>
<s> taking all destinations together , the value of re @-@ exports in the first nine months of 1997 , at $ 909.3 billion , </s>
<s> increased by 3.7 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> comparing the first nine months of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , the value of re @-@ exports of most principal commodity divisions increased . </s>
<s> more notable increases were registered for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 9.2 billion or 18 % ) ; electrical machinery , </s>
<s> apparatus and appliances , and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 8.3 billion or 9.3 % ) ; </s>
<s> miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of baby carriages , toys , games and sporting goods ( by $ 6.6 billion or 5.9 % ) ; </s>
<s> clothing ( by $ 4.9 billion or 6.6 % ) ; </s>
<s> textiles ( by $ 3.9 billion or 5.5 % ) ; photographic apparatus , </s>
<s> equipment and supplies , optical goods , watches and clocks ( by $ 1.3 billion or 3.2 % ) ; </s>
<s> and footwear ( by $ 1.3 billion or 2.5 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , </s>
<s> a decrease in the value of re @-@ exports was registered for telecommunications and sound recording and reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 3.2 billion or 3.8 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing september 1997 with september 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to the netherlands ( + 18 % ) , </s>
<s> taiwan ( + 14 % ) , the united_states ( + 13 % ) , the mainland ( + 8.0 % ) , </s>
<s> the united kingdom ( + 6.9 % ) and japan ( + 1.4 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to germany ( - 18 % ) , </s>
<s> singapore ( - 14 % ) , </s>
<s> france ( - 8.8 % ) and canada ( - 0.2 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first nine months of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , there was virtually no change in the value of domestic exports to taiwan , while decreases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to singapore ( - 17 % ) , </s>
<s> germany ( - 8.7 % ) , japan ( - 7.5 % ) , </s>
<s> canada ( - 0.8 % ) and the united kingdom ( - 0.6 % ) . </s>
<s> nevertheless , increases were recorded in the value of domestic exports to france ( + 10 % ) , </s>
<s> the netherlands ( + 7.4 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland ( + 3.6 % ) and the united_states ( + 0.5 % ) . </s>
<s> taking all destinations together , the value of domestic exports in the first nine months of 1997 , at $ 154.7 billion , </s>
<s> decreased by 1.2 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> comparing the first nine months of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , more notable decreases in the value of domestic exports were registered for office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 1.9 billion or 19 % ) ; </s>
<s> textiles ( by $ 784 million or 7.7 % ) ; </s>
<s> photographic apparatus , equipment and supplies , optical goods , </s>
<s> watches and clocks ( by $ 746 million or 6.6 % ) ; </s>
<s> and manufactures of metals ( by $ 560 million or 18 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , more notable increases in the value of domestic exports were registered for electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , </s>
<s> and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 1.8 billion or 7.9 % ) ; </s>
<s> clothing ( by $ 1.4 billion or 2.7 % ) ; </s>
<s> and professional , scientific and controlling instruments and apparatus ( by $ 1.1 billion or 47 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing september 1997 with september 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of imports from germany ( + 7.9 % ) , </s>
<s> the united_states ( + 6.6 % ) , japan ( + 5.1 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland ( + 2.8 % ) , malaysia ( + 2.0 % ) and taiwan ( + 2.0 % ) . </s>
<s> however , decreases were recorded in the value of imports from south korea ( - 10 % ) , </s>
<s> singapore ( - 9.5 % ) , </s>
<s> the united kingdom ( - 5.0 % ) and italy ( - 4.9 % ) . </s>
<s> comparing the first nine months of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , increases were recorded in the value of imports from malaysia ( + 15 % ) , </s>
<s> the united kingdom ( + 13 % ) , germany ( + 12 % ) , japan ( + 6.4 % ) , </s>
<s> the mainland ( + 5.8 % ) , </s>
<s> the united_states ( + 3.6 % ) , italy ( + 1.4 % ) and taiwan ( + 0.1 % ) . </s>
<s> however , the value of imports from singapore and south korea decreased by 2.3 % and 1.1 % respectively . </s>
<s> taking all sources together , the value of imports in the first nine months of 1997 , at $ 1,191.4 billion , </s>
<s> increased by 5.0 % over the same period in 1996 . </s>
<s> comparing the first nine months of 1997 with the same period in 1996 , more notable increases in the value of imports were registered for electrical machinery , apparatus and appliances , </s>
<s> and electrical parts thereof ( by $ 16.8 billion or 12 % ) ; </s>
<s> office machines and automatic data processing machines ( by $ 12.4 billion or 21 % ) ; </s>
<s> clothing ( by $ 8.9 billion or 11 % ) ; </s>
<s> telecommunications and sound recording and reproducing apparatus and equipment ( by $ 6.2 billion or 6.0 % ) ; </s>
<s> road vehicles ( by $ 4.9 billion or 16 % ) ; </s>
<s> and miscellaneous manufactured articles consisting mainly of baby carriages , toys , games and sporting goods ( by $ 4.7 billion or 5.8 % ) . </s>
<s> over the same period , a more notable decrease in the value of imports was recorded for photographic apparatus , equipment and supplies , </s>
<s> optical goods , watches and clocks ( by $ 1.2 billion or 2.5 % ) . </s>
<s> all the trade statistics described here are measured at current prices and no account has been taken of changes in prices between the periods of comparison . </s>
<s> a separate analysis of the volume and price movements of external trade for september 1997 will be released in early december 1997 . </s>
<s> detailed trade statistics analysed by commodity and by country / territory are published in trade statistics reports . </s>
