<s> district committees on building and fire safety planned </s>
<s> the home affairs department plans to set up a district committee in each of its 18 districts to enhance public awareness of the importance of building maintenance and fire prevention . </s>
<s> speaking at a reception hosted by the central and western district office for members of owners ' corporations ( ocs ) and mutual aid committees ( macs ) today ( saturday ) , the secretary for home affairs , mr david lan , </s>
<s> said the committees were designed to include representatives from relevant government departments and members of the public . </s>
<s> mr lan reiterated that the government was always committed to promoting effective building management and providing supportive services to property owners . </s>
<s> " these committees , which are expected to come into operation next year , </s>
<s> can provide a platform for the government on a regular basis to collect and consider the views of the public especially in the areas of building maintenance and fire safety , " he added . </s>
<s> mr lan also took the opportunity to thank all oc / mac representatives for attending the reception and sharing among themselves their valuable experiences in building management . </s>
<s> the director of home affairs , mrs shelley lau , also emphasised the importance of effective building management at the reception and outlined to oc / mac members a wide range of measures taken by the department to assist them in upgrading the management of their buildings . </s>
<s> " had is now setting up a building management resource centre to provide information and services to building owners , </s>
<s> residents and management bodies to help them improve management and safety standards and the maintenance of their buildings , " mrs lau said . </s>
<s> " professionals including lawyers , </s>
<s> surveyors , accountants and property management personnel have also been invited to participate and contribute their expert advice to maximise the centre 's effectiveness . " </s>
<s> " this centre will first be set up in kowloon and start operation next year . other centres will be established throughout the territory later , " she added . </s>
<s> in addition to the seminars and training courses on building management and fire prevention organised regularly by district offices , </s>
<s> mrs lau also called on oc / mac members to participate in the building management seminar '98 which would be held in june next year . </s>
<s> " this is a large @-@ scale territory @-@ wide building management seminar organised by the department to provide a forum for owners from various districts to exchange their views , </s>
<s> " said mrs lau . </s>
<s> she also appealed to all property owners to set up ocs in their buildings in the future . </s>
<s> " the department will continue to encourage and provide owners with all the support necessary for the formation and operation of ocs and it is no doubt that owners ' active participation and support is a prerequisite to the success of effective building management . " </s>
