<s> may 1 and buddha 's birthday proposed to be new general holidays </s>
<s> the government announced today ( tuesday ) its proposal to designate may 1 and the buddha 's birthday ( which falls on the eighth day of the fourth month of the lunar calendar ) as general holidays from 1999 . </s>
<s> these will replace two of the existing general holidays which are not also statutory holidays . </s>
<s> in effect , the total number of general holidays will be capped at 17 days a year . </s>
<s> the government will consult employers ' and employees ' organisations and the financial services sector as to which of the existing general holidays should be offset . </s>
<s> the proposal was endorsed by the executive council at its meeting this morning . </s>
<s> deputy secretary for education and manpower , mr matthew cheung kin @-@ chung , said today the proposal explained the need for the government to postpone the commencement date for may 1 as a statutory holiday from 1998 to 1999 . </s>
<s> the employment ( amendment ) ( no. 5 ) bill 1997 , which is currently before the provisional legislative council ( plc ) , is largely designed to give effect to this deferral . </s>
<s> according to mr cheung , anomalies would arise if may 1 was made a statutory holiday but not a general holiday as well . </s>
<s> statutory holidays are employment benefits which must be granted to employees , including those working in banks and schools , " he said . </s>
<s> " even though bank staff will be entitled to a statutory holiday on may 1 , </s>
<s> banks will need to maintain business as usual for operational reasons if may 1 is not designated a general holiday as well . </s>
<s> although employers can assign an alternative holiday to their employees by giving them 48 hours ' advance notice , there will be inevitable staff deployment difficulties . </s>
<s> " as the list of general holidays for 1998 has already been published and as it takes time to consult on which of the existing general holidays should be offset by may 1 , </s>
<s> it is necessary to defer the commencement date of may 1 as a statutory holiday to 1999. " </s>
<s> turning to the proposed buddha 's birthday , mr cheung said that for many years , the hong_kong buddhist community had sought to make the buddha 's birthday a general holiday . </s>
<s> the hong_kong buddhist association has now written formally to the government on this subject . </s>
<s> " there are an estimated 800,000 buddhists in hong_kong , and the bulk of the local population , </s>
<s> even if not buddhists themselves , also respect buddha . </s>
<s> buddhism is a major eastern religion and the buddha 's birthday is an important oriental religious festival in its own right . </s>
<s> we support the request of the buddhist community , and propose that the buddha 's birthday should also be celebrated as a general holiday from 1999 onwards , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> he pointed out that the designation of may 1 and the buddha 's birthday would not increase the total number of general holidays in a year . </s>
<s> " at 17 days a year , </s>
<s> the number of general holidays other than sundays in hong_kong is already better than our neighbouring economies . </s>
<s> " it is hard to justify increasing this number in terms of hong_kong 's competitiveness as against our neighbouring economies or the additional economic cost involved . </s>
<s> the cost impact of an extra general holiday is 0.2 per cent of the total wage bill or $ 692 million . </s>
<s> " in view of this , we believe that , as a matter of policy , </s>
<s> the total number of general holidays other than sundays should be capped at 17 days a year . it follows that for may 1 and the buddha 's birthday to be new general holidays , </s>
<s> then these days need to be offset by two of the existing six general holidays which are not also statutory holidays . </s>
<s> primarily from employers ' and employees ' organisations as well as the financial services sector on which two of the existing general holidays that are not also statutory holidays might be offset by the new general holidays , </s>
<s> " mr cheung said . </s>
<s> as the government has proposed under the employment ( amendment ) ( no. 5 ) bill 1997 to designate july 1 and october 1 as statutory holidays in place of the existing two floating statutory holidays , </s>
<s> only six general holidays that are not also statutory holidays may be used for offsetting . </s>
<s> these holidays are good friday , day after good friday , easter monday , </s>
<s> sino @-@ japanese war victory day ( third monday in august ) , october 2 and the first weekday after christmas day ( boxing day ) . </s>
<s> the administration has given notice to resume the second reading debate of the employment ( amendment ) ( no. 5 ) bill 1997 at the sitting of the provisional legislative council on december 3 , 1997 . </s>
