<s> director of public prosecutions appointed </s>
<s> the government announced today ( thursday ) the promotion of mr i g cross to law officer with effect from october 15 , </s>
<s> the director of public prosecutions is the head of the prosecutions division of the department of justice and is responsible for public prosecutions , the development of prosecutions policy and advising the secretary for justice on all criminal matters . </s>
<s> the following is a brief biographical note on mr cross : </s>
<s> mr cross , aged 46 , </s>
<s> was called to the bar in the united kingdom in 1974 and to the hong_kong bar in 1981. he was appointed queen 's counsel ( now senior counsel ) in 1990 . </s>
<s> he joined the former legal department in 1978 and has since been working in the prosecutions division in the last 19 years . </s>
<s> he was promoted to the rank of principal government counsel in 1991 . </s>
<s> he has been acting as law officer since october 15 , 1997 upon the departure of mr peter v t nguyen , the former director of public prosecutions . </s>
<s> sj welcomes appointment of dpp </s>
<s> the secretary for justice , ms elsie leung oi @-@ sie , today ( thursday ) welcomed the government announcement of the promotion of mr i g cross as law officer to succeed mr peter nguyen as director of public prosecutions . </s>
<s> ms leung said she was pleased that mr cross is appointed to the post . </s>
<s> he is an outstanding criminal lawyer and is well respected by the judiciary and the legal profession , she said . </s>
<s> financial secretary to visit uk </s>
<s> the financial secretary , mr donald tsang , will depart tomorrow ( friday ) evening for a visit to the uk . </s>
<s> his programme covers mainly london but includes a side trip to oxford . </s>
<s> the highlight of the financial secretary 's visit programme will be his address on november 24 to an international conference entitled " china and britain : partners for the 21 st century " . </s>
<s> other chinese officials participating in the conference include chinese ambassador to london , mr ma zhengang ; minister , research office of the state council , mr wang mengkui ; and secretary general , state commission for the restructuring of the economic system , </s>
<s> the conference is co @-@ organised by the confederation of british industry , the royal institute of international affairs and the institute of export . </s>
<s> mr tsang will take the opportunity to tell the overseas community how hong_kong has fared since the handover . </s>
<s> he will also update them on recent developments in hong_kong 's financial market with a view to reinforcing their confidence in hong_kong 's economic prospects . </s>
<s> the financial secretary will meet other leading personalities in the uk financial and banking community during his stay in london , </s>
<s> including chief executive of the financial services authority , mr andrew winckler ; and governor of the bank of england , mr eddie george . </s>
<s> before mr tsang leaves london for oxford on november 25 , he will address the hong_kong association over lunch . </s>
<s> when in oxford he will attend a high @-@ table dinner at st anthony 's college , during which he will address the college 's staff and students on how he sees the transition in hong_kong . </s>
<s> during the last day of his visit ( november 27 ) in london , mr tsang will attend a roundtable discussion at the royal institute of international affairs . </s>
<s> while in the uk , mr tsang will take the opportunity to meet with the local media . </s>
<s> mr tsang will return to hong_kong on november 28 ( friday ) . </s>
<s> director @-@ general assures british executives </s>
<s> the director @-@ general of the hong_kong economic and trade office in london said hong_kong welcomes more british companies to set up business in the territory . mr john tsang told british executives attending the hong_kong executive club gala dinner tonight ( wednesday , </s>
<s> london time ) that the united kingdom is the largest foreign investor in hong_kong 's non @-@ manufacturing sector . </s>
<s> " hong_kong gains extensive benefit from the experienced and dynamic international business community and there is a good fit between what the uk and hong_kong have to offer each other , </s>
<s> " he said . </s>
<s> he also briefed the executives on the latest developments in hong_kong following the currency crisis in southeast asia . </s>
<s> mr tsang said the recent downward adjustments in the currencies of hong_kong 's asian neighbours should have little effect on the territory 's competitiveness . </s>
<s> less than 10 per cent of the territory 's gdp is derived from the manufacturing sector and two @-@ thirds of our domestic exports and three @-@ quarters of our re @-@ exports within asia are bound for china and japan , against the currencies of which ours is stable . </s>
<s> " in the short run , </s>
<s> higher interest rates may cause pain for some , but high interest rates will also provide incentives to save and help to moderate property prices , " said mr tsang . </s>
<s> " this will help to bring down inflation and the cost of doing business in hong_kong for international firms , contributing to an increase in our competitiveness . " </s>
<s> mr tsang said that five months after the handover , the guarantees of " one country , two systems " are no longer mere promises . </s>
<s> they are now realities . </s>
<s> the only turbulence in hong_kong had been caused by the two waves of currency speculation against the hong_kong dollar , but the hong_kong dollar managed to maintain its strength amid the dramatic devaluation of other asian currencies . </s>
<s> he said the hong_kong special administrative region government has been determined to maintain the link and has employed all the measures at its disposal to counter @-@ attack the onslaught from speculators . </s>
<s> mr tsang said : " there has been no panic in hong_kong . </s>
<s> our foreign exchange reserves , at us $ 88 billion , </s>
<s> is the third largest in the world , after china and japan . </s>
<s> we have no public sector debt . </s>
<s> we have a very strong fiscal position with public sector expenditure operating under very tight discipline . </s>
<s> our economy is growing at a healthy rate and we should still be able to achieve our gdp forecast of 5.5 per cent real growth for 1997. " </s>
<s> mr tsang said some people may doubt whether hong_kong still needs to peg the hong_kong dollar to the us dollar now that the political uncertainties surrounding the handover have evaporated . </s>
<s> he said these doubters may not realise that hong_kong is committed to the us dollar peg for sound economic reasons and not just on political grounds alone . </s>
<s> external trade accounts for 285 per cent of our gdp . </s>
<s> given our exposure to external costs , a volatile exchange rate would impose huge uncertainties on the community , not just on banks and traders , </s>
<s> but on almost every company , retailer and consumer . </s>
<s> health advice on preparing vegetables </s>
<s> members of the public are today ( thursday ) advised to wash and blanch vegetables thoroughly before cooking . </s>
<s> the appeal was made by the assistant director ( hygiene ) of the department of health , dr gloria tam , following one case of food poisoning related to pesticide contaminated vegetables confirmed last night . </s>
<s> the case affected a family of three and was related to consumption of chinese chrysanthemum and french beans . </s>
<s> dr tam said that since the advent of the autumn season , the department of health had stepped up checking and sampling at man kam to food control office and retail outlets . </s>
<s> the food poisoning case was the first case related to vegetables contamination reported to the department so far this year . </s>
<s> before that , there were three confirmed food poisoning cases related to pesticide contaminated vegetables in 1996 . </s>
<s> to reduce food poisoning by pesticide contaminated vegetables , members of the public are strongly advised to take the following precautionary measures : </s>
<s> * do not patronise unlicensed hawkers ; </s>
<s> * do not buy vegetables with an obvious strange smell ; </s>
<s> * wash well before cooking ; </s>
<s> * dip vegetables into clean water for one hour to allow pesticide to leach out ; </s>
<s> * blanch in boiling water and pour away the water used for blanching as it may contain dissolved pesticides ; and </s>
<s> * cook thoroughly before consumption . </s>
<s> more samples taken to ensure safe vegetable supply </s>
<s> the vegetable marketing organisation ( vmo ) has taken more vegetable samples for testing to ensure that the vegetables handled by its cheung sha wan wholesale market are safe for consumption . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the agriculture and fisheries department ( afd ) said the vmo had taken 250 samples for pesticide residue test today ( thursday ) after a pesticide contamination case was confirmed by the department of health . </s>
<s> the vmo handles more than half of the fresh leafy vegetables consumed in hong_kong which include quality vegetables produced by accredited farms monitored by afd . </s>
<s> to rectify the situation of misuse of pesticides on vegetable farms , the afd and vmo have been jointly implementing an accredited farm scheme since 1994 . </s>
<s> under the scheme , the department monitors the participating farms ' horticultural practice , in particular on the use of pesticides . </s>
<s> the accredited produce is further checked by vmo against pesticide contamination before marketing to the accredited retailers specially appointed by vmo . all the accredited retailers have a authorization logo displayed at the vegetable selling stalls . </s>
<s> the spokesman said members of the public may wish to look for these accredited retailers for safe and quality vegetables . </s>
<s> mutual recognition agreement facilitates trade </s>
<s> under the mutual recognition agreement signed on november 19 ( wednesday ) in tokyo where the annual meeting is held , </s>
<s> laboratory accreditation bodies from six apec economies - australia ; hong_kong , china ; new zealand ; singapore ; </s>
<s> chinese taipei and the united_states - will accept test reports and calibration certificates endorsed by other parties , </s>
<s> reducing the need for re @-@ resting of products in an importing economies and saving time and money for exporters . </s>
<s> mr john gilmour , the chairman of the aplac , </s>
<s> said : " most economies have technical requirements for importing goods . </s>
<s> " they also have their own testing and inspection facilities , </s>
<s> but test reports from one country are not typically accepted in other markets . that can create barriers to trade . " </s>
<s> " mutual recognition agreements , such as this one signed in tokyo , </s>
<s> are an effective way to remove these barriers , " he said . </s>
<s> the signatory of the agreement from hong_kong is the hong_kong laboratory accreditation scheme ( hoklas ) operated by the industry department . </s>
<s> a voluntary scheme launched in 1985 , the prime objectives of hoklas is to upgrade the standards of testing and management of laboratories , </s>
<s> confer official recognition to competent laboratories and promote the acceptance of test certificates from accredited laboratories both locally and overseas . </s>
<s> dr l h ng , executive administrator of the hoklas , </s>
<s> said that the agreement indicated the importance hong_kong placed on establishing links with credible and major schemes in the world , particularly those of our major trading partners . </s>
<s> " laboratory testing plays a vital role in quality assurance in industry and it is essential that such testing services provided by local laboratories are shown to be competent and reliable and to have attained recognition overseas . </s>
<s> " this is the first multilateral agreement that hoklas has signed . " in addition , </s>
<s> hoklas has signed bilateral agreement with overseas laboratory accreditation schemes of six countries , namely , the united_states , the united kingdom , australia , </s>
<s> new zealand , the netherlands and singapore , " she said . </s>
<s> dr ng also said that the hoklas had signed an interim bilateral agreement with the european co @-@ operation for accreditation of laboratories ( eal ) multilateral agreement group which comprises 14 european countries . </s>
<s> " agreements with other overseas laboratory accreditation schemes are also being negotiated , " she said . </s>
