<s> value of manufacturers ' orders @-@ on @-@ hand in september 1997 </s>
<s> the value of manufacturers ' orders @-@ on @-@ hand for local production in september 1997 increased by 2 % over a year earlier , according to the provisional results of a monthly survey released today ( thursday ) by the census and statistics department . </s>
<s> comparing september 1997 with september 1996 , </s>
<s> increases in the value of orders were recorded in the printing and publishing industry ( + 13 % ) ; the electronic products industry ( + 7 % ) ; and the textiles industry ( + 2 % ) . </s>
<s> however , </s>
<s> decreases in the value of orders were recorded in the plastic products industry ( - 22 % ) , the fabricated metal products industry ( - 13 % ) , the electrical products industry ( - 7 % ) and the wearing apparel industry ( - 2 % ) . </s>
<s> compared with august 1997 , and bearing in mind that this comparison may be affected by seasonal factors , the value of manufacturers ' orders @-@ on @-@ hand in september 1997 decreased by 7 % . </s>
<s> the monthly survey of orders @-@ on @-@ hand covers a sample of some 300 manufacturing firms engaging 50 or more workers . </s>
<s> manufacturers ' orders @-@ on @-@ hand refer to orders and parts of orders received earlier by manufacturers for local production which remain unfilled as at the end of the reference month . </s>
<s> orders received by traders not engaged in production are included if such orders are further placed to manufacturers for production locally . </s>
<s> however , orders placed to manufacturing firms for production in the mainland of china and other places outside hong_kong are not included in this series of orders @-@ on @-@ hand statistics . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the department pointed out that caution should be exercised in interpreting the manufacturers ' orders @-@ on @-@ hand figures in a single month . instead , </s>
<s> the trend movement of the series as displayed over a wider span of time points should be looked at . </s>
<s> the survey report for september 1997 , at $ 6 a copy , is now available for sale at the government publications centre , queensway government offices , low block , </s>
<s> ground floor , queensway , and at the census and statistics department publications unit , 19 th floor , wanchai tower , </s>
<s> 12 harbour road , wan chai . </s>
<s> enquiries about the survey results may be made to the industrial production statistics section of the census and statistics department on 2805 6441 . </s>
<s> the following table shows the year @-@ on @-@ year percentage changes in the value of orders @-@ on @-@ hand in different manufacturing industries . </s>
<s> aug 97 sept 97 over aug 96 over sept 96 ( revised ) ( provisional ) </s>
<s> all industries covered in the survey + 1 + 2 </s>
<s> * wearing apparel + 2 - 2 </s>
<s> * textiles + 2 + 2 </s>
<s> * electronic products + 2 + 7 </s>
<s> * electrical products - 8 - 7 </s>
<s> * fabricated metal products - 11 - 13 </s>
<s> * plastic products - 26 - 22 </s>
<s> * printing and publishing + 16 + 13 </s>
<s> human organ transplant regulation to be gazetted tomorrow </s>
<s> the human organ transplant regulation made under the human organ transplant ordinance will be published in the government gazette tomorrow ( friday ) . </s>
<s> the ordinance and the regulation will come into force on a day to be appointed by the chief executive and the secretary for health and welfare respectively by notice in the gazette , which should be three months after the negative vetting procedure of the provisional legislative council . </s>
<s> announcing this today ( thursday ) , a spokesman for the human organ transplant board said : </s>
<s> " the ordinance provides for the prohibition of commercial dealings in human organs intended for transplant , </s>
<s> restricts the transplanting of human organs between persons not genetically related and regulates the importing of human organs intended for transplanting . " </s>
<s> the regulation will set out the means by which genetic relationship between an organ donor and a recipient may be established , specify the information on human organ transplants to be submitted to the board and the person who must submit it , and specify the additional information that must be supplied for imported organs . </s>
<s> " when the ordinance and regulation come into operation , </s>
<s> the responsible medical practitioner must obtain the prior approval of the board for any human organ transplant involving a live donor unless the donor is related to the recipient either genetically or by marriage which has subsisted for not less than three years , </s>
<s> " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> " in view of the need to process applications for transplant promptly , the board secretariat will accept and process applications which are submitted inside and outside office hours . </s>
<s> prescribed certificate / information must be submitted to the board before transplant involving the use of imported organs can take place , " he added . </s>
<s> any person who removes , transplants and disposes of organs removed from dead or living persons for the purpose of transplanting them into other persons , </s>
<s> whether obtained locally or imported , is required to supply prescribed information to the board in the appropriate statutory forms shown in the schedule to the regulation . </s>
<s> a set of administrative guidelines is being prepared for distribution to private and public hospitals , medical bodies and related organisations to advise those with the responsibility for transplant operations or importing of human organs intended for transplanting , </s>
<s> of the relevant procedures and legislative requirements . </s>
<s> in addition , a leaflet containing general information on the ordinance will be published for public distribution . </s>
<s> it is anticipated that the administrative guidelines and the leaflet will be available early next year . </s>
<s> members of the public can now assume a more active role against insecure and dangerous loading of goods vehicles to further enhance safety on roads . </s>
<s> the administrative officer ( administration ) of the transport department , miss christina chong yau @-@ ling , made this comment today ( thursday ) when introducing the newly designed report form on unsafe loads . </s>
<s> " the public are welcome to report and help facilitate police 's prosecution whenever and wherever they spot dangerously loaded vehicles with a potential threat to road users . </s>
<s> " all they have to do is to simply fill out a purposely @-@ designed form and fax or post it to the department for analysis and subsequent referral to the police for follow @-@ up action . </s>
<s> " the information supplied by reporters will assist in identifying which types of vehicles are more likely to involve in insecure loading and the locations where these vehicles are mostly found . " this can help the police to undertake their enforcement against insecure / dangerous loading , </s>
<s> " miss chong said . </s>
<s> the report form consists of a number of items for the officers responsible to obtain a brief outline of the allegation . </s>
<s> these include the registration mark of the reported vehicle , street name , nearby landmarks or buildings as well as the date and time when the reporter spotted the accused vehicle . </s>
<s> " the report form uses diagrams to give a clear indication to the public the correct and incorrect ways of transportation of goods . </s>
<s> " the public just have to tick the appropriate box next to the diagram which best describes the concerned vehicles , " miss chong added . </s>
<s> in 1997 ( january - september ) , there were a total of 15 accidents involving insecure loading in which one of them was classified as serious . </s>
<s> same accident rate was observed for 1996 . </s>
<s> in 1995 , there were a total of 26 such accidents , involving two fatal cases . </s>
<s> " though statistics showed that the accident rate is dropping , </s>
<s> the department still find it necessary to arouse public 's concern on insecure and dangerous loading of vehicles . </s>
<s> " unsafe loads pose a potential risk to road users . </s>
<s> it is the responsibility of all goods vehicle owners , operators and drivers to ensure that loads carried are safe and properly secured , " miss chong said . </s>
<s> the report forms will be available for collection at the four licensing offices : </s>
<s> * hong_kong licensing office , third floor , united centre , 95 queensway , hong_kong ; </s>
<s> * kowloon licensing office , ninth floor , park @-@ in commercial centre , 56 dundas street , kowloon ; </s>
<s> * kwun tong licensing office , fifth floor , kowloon east government offices , 12 lei yue mun road , kwun tong ; </s>
<s> and </s>
<s> * sha tin licensing office , fifth floor , citylink plaza , sha tin station , new territories . </s>
<s> the public can also obtain the report forms at the vehicles examination centres , the hong_kong school of motoring and the public enquiry service centres of the home affairs department . </s>
