<s> storage in hong_kong 's reservoirs at 9 am today ( monday ) stood at 87.1 per cent of capacity or 510.680 million cubic metres . </s>
<s> this time last year the reservoirs contained 561.520 million cubic metres of water , representing 95.8 per cent of capacity . </s>
<s> ce wraps up ' useful ' first day at apec leaders meeting </s>
<s> the first day of meetings by apec economic leaders were " useful and constructive " , says the hong_kong special administrative region chief executive , mr tung chee hwa . </s>
<s> mr tung spent the afternoon with the 17 other leaders of apec economies discussing the agenda of the leaders summit to be held on tuesday . </s>
<s> it was the first time mr tung had attended an apec leaders meeting and the first time hong_kong had taken part in the forum under the name " hong_kong , china " . </s>
<s> also on today 's diary was the official apec " family photo " , which shows a line @-@ up of apec economic leaders . </s>
<s> an afternoon session was taken up by discussions with apec business advisory council ( abac ) members . </s>
<s> discussions touched on trade and investment liberalisation , the cross @-@ border flow of goods , services and capital , </s>
<s> ease of travel for business purposes and the promotion of co @-@ operation in apec " ecotech " ( economic and technical co @-@ operation ) projects to facilitate equitable growth . </s>
<s> also discussed was the current trouble in the asian currency and financial markets , which mr tung expects to be a topic of major focus during the leaders summit , to be held at the museum of anthropology . </s>
<s> last night ( vancouver time ) , </s>
<s> mr tung took part in a vvip reception before attending the dinner and cultural performance hosted by the canadian prime minister , mr jean chretien , this year 's apec chair . </s>
<s> mr tung started his day with a bilateral meeting with new zealand prime minister , mr jim bolger . </s>
<s> mr tung said he and mr bolger agreed on the importance of ongoing trade liberalisation in the asia @-@ pacific region . </s>
<s> they also agreed that the current financial setbacks were a short @-@ term problem and that the next millennium would herald the asia @-@ pacific century . </s>
<s> after the bilateral meeting , mr tung told reporters that the current trouble in the asian financial markets would be an important area of discussion for the apec economic leaders . </s>
<s> " but let me emphasise , the fundamentals in asia continue to be strong , " he said . </s>
<s> " we have one of the highest savings rates , investment levels are high , workforces are very flexible , </s>
<s> trade is open . so all the good fundamentals are there . </s>
<s> " there needs to be some correction in the financial supervision and banking management but i am sure that corrections will be made and we will come out stronger than before . " </s>
<s> executive council approves bus fare increase </s>
<s> the executive council today ( tuesday ) approved a 7 % fare increase for kmb ( a reduction of 2.5 % on the 9.5 % increase sought by kmb ) , </s>
<s> an 8 % fare increase for cmb ( a reduction of 3 % on the 11 % increase sought by cmb ) , </s>
<s> and a 6 % fare increase for citybus ( a reduction of 2.7 % on the 8.7 % increase sought by citybus ) . </s>
<s> the new fares will take effect on december 1 , 1997. members noted cmb and citybus last increased their fares in march 1996 by a weighted average of 10.4 % and 9.6 % respectively . </s>
<s> kmb last increased the fares on its cross harbour routes in march 1996 and its kowloon and new territories routes in april 1996 by a weighted average of 3.6 % . </s>
<s> by december 1997 , the bus companies would have gone without any fare adjustments for over 20 months . </s>
<s> the forecast inflation between the last increase and the proposed date of fare increase in december 1997 is 9.5 % in the case of kmb , and 10 % in the case of cmb and citybus . </s>
<s> in their deliberations , members considered carefully the need to pitch bus fares at a level acceptable to the public , and the need to provide bus companies with a reasonable rate of return as an incentive for further service improvements . </s>
<s> other factors such as increases in operating costs , service development plans , cost economy measures and public acceptability were also taken into consideration . </s>
<s> " in approving the fare increases , members were mindful of the impact of the increase on inflation and public acceptability , </s>
<s> " a government spokesman said . </s>
<s> " the approved fare increase rates for kmb , cmb and citybus are 2.5 % , 2 % and 4 % below the forecast accumulated inflation respectively since the last fare rises . </s>
<s> the rates of increase , if annualized , are 4.14 % for kmb , </s>
<s> 4.5 % for cmb and 3.39 % for citybus . </s>
<s> the approved rates are all below the forecast accumulated annual inflation of 5.3 % . the approved fare rises together would only increase the consumer price index ( a ) by 0.14 % . " </s>
<s> " with the approved overall weighted average fare increase of 7 % , kmb 's forecast profit in 1998 will be similar to its 1996 level . </s>
<s> a 7 % fare increase would give the company a sufficient incentive to improve its operating efficiency , so as to achieve profit growth . " </s>
<s> as for cmb , </s>
<s> members noted that cmb had suffered from a continuous decline in patronage in recent years with a corresponding drop in its profitability . improvements to its staff retirement scheme since january 1997 had pushed up cmb 's operating costs by $ 40 million for 1996 / 97 . </s>
<s> without a fare increase , cmb would suffer a sizable loss in 1997 / 98 . </s>
<s> the approved overall weighted average fare increase of 8 % would enable cmb to recover the operating costs and to improve its services . </s>
<s> members noted that cmb had a low fare base . </s>
<s> even with a higher fare increase rate , its fares were still among the lowest of the three franchisees , and so were its profit levels . </s>
<s> without a fare increase , citybus 's forecast profit in 1998 would be much lower than those in 1996 and 1997 . </s>
<s> the approved overall weighted average fare increase of 6 % would give citybus an incentive for further investment to improve its services . </s>
<s> the spokesman added that under the new fares , more than 83 % of the passengers affected will have to pay no more than 50 cents more per trip . </s>
<s> the transport advisory committee ( tac ) today ( tuesday ) supported the government 's recommendations to cancel three hyf franchised routes and to revise lantau taxi fares . </s>
<s> speaking after the tac meeting , the chairman , dr cheng hon @-@ kwan , said : </s>
<s> " having regard to the drop in patronage of a number of hyf 's franchised routes , especially after the opening of the western harbour crossing , we consider that the north point - kowloon city vehicular ferry route , </s>
<s> the central - jordan road passenger ferry route and the central - tsuen wan via tsing yi passenger ferry route should be cancelled . " </s>
<s> the tac recommended that the north point - kowloon city vehicular ferry route and the central - jordan road passenger ferry route should be cancelled in january 1998 , </s>
<s> and the central - tsuen wan via tsing yi passenger ferry route should be cancelled when a replacement service is available sometime in september 1998 . </s>
<s> " we have considered carefully the impact on passengers being affected and the land transport alternatives available , </s>
<s> and conclude that the north point - kowloon city vehicular ferry route and the central - jordan road passenger route are not commercially viable , and replacement services are not necessary , " added dr cheng . </s>
<s> the tac also supported the government 's proposal to increase the lantau taxi fares by an average of 9.1 per cent with effect from early march 1998 . </s>
<s> " the fare revision is proposed taking into account increases in operating costs , changes in the operating environment and the financial position of the lantau taxi operators , </s>
<s> " said dr cheng . </s>
<s> the lantau taxi fares were last increased by 10 per cent in july 1996. the lantau taxi association has applied for a 10.2 per cent fare revision . </s>
<s> " we try to balance the interests of the taxi trade and passengers , and recommend a fare revision which is in line with inflation , </s>
<s> " said dr cheng . </s>
<s> the projected accumulated inflation for the period july 1996 ( the date of the last fare increase ) to march 1998 ( the proposed implementation date of the new fares ) is 9.2 per cent . </s>
<s> the recommended fares are as follows : </s>
<s> flagfall for first 2 km $ 11.00 $ 12.00 fare for every subsequent $ 1.10 $ 1.20 0.2 km waiting time charge for $ 1.10 $ 1.20 every 1 minute </s>
<s> the telephone booking surcharge and the surcharge for every article of baggage , animal or bird will remain at $ 5. </s>
<s> at the meeting , tac members were briefed on the existing provision of transport information and proposals for possible future development and enhancement . </s>
<s> members were also informed that the transport department would commission a consultancy study in mid @-@ 1998 on the feasibility of a traffic information and management centre as a move to improve the provision of traffic and transport information to the public . </s>
<s> energy codes should be practised on voluntary basis </s>
<s> the energy advisory committee today ( tuesday ) advised the government that the codes of practice setting standards for energy efficient design of buildings and building services and installations should be implemented initially on a voluntary basis . </s>
<s> the building energy codes cover the energy efficiency of a building and its essential systems , </s>
<s> including lighting , air @-@ conditioning , electrical , lift and escalator systems . </s>
<s> at its meeting today , the committee advised that these codes should be implemented through special efforts to gain the support of all concerned parties , </s>
<s> including a scheme of accreditation for energy @-@ efficient buildings . </s>
<s> under the scheme , any new building that fully complies with the codes will be eligible for accreditation as an energy @-@ efficient building . </s>
<s> a certificate of accreditation will be issued to the building 's owner and its name entered into a register kept by the electrical and mechanical services department . </s>
<s> the committee was also briefed on the progress of developing an " energy end @-@ use database " in hong_kong . </s>
<s> the database is a detailed set of statistics on energy use in different sectors of the community that can be analysed in different ways for a variety of purposes . </s>
<s> typical applications include identifying specific areas for improving energy productivity in hong_kong ; assessing the impact of transportation and environmental policies on hong_kong 's energy consumption ; </s>
<s> tracking trends in energy consumption and intensity ; and evaluating cost @-@ effectiveness of energy efficiency programmes and policies . </s>
<s> the committee was also briefed on energy management opportunities in public buildings in hong_kong and on the outcome of the public consultation exercise on the report on the feasibility of introducing a common carrier system for gas supply . </s>
<s> the committee noted that a consultancy study would be commissioned on the feasibility and economic justification for wider adoption of water @-@ cooled air conditioning systems in hong_kong . </s>
<s> water @-@ cooled air conditioning systems were more energy @-@ efficient than air @-@ cooled air conditioning systems . </s>
<s> the committee , which is chaired by professor charles kao kuen , advises the government on energy policy matters , </s>
<s> including energy efficiency and conservation . </s>
