<s> suspected case of h 5 n 1 detected </s>
<s> a suspected case of influenza a ( h 5 ) was detected as a result of enhanced surveillance activities taken by the department of health ( dh ) , </s>
<s> it was announced today ( friday ) . </s>
<s> the present suspected case involved a two @-@ year @-@ old boy with a congenital heart condition . </s>
<s> he made a full recovery and was discharged on november 9 . a nasopharyngeal aspirate taken from the patient was tested by the government virus unit and the preliminary test was positive for influenza a ( h 5 ) . </s>
<s> a specimen was sent to the centres for disease control ( cdc ) in the united_states for confirmation and the results are expected to be available next week . </s>
<s> the world health organisation was also informed of this suspected case . </s>
<s> speaking at a press briefing today , the deputy director of health , </s>
<s> dr paul saw assured the public that although a suspected case had occurred , there was no cause for panic as the suspected case was found to be unrelated to the first confirmed case and the patient involved in this case had made a full recovery . </s>
<s> " there is no evidence that the infection has widely spread in the community , " dr saw said . </s>
<s> " following the detection of the case , a special team of doctors and nurses of dh had conducted field investigations and laboratory tests . </s>
<s> " the dh team visited the patient and his family at their home and blood samples were taken for laboratory analysis . possible sources of exposure to the virus are being traced . </s>
<s> " the department is closely liaising with the agriculture and fisheries department , world health organisation and the centres on disease control to monitor the situation . " </s>
<s> dr saw said since the discovery of the first confirmed case of h 5 n 1 , </s>
<s> the dh had already stepped up its influenza surveillance activities and the successful detection of the suspected case reflected the effectiveness of this surveillance programme . </s>
<s> he advised that the best way to combat influenza infection was to build up body resistance by having a proper diet with adequate exercise and rest . </s>
<s> " good ventilation should be maintained to avoid the spread of respiratory tract inflection , " dr saw added . </s>
