<s> laws of hk launched on the internet </s>
<s> the statutory laws of hong_kong and a selection of constitutional documents are now available to anyone who has access to the internet . </s>
<s> the secretary for justice , ms elsie leung oi @-@ sie , today ( friday ) noted that this facility launched by the department of justice would greatly help in promoting public knowledge of these laws . </s>
<s> with the launch of the new system , the laws of hong_kong for the first time will be readily accessible to the public , to the legal profession in hong_kong and to interested persons and organisations around the world . </s>
<s> government staff who administer the various laws in their daily work will also benefit from having access to up @-@ to @-@ date laws . </s>
<s> with wider public understanding of the laws that apply to them in their everyday life , there should be greater awareness of and support for the rule of law , ms leung said . </s>
<s> the laws of hong_kong on the internet are being made available in both english and chinese , without charge . </s>
<s> an english / chinese glossary of terms used in the laws will also be available soon . </s>
<s> making blis ( bilingual laws information system ) available on the internet is one of the projects of the five @-@ year information systems strategy plan of the department of justice . </s>
<s> the plan , steered by the law draftsman , mr tony yen , </s>
<s> sets out to take maximum advantage of technology to improve the professional and administrative functions of the various divisions of the department . </s>
<s> the new system is developed by the department 's information technology & resources unit led by mr allan roger , a lawyer and qualified electronic engineering technologist ; together with staff of the information technology services department . </s>
<s> taking advantage of recent developments in technology , blis on the internet is user @-@ friendly and has a number of easy search functions . </s>
<s> anyone who already has computer access to the internet can use an internet browser program and the address : </s>
<s> www.justice.gov.hk to access blis . </s>
<s> alternatively , blis can be assessed through the home page of the department of justice at the address : www.info.gov.hk/justice/laws/index.htm. </s>
<s> to see the chinese version of the laws , chinese windows 3.1 or chinese windows 95 is required . </s>
<s> in view of the great interest shown by the legal and academic communities in hong_kong , </s>
<s> the new system will be demonstrated at meetings of the law society and bar association in the next two weeks . </s>
<s> major features of the blis database are : </s>
<s> * quick display of any section of an ordinance or subsidiary legislation , in either english or chinese . </s>
<s> * all common full @-@ text search functions are included , </s>
<s> such as searching for words , parts of words , combinations of words , words near other words , synonyms and word variations . </s>
<s> * as the program is microsoft windows based , users will be able to copy text from blis and paste it into other documents . </s>
<s> this will be particularly useful for lawyers and academics who frequently have to include extracts of the law in their working documents . </s>
<s> * users are not restricted to viewing the current law . </s>
<s> all changes to the law after june 30 , 1997 will be stored as separate documents and users will be able to choose to view the current law or the law as at any date after june 30 , 1997 . </s>
<s> users can also easily check to see if changes have been made to a particular section between two dates . </s>
<s> * the laws are expected to be kept current to within an average of three weeks . </s>
<s> when a change to the laws is made , </s>
<s> the blis editing staff will , within a day , mark each affected section with a pencil check mark icon to indicate that an amendment to the text is pending . </s>
<s> a section that does not have a pencil icon next to it can therefore be taken to be current up to the previous day . </s>
<s> the department welcomes comments from users of blis . a convenient e @-@ mail address facility is included on the blis home page for that purpose . </s>
<s> for a copy of the information brochure or for more information about gaining access to blis , contact can be made with the information technology and resources unit : </s>
<s> - by mail addressed to the department of justice ; </s>
<s> - by fax at 2862 5455 ; </s>
<s> or </s>
<s> - by phone at 2528 0154 . </s>
