<s> dh explains dispensing error involving anti @-@ fever syrup </s>
<s> the department of health ( dh ) today ( saturday ) confirmed that a dispensing error involving the mixing up of anti @-@ fever syrup with a mouthwash in 60 @-@ ml small bottles had occurred in the dispensary of the department 's cheung sha wan jockey club clinic . </s>
<s> a dh spokesman said : </s>
<s> " the dispensing error was found to have taken place on november 17 when staff of the dispensary inadvertently mixed up the anti @-@ fever syrup with the mouthwash in the bottling process because they were of the same pink colour . </s>
<s> " between november 17 and 25 , </s>
<s> 144 clients , aged between two months and six years , were issued with anti @-@ fever syrup in these 60 @-@ ml small bottles as a treatment for fever . </s>
<s> " the case came to light on november 25 and the department has been contacting all clients who might have been given the contaminated batch of medicine . " </s>
<s> the spokesman said so far , the department had successfully contacted 132 clients . </s>
<s> among them , 107 had turned up for assessment . </s>
<s> the children involved were examined and explanation and counselling were given to the parents . </s>
<s> the commonest symptoms reported by the parents were vomiting and loose stool . </s>
<s> at examination , all children involved were found to be well . </s>
<s> they chose not to bring their children back for assessment because they were well . for the remaining 12 clients who could not be reached by telephone , </s>
<s> the department had arranged home visits by health personnel . </s>
<s> " at the doses prescribed , it is unlikely that the contaminant will lead to serious side effects . nevertheless , </s>
<s> all clients will be closely followed up by the department , " the spokesman emphasised . </s>
<s> upon discovery of the dispensing error on november 25 , all contaminated medicine has been discarded . </s>
<s> he assured the public that this was an isolated incident only occurring in cheung sha wan jockey club dispensary between november 17 and 25 . </s>
<s> " precautionary measures have been instituted to prevent recurrences in future . these include a change in the colouring of the mouthwash as soon as possible . in the meantime , </s>
<s> " for the discomfort caused to the children and the inconvenience and anxiety caused to the parents , </s>
<s> the department wishes to extend its deepest apology and will do its best to help the families involved , " the spokesman added . </s>
<s> the department of health has set up this ( saturday ) evening a hotline to receive enquiries from families affected by the contaminated medicine in the dispensary of the cheung sha wan jockey club clinic between november 17 and 25 . </s>
<s> " the telephone number of the hotline is 2836 0239 , " a department spokesman said . </s>
<s> " the hotline will be manned throughout the night and tomorrow by doctors who will answer enquiries from the families affected and provide medical advice . " </s>
<s> in addition , staff will be available at cheung sha club jockey club clinic tomorrow from 9 am to 1 pm to provide medical examination and counselling service to affected children and their parents respectively . </s>
