<s> the marine department today ( saturday ) announced that starting from monday ( december 1 ) , </s>
<s> all vessels of 20,000 gross tonnage ( gt ) and above are required to embark and disembark pilots at the pilot boarding station off ngan chau ( also known as round island ) when entering and leaving hong_kong through the east lamma channel . </s>
<s> a spokesman for the marine department said that smaller vessels had the option of embarking and disembarking pilots at green island pilot boarding station . </s>
<s> " owners , agents and shipmasters who book pilots in compliance with such requirement must clearly nominate one or the other pilot boarding station , " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> " all vessels navigating in the vicinity should proceed with caution and give due consideration to those vessels maneuvering for the purpose of embarking or disembarking of pilots . " </s>
<s> the ngan chau pilot boarding station was established at outer entrance of the east lamma channel in december 1996 and all ships of 40,000 gt and over were required to pick up pilots there . </s>
<s> the second phase of the obligation comes into effect on december 1 this year which includes all ships of 20,000 gt or over into the measure . </s>
