<s> joint statement by finance ministers in kuala lumpur </s>
<s> the financial secretary , mr donald tsang , welcomed the endorsement by the meeting of the finance ministers held in kuala lumpur to develop a market @-@ based approach to address the intermediation problem in the region . </s>
<s> at the conclusion of the meeting of asean plus six ( australia , china , hong_kong , japan , korea and us ) today ( tuesday ) , </s>
<s> the finance ministers agreed that " there is an urgent need to develop a deep , liquid and mature debt market in asia to address the intermediation problem . </s>
<s> ministers strongly endorsed the initiative to develop a market @-@ based approach to mobilise private sector resources " . </s>
<s> " while the authorities in the region are preoccupied with fire fighting , </s>
<s> we should not lose sight of the need for fire prevention . developing a market @-@ based approach to address intermediation problem is the right way forward , " said mr tsang in kuala lumpur . </s>
<s> " i felt encouraged by the warm support i got this morning from other finance ministers on hong_kong 's suggested approach , " he added . </s>
<s> hong_kong will host the first meeting of technical experts to explore these ideas with the assistance of international financial institutions such as the world bank and the asian development bank . </s>
<s> mr tsang also shared the meeting consensus on the need to strengthen domestic financial systems and to foster closer collaborative efforts on financial regulation and supervision . </s>
<s> " we are all for more vigilant monitoring of domestic banking systems . </s>
<s> the hong_kong experience has shown the value of sound prudential standards in helping to withstand external shocks to the banking system . " </s>
<s> earlier on , mr tsang welcomed the undertaking by the international monetary fund to examine how " below the line " hedging activities of domestic activities should be monitored . </s>
<s> the meeting of the finance ministers of asean plus six in kuala lumpur will be adjourned today and mr tsang is due back in hong_kong at 9.30 pm this ( tuesday ) evening . </s>
<s> further amendments to public housing rent </s>
<s> the chief executive in council approved today ( tuesday ) the housing authority 's ( ha ) proposal that legislative amendments to the housing ( amendment ) ordinance 1997 should be introduced so as to minimise the operational and financial difficulties and legal ambiguities created before bringing the further amended legislation into operation . </s>
<s> the secretary for housing , mr dominic wong , said that legislative amendments will be introduced into the provisional legislative council early in 1998 : </s>
<s> - to provide for a clear definition of the median rent to income ratio ( mrir ) and to allow the ha to maintain its present practice of determining the mrir of public rental housing tenants ; </s>
<s> - to replace the three @-@ year rent review cycle prescribed by the amendment ordinance by the well @-@ established two @-@ year review cycle , </s>
<s> but to exclude from this restriction better @-@ off tenants who are required to pay additional or market rent and beneficiaries of the rent assistance scheme ; </s>
<s> and </s>
<s> - to exclude from the scope of the amendment ordinance licence fees charged in respect of cottage areas and interim housing . </s>
<s> the housing ( amendment ) ordinance 1997 , passed by the previous legislative council on june 28 , 1997 , </s>
<s> provides that : </s>
<s> - no rent adjustment shall cause the overall mrir of households living in the ha 's public rental estates to exceed 10 per cent ; </s>
<s> - rent adjustment by the ha shall be implemented no more frequently than once every three years ; and </s>
<s> - the amendment ordinance shall come into operation on a day to be appointed by the secretary for housing . </s>
<s> at the request of the secretary for housing , the ha completed and submitted an assessment of the full implications of the amendment ordinance at the end of september . </s>
<s> " the report confirmed that implementation of the amendment ordinance would create operational and financial difficulties and legal ambiguities . the ha proposed that legislative amendments should be introduced to minimise these problems before bringing the further amended legislation into operation , </s>
<s> on operational difficulties , </s>
<s> the amendment ordinance will prevent the ha from varying rents for a fixed period since the last rent review exercise , </s>
<s> in addition , </s>
<s> the ha is obliged to conduct comprehensive surveys of incomes of all households living in public rental estates at least twice each year in order to determine the overall mrir . tenants are also obliged to provide accurate details of their incomes . </s>
<s> this will arouse resentment from tenants and incur high administrative costs of about $ 64 million a year . </s>
<s> the original intention of the amendment ordinance is not directed at licence fees paid by those living in cottage areas and interim housing . </s>
<s> failure to specify clearly how the determination of the mrir is to be made may expose the ha to legal challenges which will affect its normal operations . </s>
<s> on the financial side , </s>
<s> the statutory 10 per cent mrir ceiling will lead to revenue foregone of $ 1.7 billion , and the change to a three @-@ year rent review cycle will result in revenue foregone of $ 5.2 billion , </s>
<s> making a total revenue foregone of $ 6.9 billion between 1997 @-@ 98 and 2005 @-@ 06 . </s>
<s> the three @-@ year rent review arrangement will also mean a higher cumulative rate of increase for each rent review exercise and thus make it more difficult for public housing tenants to adjust to new rental levels . </s>
<s> " introducing legislative amendments to the amendment ordinance is a pragmatic way forward to deal with the specific problems created by the amendment ordinance , whilst respecting the spirit of the law , </s>
<s> " mr wong said . </s>
<s> although retaining the statutory 10 per cent mrir ceiling will result in $ 1.7 billion revenue foregone by the ha by 2005 @-@ 06 , </s>
<s> it can be implemented without causing serious operational and legal problems in the short term . </s>
<s> in the long term , it will also undermine the established policy that public housing rents should be based on affordability on the part of tenants . </s>
<s> the administration and the ha will need to address these aspects at an appropriate time in future . </s>
<s> review of education @-@ related executive and advisory bodies </s>
<s> in response to press enquiries , </s>
<s> a spokesman for the education and manpower bureau ( emb ) today ( tuesday ) confirmed that the review of the present system of the education @-@ related executive and advisory bodies is under way . </s>
<s> " the review is one of the major recommendations of the education commission report no. 7 on quality school education . the chief executive has undertaken that the administration will conduct this review in his first policy address , </s>
<s> " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> " this is a macro review being undertaken by the emb of the roles , functions and inter @-@ relationships of some 30 education @-@ related executive and advisory bodies . </s>
<s> in addition , we have commissioned a consultancy study on the organisational and management structure of the education department ( ed ) , having regard to its interface with other bodies in the government and the schools sector . </s>
<s> the two exercises are closely related . </s>
<s> " the macro review aims to streamline the present system of education @-@ related executive and advisory bodies with a view to making the system more responsive , </s>
<s> efficient and effective . </s>
<s> " we have invited three internationally renowned and accomplished educationalists to advise the emb in the course of the review . they are the pro @-@ vice chancellor of the university of hong_kong , professor k m cheng ; the former director @-@ general of the ministry of education in denmark , </s>
<s> all of them have profound knowledge of the education systems and practices in various parts of the world . </s>
<s> " the three experts will meet various education bodies in hong_kong next week to collate views on how the existing system can be improved . </s>
<s> they are expected to give their comments to the emb before the end of this year . </s>
<s> " as regards the consultancy study on the ed , a consultancy firm has been appointed and the study is expected to be completed in four months ' time . </s>
<s> the consultancy firm will examine the present organisational and management structure of the department , identify those aspects of ed 's work and procedures that can be streamlined or reduced , and make recommendations for improvements . </s>
<s> " the outcome of these two exercises will represent another major contribution towards government 's objective to raise the quality of education in hong_kong , " he said . </s>
