<s> personal data deleted from goods vehicles </s>
<s> vehicle owners will no longer have to display their personal particulars on goods vehicles , </s>
<s> special purpose vehicles and trailers from december 15 ( monday ) onwards . </s>
<s> speaking on the new arrangements today ( thursday ) , a spokesman for the transport department said : </s>
<s> " at present , these vehicle owners are required to paint their names , addresses as well as the permitted gross vehicle weight and maximum permitted axle weight upon conspicuous places on their vehicles . </s>
<s> " this is for the convenience of the police in taking enforcement action against irresponsible drivers and vehicle owners . </s>
<s> " in a review of this regulation , </s>
<s> the department has decided to make amendments to tie in with global changes and the requirements of the personal data ( privacy ) ordinance . " </s>
<s> the road traffic ( construction and maintenance of vehicles ) regulation was amended and gazetted in may this year . </s>
<s> under the amendments , the statutory requirement to paint the names and addresses of the vehicle owners upon conspicuous spaces on goods vehicles , special purpose vehicles and trailers was deleted . </s>
<s> however , owners of these vehicle types still have to display the permitted gross vehicle weight and maximum permitted axle weight until they have attained a valid vehicle licence containing the information . </s>
<s> " a new type of vehicle licence added with these information has been issuing to the public since october , </s>
<s> " the spokesman said . </s>
<s> moreover , the requirement for public light buses to mark the registration mark of the vehicles , names and addresses of the owners in a conspicuous place inside the vehicles will also be repealed from december 15 . </s>
