<s> during the visit , mr tung toured the air quality laboratory where he was shown how air pollution was measured and transformed into the air pollution index . </s>
<s> mr tung then visited the water microbiology laboratory where the beach monitoring programme was introduced . </s>
<s> the programme aims to provide the public up @-@ to @-@ date information on beach water quality and to identify any areas that require remedial action . </s>
<s> programmes and plans to further improve the environment were also introduced . </s>
<s> in expressing his appreciation for the work the department has done in protecting the environment and improving environmental awareness in the community , mr tung said that the government was committed to creating a cleaner and healthier environment for hong_kong in the years to come . </s>
<s> " improving the quality of the environment is as vital as economic growth to improving our quality of life . </s>
<s> we will ensure that consideration of how to sustain and enhance the environment is built into strategic planning and policy making , " he said . </s>
<s> noting that a waste reduction plan would be launched next year , mr tung said that the government would examine all processes to see where it could be more efficient in handling and reducing waste . </s>
<s> " keeping hong_kong clean is everyone 's responsibility . sensible planning and action to reduce waste will enhance our competitiveness , </s>
<s> " he added . </s>
<s> mr law said it was most encouraging to have the chief executive 's support for the department 's work in protecting the environment . </s>
<s> " support from the highest levels within the government , and also from the general community , is essential if we are to see real improvements in hong_kong 's environmental conditions " , </s>
<s> he said . </s>
<s> hk continues to be world @-@ class service economy </s>
<s> hong_kong will continue its development into the 21 st century as a world class , high value @-@ added service economy and the premier services centre in the asia @-@ pacific region . </s>
<s> and it will focus on the highest part of the value @-@ added chain . </s>
<s> the deputy secretary for trade and industry , mr tam wing @-@ pong , said this today ( friday ) at a luncheon meeting of the regional conference on marketing & market research organised by the trade development council with the co @-@ operation of the market research society of hong_kong and the hong_kong institute of marketing . </s>
<s> he said much was being done to sustain hong_kong 's strength and ensure its competence for the challenge lying ahead in the millennium . </s>
<s> " chief among these is that hong_kong will maintain our firm hold on free trade policy . we know too well that this is the key to hong_kong 's success . </s>
<s> " the government see its role in ensuring a level playing field for all and to provide the necessary infrastructure . </s>
<s> hence , work is well in place to ensure that there will be world @-@ class physical and ' soft ' infrastructures for the development of our economy , </s>
<s> and put in place the right policies and measures . " </s>
<s> such physical infrastructure included port , airport , roads , railways , bridges , utilities , telecommunications network and other on @-@ going developments . </s>
<s> " soft " infrastructure included the rule of law , a level @-@ playing field , a clean and efficient civil service , </s>
<s> and free flow of information . </s>
<s> " our showcase new airport will be opening soon connecting hong_kong to all parts of the world of the 21 st century . </s>
<s> " we are developing our hong_kong information infrastructure to make sure hong_kong is a leader into the information age . " </s>
<s> since services would remain the mainstay of hong_kong 's future economic development , </s>
<s> the government had launched the services promotion programme in 1995 under the aegis of a task force chaired by the financial secretary , mr tam said . </s>
<s> it reviewed the government 's work supporting the services sector undertaken by various bureaux and departments and framed new initiatives and brought all into a coherent services promotion programme . </s>
<s> the result was published in a final report in march this year . </s>
<s> besides , as the services sector cut across the responsibilities of many bureaux , </s>
<s> the government had set up a dedicated business and services promotion unit in the financial secretary 's office in may 1997 to co @-@ ordinate and support the efforts of various government bureaux and agencies to implement the services promotion programme . </s>
<s> a high @-@ powered services promotion strategy group comprising academic people , </s>
<s> leading business figures and senior officials had been formed to advise the financial secretary on matters relating to the development of hong_kong as a service economy and as a pre @-@ eminent services centre in asia . </s>
<s> mr tam said another area the government saw its role in was to strive for the best possible access into the markets of its trading partners . </s>
<s> " trade in services is an integral part of our efforts . </s>
<s> we are adamant to ensure full , faithful implementation of the general agreement on trade in services and have been participating actively in the sectoral talks in telecommunications , financial services and maritime transport . </s>
<s> " early liberalisation of trade in services is also part of the asia pacific economic co @-@ operation 's goal as economies strive for free and open trade and investment in the region by 2010 or 2020 . </s>
<s> " we are also taking an active part in the world trade organisation working group in trade and investment and the organisation for economic co @-@ operation and development negotiation in the conclusion of the multilateral agreement on investment . </s>
<s> " liberalisation in investment would be an important factor contributing to the future role of hong_kong as a services and financial centre in the region , " he said . </s>
<s> mr tam added that all these active efforts , combined with the strong economic fundaments of hong_kong , and the promising development of the region in the long term , </s>
